(1, 'E2-0001AC', '1', 'Conference Proceedings : Electrical Engineering Computer Science ', 'Route 23, Box 620 Claverack, NY 12513', 'Curran Associates, Inc. ', 'Sep-91', 'Pricelist of Proceedings', '', '', '', '', 'uploads\\1773893353616-E2-0001AC Conference Proceedings _ Electrical Engineering Computer Science .pdf', NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-17 08:36:49', '2026-03-17 08:36:49'),
(2, 'E2-0002AC', '', '16th IIEE Annual National Convention : \"Sufficiency in Electrical Energy - A Challenge to IIEE\"', '', 'Institute of Integrated Electrical Engineers of the Phils., Inc. (IIEE)', 'Manila Midtown Hotel : November 26-29, 1991', '', '', 'Optimizing Power System Reliability\nDel Mundo, Rowaldo R. ', '', 'Electric utility\nReliability\nReliable system\nPower interruptions\nElectric power system', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(3, 'E2-0003AC', '', '22nd mid-year general membership meeting : \"New Electrical Engineering Law (RA 7920) : IIEE\'s Key to Professional Upliftment & Social Responsibility ', '', 'Institute of Integrated Electrical Engineers of the Phils., Inc. (IIEE)', 'Philippine International Convention Center World Trade Center CCP Complex, Roxas Blvd., Pasay City : July 9-12, 1997', '', 'Technical Papers ', 'Proposed Philippine Photovoltaic Standards\nDel Mundo, Rowaldo R. ', 'The application of solar photovoltaic (PV) technology is becoming popular due to increasing awareness and concern in the environment. The PV experience in the Philippines since the early \'80s have indicated that many failures in PV systems can be attributed to the lack of standards in PV products and in systems design, installation, operation and maintenance practices. This paper presents the Proposed Philippine Photovoltaic Standards developed by the Solar Laboratory of the University of the Philippines for adoption by the Institute of Integrated Electrical Engineers of the Philippines (IIEE) and the Bureau of Product Standards (BPS) of the Department of Trade and Industry. ', 'Solar Photovoltaic Technology\nPhotovoltaic Systems\nPhotovoltaic Standards \nInstitute of Integrated Electrical Engineers of the Philippines (IIEE)\nBureau of Product Standards (BPS)\nDepartment of Trade and Industry', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(4, 'E2-0004AC', '', '13th Annual National Convention : \"Electrical Technology for Higher Productivity\"', '', 'Institute of Integrated Electrical Engineers of the Phils., Inc. (IIEE)', 'Westin Philippine Plaza : November 17-20, 1988', '', '', 'Impact of Power Interruptions on National Economy\nViray, Francisco L. \nDel Mundo, Rowaldo R. ', '', 'Power interruptions\nNational Economy', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(5, 'E2-0005AC', '', '\"IIEE : realizing its vision\"\n19th annual national convention\n ', '', 'Institute of Integrated Electrical Engineers of the Phils., Inc. (IIEE)', 'Manila Midtown Hotel : November 26-29, 1991', '', '', 'DOE Guidelines on Electrical Design for Energy Conservation\nDel Mundo, Rowaldo R. \n', '', 'Energy consumption\nDepartment of Energy (DOE)\nEnergy conserving design\nUtility systems\nEfficient energy utilization\nDepartment of Public Works and Highways (DPWH)\nReferral Code\nNational Building Code \nEnergy--Buildings \nPhilippine Electric Energy Consumption\nEnd-Use Energy Index--Buildings\nPower Sector\nEnergy consumption--Buildings \nElectrical Design\nDesign Illuminance Levels\nBuilding Lighting Systems\nMotors\nTransformers\nPower Distribution', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(6, 'E2-0006AC', '', 'Coswen\'97 : 1997 Conference on Ocean, Solar & Wind Energy ', '', 'Department of Energy and Society for the Advancement of Technology Management in the Philippines', 'Manila : New World Hotel, December 1, 1997', '', '', 'Solar PV Technologies for Pole Vaulting in the Energy Sector \nDel Mundo, Rowaldo R. \nCruz, Erwin Vic', '', 'PV Technology--Asia\nPV Technology Experience--Philippines\nCrystalline Silicon Solar Cells\nEnergy Pole Vaulting\nU.P. Solar Laboratory\nCore Competency Building', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(7, 'E2-0007AC', '2', 'King Mongkut\'s Institute Technology Ladkrabang : Faculty of Engineering Brochure', 'Thailand : Bangkok', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(8, 'E2-0008AC', '', 'Participation of State and Private Universities and Colleges on Implementation and Development of Information Technology\nComputer Aided Design (CAD) / Computer Aided Engineering (CAE) Skills Training Program', 'Makati Avenue, Makati, Metro Manila, Philippines ', 'ATS Technologies, Inc. ', 'ATS ADVANCED APPLICATIONS TRAINING CENTER\n118A & 119A Ground Floor, The Atrium of Makati, August 10, 1990', 'News Releases\nTechnical Papers ', '', 'Towards a Common Database for Architects, Engineers, Surveyors, Contractors & Developers\nDr T H Ang ', 'This paper describes the problem of information management in the building industry. It looks into some of the factors which has contributed to the problem. A manual approach to solve this problem using the CI/SfB system is briefly discussed. Computer-based applications using CAD and other software will also be covered. Finally, the paper discusses some of the new innovations in information management which will further assist in this task of creating a common database for the building industry. ', 'Information management \nBuilding industry\nComputer-based applications\nComputer aided design', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(9, 'E2-0009AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Practical Computer Applications in Architecture \nATS Software Centre Pte Ltd\n10 Anson Road, #03-05/0', '', 'Computer aided design \nComputer aided engineering', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(10, 'E2-0010AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Utilizing graphics facilities in computer aided structural/stress analysis and design \nAssociation o', '', 'Computer aided strucutural engineering solutions ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(11, 'E2-0011AC', '', 'Enhancing the implementation of AFMA through improved agricultural engineering standards ', '', 'AMTEC \nAgricultural Machinery Testing and Evaluation Center\nUniversity of the Philippines Los Baños, College, Laguna ', 'April 11, 2002', 'Draft Standards on \nEngineering Materials - Bolts and Nuts - Part 1 : Specifications and Applications for Agricultural Machines', '', '', '', 'Agricultural engineering standards ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(12, 'E2-0012AC', '3', 'Mena, Marino M.\nDean, College of Engineering\n1979-1985', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Fundamentals of Environmental Engineering Education\nMarino M. Mena ', 'The engineer plays an important role in development and change. However, the traditional concept of development has been a compromise between what is technically feasible and what is considered economically attractive. The increasing environmental problems associated with engineering development projects has made the engineering profession modify this traditional concept. This means that, today, development has to be a compromise between what is technically feasible, what is considered economically attractive, and what is acceptable on environmental grounds. If engineers can be  educated and trained with regard to the important environmental issues of the day, they would then be better prepared to understand the environmental consequences of their actions. This is the essence of the environmental education and training of engineers. ', 'Environmental Engineering Education', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(13, 'E2-0013AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'An Overview of Solid Waste Management \nMarino M. Mena ', '', 'Solid Waste Management ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(14, 'E2-0014AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Solid Waste Management : An Integrated Approach\nMarino M. Mena ', '', 'Solid Waste Management ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(15, 'E2-0015AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Solid Waste Management : Its Value-Education Component \nMarino M. Mena ', 'Solid waste management is an environmental problem. As such the problem has many aspects : social, technical, economic, financial, political. An effective solution to the problem requires a process of change in which human attitudes and behaviors are modified so that in endeavors to address it holistically goals, strategies and plans are established and implemented in the most efficient way. To accomplish this process of change, a solid waste management program has to have a value-education component. This paper focuses on this specific issue. ', 'Solid Waste Management ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(16, 'E2-0016AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Sanitary Landfill Technology : An Overview of Design, Construction, Monitoring, Operation and Econom', 'This paper deals with an overview of the general activities involved in the application of sanitary landfill technology which includes design, construction, monitoring, operation and economic analysis. Detailed discussions of each activity are made in separate papers. It is the purpose of this paper to give the reader a general overview of the various stages in the application of sanitary landfill technology for the disposal of solid wastes. Let it be said that site location is an integral part of design and that sanitary landfill technology when properly designed, properly constructed, well operated and maintained, and adequately monitored are acceptable on environmental grounds.', 'Sanitary landfill technology', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(17, 'E2-0017AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Question of concern : how could we return public trust in sanitary landfill technology \nMarino M. Me', '', 'Sanitary landfill technology ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
