(163, 'E2-0163AC', '8', 'New Marian Gold Mine\n\nAdditional Information on Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA)', 'Metro Manila, Philippines ', 'Vulcan Industrial and Mining Corporation, 4th Floor, Quad Alpha Centrum Bldg., 125 Pioneer st. Mandaluyong ', 'July 1990', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(164, 'E2-0164AC', '', 'Central Azucarera Don Pedro (CADP) Sugar Factory Project', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Central Azucarera Don Pedro (CADP) sugar refinery is designed to produce 550 tons of refined sugar and 30 tons of final molasses daily. The adjoining CADP raw sugar factory shall supply 50% of the total annual raw sugar requirements while 50% shall be taken from outside sources.\n\nThe proposed project site shall be located inside the existing 40 hectare CADP raw sugar factory in Barangay Lumbangan, Nasugbu, Batangas. The plant shall occupy a total land area of 7,200 m2. The total capital investment of the project is P 500 million. The workforce needed by the project during construction shall vary at different stages of the project ranging from 20 to 642 men. During operations, workforce requirement is approximately 120 men. Hiring of locally available qualified men during the implementation of the project shall be prioritized.\n\nThe processes involved in sugar refining are affination, carbonation, filtration, decolorization, evaporation and crystallization. The total water requirement of the sugar refining process shall be taken from Lian River at a rate of 0.9 m3/sec. A spray pond shall be provided to recycle the cooling water especially during dry months where Lian River flow is low.\n\nThe construction phase of the project will last for one year. The construction site preparation is minimal. It only involves the demolition of the existing warehouse in the site. Build-up of localized suspended particulate matter concentration will only occur within the vicinity of the project site. Noise levels may increase but will be confined within the CADP compound. \n\nDuring operation, the wastewater effluents generated can be classified into spent acids, spent brine and gas scrubber wastewaters. The existing wastewater treatment scheme of CADP shall be used but with some improvements. An installation of an additional ash settling pond to accomodate the gas scrubber effluent and maximum utilization of wastewater or irrigation by acquisition of mobile irrigation pumps and sprinklers are recommended. \n\nThe workers health and safety shall be protected by the existing CADP House Safety Rules and Regulations. Construction safety and goodhousekeeping manuals were developed. Workers health are monitored by conducting annual physical examination. Training on fire prevention and control are regularly conducted. Personnel protective devices are provided to all employees of CADP involved in plant construction and operation. \n\nAn environmental monitoring program is recommended to assure that wastewater facilities are working on their expected efficiency, provide a record for future plans of improving the treatment scheme and to seek compliance with the DENR standards. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(165, 'E2-0165AC', '', 'General Conditions and Specification\n\nPhysical Science Bldg\nUP College of Agriculture', '', '', '', 'Sections\nGeneral Conditions of the Contract\nSpecial Provisions of the Contract\nPreparation of Site\nFoundation\nConcrete & Reinforced Concrete\nConcrete Blocks\nBricks\nWaterproofing\nCarpentry\nCeiling work\nHardware\nToilet room accessories\nCeramic tiles\nVinyl Asbestos Tiles\nStell Clad Doors\nSteel Windows\nGlass & Glazing\nMiscellaneous Metal Works\nPainting\nPlumbing Works\nSteam Water Supply System\nExhaust System\nAir Conditioning Work Room Dehumidifiers & Water Coolers\nCompressed Air System\nCentral Air Conditioning System\nElectrical Works ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(166, 'E2-0166AC', '', 'Environmental Impact Statement\n\nCathay Pacific Steel Corporation\nProposed Wire Rod Mill', 'Quezon City', 'Brgy. San Bartolome, Novaliches ', 'July 1992', 'Section\nName and Address of Project Proponent\nType of Project\nOverview Summary\nProject Setting\nThe Project/Proposal\nA Brief History of Past Environmental Conditions and a Description of Existing Environmental and Resource Use\nFuture Environmental Conditions Without the Project\nPrediction and Assessment of Impacts and Suggested Mitigating Measures\nContingency Plans\nEnvironmental Briefing and Monitoring ', '', '', 'Cathay Pacific Steel Corporation (CAPASCO) proposes to set up a wire rod mill capable of producing 45 metric tons (MT) per hour or about 300,000 MT annually from imported and locally available steel billets to serve the growing needs of the steel wire and rod industyr of the country. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(167, 'E2-0167AC', '', 'Environmental Impact Assessment for Sipalay Copper Mine of Maricalum Mining Corporation San Jose, Sipalay, Negros Occidental \n\nPart I', '', '', 'November 1991', 'Table of Contents\n(Part I)\nChapter 1 - Introduction\nChapter 2 - Project Description\nChapter 3 - Environmental Setting\nChapter 4 - Environmental Impacts of the Mining Operation\nChapter 5 - Mitigating Measures \nChapter 6 - Abandonment\nChapter 7 - Monitoring ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(168, 'E2-0168AC', '', 'Background Information and Terms of Reference \n\nSecond Airports Development Project ', 'Philippines ', 'Asian Development Bank', '', '', '', '', 'The objectives of the TA are to (i) examine the policy and institutional reforms that are necessary to provide the framework the sustainable and effective development of the civil aviation sector, (ii) update and upgrade the Master Plan in order to identify the infrastructure investment requirements for the civil aviation sector up to the year 2010, and (iii) identify and prepare a high priority project that is focused on alleviating key infrastructure bottlenecks. The identified project may then be proposed by the Government for external financing. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(169, 'E2-0169AC', '', 'Environmental Impact Statement\n\nDavao Union Cement Corporation', 'Metro Manila ', '2nd Floor Phinma Building\n166 Salcedo st., Legaspi Village,\nMakati', '', 'Name and Address of Project Proponent\nLead Agency\nType of Project\nOverview Summary\nThe Project Setting\nThe Proposal\nA Brief History of Past Environmental Conditions and A Description of the Existing Environmental and Resource Use\nFuture Environmental Conditions Without The Project Prediction and Assessment of Impacts\nContingency Plans\nEnvironmental Briefings and Monitoring \nMitgating Measures\nResidual/Unavoidable Impacts\nInformation Deficiencies\nAttachments', '', '', 'The proposed Dry Process Plant has a rated capacity of 3500 TPD or 1 Million Ton Clinker/year will be an expansion of the existing two units (wet & dry) process plant of Davao Union Cement Corporation (DUCC), located at Bo. Ilang, Davao City. The proposed plant is a modernization of the existing plant and will be constructed adjacent to the existing kiln facilities. The proposed dry process plant has an air suspension in preheater with precalciner and kiln feed system that minimize false air, which has a lower fuel consumption compared to the existing wet & dry process plant. Coal firing facilities that utilize more effectively the coal rejects that the existing wet process plant currently produces. \n\nThe new plant will share compound with the existing DUCC plant so that there will be no additional clearing of the area covered. \n\nCement manufacture is the process where in limestone, shale and silica components are ground together in proportion of approximately 87% limestone, 9% shale and 4% Silica. After grinding, the mixture called the raw meal is homogenized and fed to a Rotary Kiln where it is burned at approximately 1450 deg. centrigrade. The output product of the kiln is called cement cliner. It is cooled, crushed and then ground with 5% gypsum proportion by a ball mill to produce portland cement. The clinker could also be ground with pozzolanic material & slag to produce other types of cement like pozzolan or primero. The finished product is pneumatically conveyed to the packhouse for packing and delivery. \n\nThe probable environmental impact here will be on the nearby communities including the residents of Davao City and other neighboring towns which will be benefited with job opportunities and other money generating pursuits in life, as well as other socio-economic benefits. \n\nAnother environmental impact here is on the dust emission during the operation of the plant. Such air pollution is being taken cared-of and controlled by implementing measures, such as installation of electrostatic precipitators, dust collecting and multi-cyclones before every emission points. Process water will continue to be taken from Ilang River beside the plant with appropriate water treatment of water before it is utilize as coolant for the grinding mills, kiln and other equipments. The used cooling water will be collected in a setling pond and shall be recycled so that no water is discharged outside the plant and make-up water from the river will be at a low level and volume. Other major equipments will be enclosed in a building to abate noise pollution. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(170, 'E2-0170AC', '', 'Environment Impact Statement\n\nCasecnan Transbasin Diversion Project (CTDP) Irrigation Component ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
