(253, 'E2-0253AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'A proposal to establish a computating facility for computer-aided engineering, design, and manufactu', 'The establishment of a Training and Research Facility for VLSI Technology and Systems is an urgent and pressing need if the country\'s goal of infusing microelectronic technology before the year 2000 is to be achieved. \nThe funding requested is US$529,500 over a period of three years excluding counterpart funds to be requested from the Philippine government. This may seem a large amount at first glance, however, this what is needed. Corporations spend many times more just to maintain their momentum. With this comparatively small amount, the proponent aims to accelerate the industry\'s momentum.\nSpecifically, local industry will benefit from this project in the following ways : 1) a ready pool of young talent; 2) availability of training for their in-house pool of engineers; 3) a low risk means by which to sample VLSI technology; and 4) a local pool of experts whom they may tap as they climb the learning curve of VLSI. All of these translate to a highly conducive environment for the local electronics industry to grow. \nThe project is also beneficial to the donor country aside from the goodwill generated by its interaction with Philippine project members. Significant will be the exposure received by the donor country\'s related industries. This is the crucial time since few cooperative ties have been established in the area of microelectronics and more so in the field of VLSI design. It would be to the advantage of the donor country if the software and foundry services were sourced there. \nIn summary, it is the sincere conviction of the proponent and his colleagues that given such a facility with the direction set for it in this proposal, the Philippine\'s electronics industry will be on the right path towards a better future. ', 'Training/Research Facility for VLSI Technology and Systems ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(254, 'E2-0254AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Republic Act No. 6959. An act establishing provincial centers for science and technology in all prov', '', 'Salonga, Jovito R.\nMitra, Ramon V.\nAcoba, Edwin P.\nAbad Santos, Quirino D. Jr. \nAquino, Corazon C. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(255, 'E2-0255AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1989, January 12-13) Keynote address by Dr. Ruben A. Garcia\nFirst annual Asian CAD training confere', '', 'Garcia, Dean Ruben A. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(256, 'E2-0256AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1989, March 27) The Application Form for Japan\'s Grant Aid \nProject Title : Upgrading the U.P. Coll', 'The \"strategic importance of science and technology in socio-economic development\", basically in the \"attainment of quality and productivity in the country\'s industry and agriculture\" is fittingly emphasized in a recent report to the President of the Philippines. It specifically states that \"acquiring science and technology manpower and financial support is the most important task for science and technology development\". The College of Engineering in the University of the Philippines can contribute directly to the attainment of making the Philippines a newly industrialized economy at the turn of the century by training the best students in engineering specifically at the graduate level, in fields relevant to the priority production sectors identified by the Presidential Task Force, such as, energy, electronics, metals and engineering, information technology and processing industries, among others. ', 'Grant aid--Japan\nUP College of Engineering upgrade', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
