(361, 'E2-0361AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1986, August 18) Appointment to the College Committee on Private Scholarships in Engineering ', 'Appointed to compose the College Committee on Private Scholarships in Engineering with Dr. Regano G. Benito as Chairman for a period two years effective, August 18, 1986. The other member is Ms. Marilou P. Dalida. \nThe Committee is in charge of selecting grantees as well as in formulating rules, policies and guidelines affecting private scholarships in engineering. ', 'Benito, Dr. Regano G.\nEscoto, Prof. Angela D.\nGarcia, Ruben A. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(362, 'E2-0362AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1987, September 9) Diliman Technology Park Feasibility Study Project Sponsored by the Philippine Na', 'During the National Science and Technology Week Celebration last year the then National Research Council of the Philippines (now the Philippine National Science Society) and the National Engineering Center, University of the Philippines co-sponsored a symposium on technology parks. The consensus of the symposium participants at that time was that there is a need to study the feasibility of putting up one such technology park for the Diliman Science Community. ', 'Garcia, Ruben A. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(363, 'E2-0363AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1987, November 3) Five year development plan ', 'The U.P. College of Engineering is formulating a five-year development plan and we are soliciting your help by requesting you to accomplish the attached questionnaire. The survey seeks to determine the opinion of our faculty and alumni on what particular area the college must focus its resources to in the next five years. ', 'Garcia, Ruben A. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(364, 'E2-0364AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1987, October 2) U.P. delegation to Hua Chiao University, PROC ', 'This is to request the participation of Dr. Adolfo Jesus R. Gopez who is an officer of your unit in the UP Delegation to Hua Chiao University, PROC. This is a UP System delegation which will explore the possibilities of cooperation and exchange with leading universities in China. The delegation will leave on October 22, Thursday and be back by November 8, Sunday. Processing of travel papers will be done at the Central Administration Level and the participation of Dr. Gopez in the delegation will not entail additional expenses from your unit except for his salary during the period of travel. ', 'Garcia, Ruben A. \nLee, Emeteria P. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(365, 'E2-0365AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1987, October 8) Invitation to participate in energy workshop. Prof. Rañeses accepts invitation.', 'Received TLX. Prof. Nestor Rañeses accepts invitation to participate in energy workshop in Jakarta 3-7 Nov. Please send details of workshop and arrangements. ', 'Garcia, R. A. \nDang, Dr. Giap', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(366, 'E2-0366AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1987, October 8) Ad-Hoc Committee for the food service in the College ', 'You are hereby constituted as an Ad-Hoc Committee, with Mr. Derrick Nicdao as Chairman, to study the food service requirements in the College. Specifically, the task involve the following:\na.) Determine whether there is a need for a college canteen/eatery within Melchor Hall to serve the constituencies of the Colleges of Engineering and Architecture, considering the proximity of other such services in the immediate neighborhood;\nb.) If the need is established, a possible and relatively good location is the area being currently used by the UFS plus the area to be vacated by the Property Office. Consider and study various options (UFS, CASAA-style, private concessions, etc.). Recommend the best option considering factors such as preference of the constituency, scope and quality of service, possible revenue to the College for the use of the \"premium\" space, which, otherwise could be used as classrooms or offices, etc.;\nc.) Prepare and submit report on or before December 3, 1987. It should include recommendations. ', 'Nicdao, Derrick\nReyes, J.G.T.\nBalangue, Pacifico G.\nAbueg, Adolfo\nPiedad, Floyd', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(367, 'E2-0367AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1987, December 14) Handbook of Industrial Engineering by Gavriel Salvendy, editor. ', 'This acknowledges with gratitude receipt of Handbook of Industrial Engineering by Gavriel Salvendy, editor. Our college librarian has informed us that our industrial engineering faculty members have recommended this particular title and we have been looking for this book to be purchased. We did find the title in one of the leading bookstores and another copy from you is indeed a welcome addition. ', 'Garcia, Ruben A. \nTanchoco, Jose M.A. \nDe la Peña, Fortunato\nGranda, Yolanda C.\nDe Castro, Jose Ma. \nTabujara, Ernesto G.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(368, 'E2-0368AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1988, April 29) Memorandum No. 20 Textbook Committee of the College of Engineering ', 'Per your Memorandum No. 20, submitting to your office the following list of members of the Textbook Committee of the College of Engineering ', 'De Castro, Prof. Jose Ma. \nGranda, Yolanda C. \nDe Leon, Rizalinda L. \nViray, Dr. Francisco L. \nVencio, Ma. Luz S.\nRamos, Alice C. \nAtanacio, Edgardo G.\nSantos, Arturo B.\nCalata, Jesus\nThe Chairman, Engineering Student Council ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(369, 'E2-0369AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1988, June 9) College Building Facilities Committee \n\"As per Office Order, a College Building Facil', 'One of the functions of the Committee is the supervision of the custodial services. With regard to this, the following guidelines will be adopted by the committee :\n1. Offices must be cleaned (i.e. sweeping and collection of garbage) at least every other day, say MWF. \n2. Office flooring should be waxed at least monthly.\n3. Comfort rooms should be cleaned daily.\n4. Repairs of lighting fixtures and other related tasks, upon request.\n5. Assist in moving furniture and equipment and other related tasks, upon request.\n6. Other services in related to the maintenance of the building and its facilities, upon request. ', 'Beaquin, Redem', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(370, 'E2-0370AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1988, June 15) College of Engineering Representative to the University Council Curriculum Committee', 'In view of the resignation of Dr. Edgardo S. Pacheco as the College\'s representative to the University Council Curriculum Committee (letter or resignation is attached). I have the honor to recommend Professor Marino M. Mena as the College\'s representative to the said committee effective June 16, 1988. ', 'Tabujara, Dr. Ernesto G. \nGarcia, Ruben A. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
