(475, 'E2-0475AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1983, February 24) Program, Technology - Industry LINK UP, Hyatt Regency Hotel, Roxas Blvd., Metro ', 'Objectives\n1. To identify priority areas for technology development in the Philippines\n2. To identify aspects of R&D work necessary for its promotion and development\n3. To identify problems and issues affecting indigenous R&D and its flow to industry\n4. To identify government agencies and institutions concerned with internal technology transfer and their roles\n5. To recommend strategies to effect promotion of R&D and its transfer to industry for a more effective LINK UP.', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(476, 'E2-0476AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, January 14) Memorandum for Prof. Manuel P. Bandaña', '1. Permission for Mr. Nathaniel C. Lim are cross register as a research student in the University of Tokyo until June 1982; \n2. He shall report the progress of his work at least once every two months to his thesis adviser, Dr. Luis M. Alarilla, Jr., and he shall carry out whatever instructions Dr. Alarilla may give him regarding the research; and\n3. Upon completion of the research, Mr. Lim shall defend his thesis before a thesis committee to be formed in accordance with the rules of the Graduate School of our University. ', 'Alvarez, Armando D.\nBandaña, Manuel P. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(477, 'E2-0477AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, December 1) Circular 81-12-11, Superseding Bed Circular No. 10, Series of 1977\nTo : Agencies ', 'The attached materials describe relevant operational policies and criteria set by the Bureau for the consideration and awarding of grants-in-aid to prospective implementors of nonconventional energy projects. It is hoped that these shall encourage well-organized, cost-effective project proposals, the potential outputs of which satisfy important needs within the national program.  ', 'Velasco, Geronimo Z.\nDe la Paz, Wenceslao R.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(478, 'E2-0478AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, November 11) Memorandum for Prof. Irene R. Cortes', 'Extension of graduate studies in Nuclear Engineering, College of Engineering, of Mrs. Marilou Claire J. Noriel up to April 30, 1983, provided she enrolls in ES-204 : Numerical Methods in Engineering during the Second Semester, 1982-1983. ', 'Alvarez, Armando D.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(479, 'E2-0479AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1983, August 8) Memorandum for Prof. Alfredo L. Juinio', 'Alternative proposals regarding the funding requirements for the acquisition of ten (10) additional microcomputers : \nI. Utilize part of the allocation for research (P200,000) and for Special projects (P100,000) from the total assistance budget. This will require an official request from the College Executive Committee and the Dean of the College of Engineering for the realignment of the approved budget breakdown. \nII. Purchase of only two (2) microcomputers for this school-year chargeable against the P100,000 fund for special projects and include the reminder in the budget proposal for UPERDFI\'s 1984-1985 assistance. ', 'Gregorio, Martin V. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(480, 'E2-0480AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1984, January 17) Memorandum for The Deans, UP Diliman\nSubject : Recommendations on the Revision of', 'Attached are recommendations on the revision of the General Education Program from several sources:\n1. Committee on a System-wide General Education\n2. College of Arts and Sciences, U.P. Diliman\n2.1. Division of Natural Sciences\n3. U.P. Los Baños General Education Program\n4. U.P. Visayas General Education Program ', 'Cortes, Irene R. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(481, 'E2-0481AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, February 4) Memorandum for Dean Marino M. Mena ', 'For the participation on official time of the following faculty member in the 5th Inter-Congress of the Pacific Science Association on February 3-7, 1985 at the Manila Hotel with registration fee of P100.00 per participant chargeable against the College budget:\n1. Dr. Ruben A. Garcia\n2. Dr. Perfecto K. Guerrero\n3. Dr. Meliton U. Ordillas, Jr. ', 'Frago, Pio P.\nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(482, 'E2-0482AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, February 20) Memorandum for Dean Marino M. Mena', 'Permission to participate on official time in the 46th Annual Convention of the Philippine Institute of Chemical Engineers on February 15-16, 1985 with registration fee of P600 per participant for the following faculty members:\nDr. Wilfredo I. Jose\nDr. Rogelio A. Panlasigui', 'Frago, Pio P.\nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(483, 'E2-0483AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, June 14) Memorandum for : Faculty Members\nSubject : Engineering College Convocation', 'There will be an Engineering College Convocation at 10:30 AM today, June 14, at the Engineering Theater. This is sponsored by the Engineering Student Council to welcome the newly admitted third year engineering students.', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(484, 'E2-0484AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, July 20) Memorandum to : Dr. Luis M. Alarilla, Jr. ', 'I read the two evaluation reports that you furnished me with great interest. There is really need for a continuing process of review of our various programs and this requires the institutionalization of mechanisms for the critical evaluation of our curricula. The step that the EE Curriculum Development Committee had taken is one of these mechanisms. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(485, 'E2-0485AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, September 24) Memorandum for : Mr. Danilo C. Mangaoang (College Student-Relations Officer)\nPr', 'Please constitute yourselves into a College Investigation Committee with Mr. Mangaoang as chairman, to investigate the attached complaint of Dr. Edgardo S. Pacheco against Mr. Mario Carlos, a student in ES 13. \nThe constitution of this Committee is in pursuance to Section 6 of the Rules and Regulations on Student Conduct and Discipline which is quoted below : \n\"Section 6. College Investigation. - Investigation of cases falling under the jurisdiction of a college shall be conducted by a committee of three (3) members appointed by the dean, one of whom shall be a student of the college.\"\nAttached herewith is the written complaint of Dr. Pacheco together with the written reply of Mr. Mario Carlos. The investigation shall be conducted in accordance with the Rules and Regulations on Student Conduct and Discipline, a copy of which is available at the Office of the College Secretary. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(486, 'E2-0486AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, January 10) Memorandum for : Mr. Lorenzo R. Mateo ', 'In compliance with Memorandum No. 2 from the Office of the President requiring an \"Annual Inventory of Equipment of the University of the Philippines,\" please constitute yourselves into a Committee, with Mr. Mateo as Chairman, to undertake the physical inventory of equipment in the College of Engineering as required by existing rules and regulations, and submit a report to the Office of the Auditor through this Office not later than 25 January 1980. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(487, 'E2-0487AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, January 10) Memorandum for : Mr. Rufino L. Vallente, Chairman\nMr. Lorenzo R. Mateo, member\nMr', 'Please constitute yourselves into a Committee on Physical Facilities Improvement with Mr. Vallente as Chairman. The functions of the Committee  will be : \n1. To identify areas in the College of Engineering where physical improvement is needed;\n2. To submit recommendations on priority improvement areas together with the financial requirements. Should there be a need for the services of other offices to accomplish this objective, the Committee can make the necessary recommendation for the Indorsement of the Dean. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(488, 'E2-0488AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, June 5) Memorandum for : The Faculty, College of Engineering\nSubject : UPAE 1980 Homecoming ', 'This is to inform you that the UPAE 1980 Homecoming will be held on Saturday, July 5, 1980, at the Quezon City Sports Club at 1800 hours. This year\'s host will be graduates of 1920, 1925, 1930, 1935, 1940, 1945, 1950, 1955, 1960, 1965, 1970 and 1975. Of course, we are expecting graduates of other years to come. \nBecause of the increasing number of attendance, the UPAE Homecoming for the past few years were held outside of the campus. But the presence of the faculty during these celebrations make the occasion indeed a homecoming and not simply a reunion. Thus, the occasion would not be complete without you and your participation', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(489, 'E2-0489AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, July 24) Memorandum for : Department Chairmen\nDr. R. Panlasigui\nDr. E. Tabujara\nDr. L. Alaril', 'The U.P. Engineering Research and Development Foundation, Inc. had approved the allocation of P30,000 for our curriculum revision and development. This amount will be used to support college/departmental activities as part of our continuing program of curriculum revision and development. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(490, 'E2-0490AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, August 1) Memorandum for : Faculty Members\nSubject : Remarks in forms for grades and leaves o', 'This is to remind members of the faculty to be careful in placing remarks in official forms such as those for grades and leaves of absence. There instances where the remarks are not consistent wih the action taken. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(491, 'E2-0491AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, December 4) Memorandum for : Cristy Hernandez, GE Department\nRodolfo Casiple, ME Department\nM', 'The College Executive Committee at its meeting held on December 3, 1980 approved to form a committee with you as a member. The task of the committee is to draft a set of operational guidelines that could be uniformly adopted by the various departments with laboratory facilities in the College of Engineering. The purpose of such guidelines is how twe can effectively utilize the College laboratory facilities in support of our functions, namely : teaching, research and extension services and at the same time make such facilities available to the National Engineering Center through the various centers under its umbrella. It is noted that the College of Engineering and the National Engineering Center have a mutual commitment to help each other. It is felt that it is necessary to adopt sufficient guidelines that will allow an effective utilization of the College laboratory facilities to the best interest of both entities. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(492, 'E2-0492AC', '', '', '', '', '', 'Justification\nProgram Components\nProject I. Inclusion of Energy Issues in University Academic Programs\nProject II. An Energy and Resources Conservation Program for the University of the Philippines\nProject III. Coordination of Energy Research Efforts\nThe Role of the U.P. College of Engineering\nProject IV. Creation of a Multidisciplinary Project for Energy Policy Studies', '', '(1980, December 4) Proposed Integrated Program on Energy and Resources by U.P. College of Engineerin', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(493, 'E2-0493AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, January 30) Memorandum for : Dr. Jose Azarcon,\nDr. Juan Bala, Jr. \nDr. Ibarra Cruz\nProf. Teod', 'As approved by the College Executive Committee as its meeting last December 3, 1980, please constitute yourselves into a committee for the purpose of : \n- identifying how the College of Engineering and the National Engineering Center can further contribute to the solution of the country\'s energy problem\n- assessing our capability in fulfilling such a role\n- studying the need for the instruction of a Masters Program in Energy Technology as well as non formal continuing educaiton programs and defining the courses and laboratory facilities required. Specifically, the following requirements : list of courses that have to be institution, list of equipment based on research and development work that have to be undertaken, space requirement for an Energy Research Laboratory should there be a need for one. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nProposed Institution of a Masters Program in Energy Technology ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(494, 'E2-0494AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, September 1) Memorandum for : Dr. Jose Azarcon, Jr.\nDr. Ruben A. Garcia\nProf. Herminio Abcede', 'Please be informed that you are hereby constituted into a College Committee on Physical Plant with Dr. Jose Azarcon, Jr. as Chairman. It will henceforth be one of the Standing Committees of the College. \nThe functions of the Committee are : \n1. To recommend ways and means of improving the physical facilities of the College such as those related to power, water, communications and parking;\n2. To develop an energy and water conservation program for the College;\n3. To coordinate the improvement of such facilities;\n4. To promote and monitor the efficient and effective utilization of these facilities.', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(495, 'E2-0495AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, September 15) Memorandum for : Dr. Eddie Pacheco\nProf. Joe de Castro\nProf. M. Castro', 'The UPERDFI Board, during its last meeting on August 25, 1981, had asked me to propose a reward mechanism that will encourage our professorial chairholders to do research or other creative work - say, a mechanism that is output oriented. \nAttached are some thoughts. I tried to assess some of the factors which I think will contribute to a favorable environment for research besides an effective reward mechanism.\nYour comments as well as suggestions on how best we can achieve the objectives of the professorial chair award will be highly appreciated. What other forms of support should UPERDFI provide? UPERDFI is now willing to extend additional support. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(496, 'E2-0496AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, November 3) To : All Division Heads\nERDC Staff\nNCRD Staff\nCode : Dr. Schipper\'s Lecture on En', 'Dr. Lee Schipper, one of the foremost energy specialists in the United States and Europe will be in Manila under the auspices of the United States International Communication Agency. He will give a series of lectures on different energy topics. \nHe is scheduled to visit ERDC on November 11, 1981. We have been lucky enough to invite him to give ERDD staff a lecture in one of his areas of expertise. The topic is \"Energy and the Built Environment : Residential and Industrial Energy Assessments, Use, Modelling and Potential for New and Renewable Sources of Energy.\" We are certain, Dr. Schipper\'s lecture will enrich our understanding and know-how of various technologies. ', 'Cruz, Dr. I.E. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(497, 'E2-0497AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, May 3) Memorandum for : Graduates, Academic Year 1981-1982, College of Engineering ', 'You are hereby informed that the College of Engineering will hold its Recognition and Closing Exercises on Sunday, May 9, 1982, at 3:00 PM in front of Melchor Hall. Since the ceremonies will start at 3 PM., the members of the graduating class as well as the faculty members in academic costume should assemble not later than 2:30 PM ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(498, 'E2-0498AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, May 21) Memorandum for : Dr. Ruben A. Garcia\nDr. Juan L. Bala, Jr.\nDr. Edgardo S. Pacheco\nDr.', 'In view of the trip abroad of Dr. Jose Azarcon, Jr., the Energy Graduate Committee is hereby reconstituted effective May 21, 1982 to be composed of the above-named members with Dr. Ruben A. Garcia as Chairman.', 'Mena,  Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49');
