(499, 'E2-0499AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, July 1) Memorandum for : Prof. Cristy R. Hernandez\nProf. Miguel B. Escoto\nProf. Jose Ma. de C', 'Each unit is being asked to submit to the U.P. Diamond Jubilee Committee a year-long program of activities on or before July 18, 1982. Please attend a meeting that the undersigned is calling for this purpose on Tuesday, July 6, 1982, at 2:30 PM at the Office of the Dean. ', 'Mena,  Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(500, 'E2-0500AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1983, September 9) Memorandum for : Mr. Reynaldo B. Vea\nDr. Salvador F. Reyes\nDr. Manuel V. Hernand', 'You are hereby constituted into a committee to study the possible institution of a Masters Degree Program in Naval Architecture and Marine Engineering at U.P. Mr. Vea is also hereby designated as Chairman of the Committee. Specifically, the study should include the following : \n1. the need for such a program in relation to national plans for development;\n2. its requirements in terms of staff, laboratory, and library facilities\n3. curriculum development\n4. its financial implications and potential sources of funds\n5. other aspects which the Committee considers as relevant. ', 'Mena,  Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(501, 'E2-0501AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1983, September 28) Memorandum for : Dr. Perfecto K. Guerrero\nDr. Edgardo S. Pacheco\nDr. Manuel V. ', 'Dr. Perfecto K. Guerrero is hereby designated as Acting Chairman of the Committee on Research until the return of Dr. Francisco Viray and Prof. Armando dela Cruz who are presently participating in a special course on Energy Planning and Management in Turin, Italy. They are expected to return by the end of November, 1983. ', 'Mena,  Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(502, 'E2-0502AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1984, February 22) Memorandum for : Dr. Efren F. Abaya, EE\nMs. Aura V. Castillo, IE\nProf. Armando d', 'During a meeting of the faculty held on 9 February 1984, it was agreed that a College Committee be created to review the General Education Program in relation to our engineering education curricula. You are hereby constituted into a Committee with Prof. Armando dela Cruz as Chairman. \nAttached herewith is the communication that the undersigned sent to the University Registrar for your guidance and consideration. Please feel free to discuss these issues or even modify the view expressed in the attached communication as seen fit by the Committee. Also feel free to invite resources persons from the engineering faculty and students as well as from other units of the University. ', 'Mena,  Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(503, 'E2-0503AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'School Science Development Project\nCollege of Engineering\nUniversity of the Philippines \nProject No.', 'The main purpose of this Amendment is to extend the project by two years until December 1980 for the reasons indicated and the purposes specified in this document. \nThe effect of this Amendment is to increase the UNDP contribution by US$195,458 to US$458,567 and the Philippines contribution by P1,800.970 to P3,022,000', 'United Nations Development Programme', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(504, 'E2-0504AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, January 9) Office of Cultural Affairs and Information\n\n', 'In its Note No. 25 dated 4 January 1979, the Mexican Embassy has informed the Ministry that the Mexican Government, in its desire to fully implement the Cultural Agreement between the United Mexican States and the Republic of the Philippines, would like to propose a first Working Meeting to be held in Manila from the 18th to the 20th of April 1979, in order to exchange ideas for the abovementioned purpose. \nThe Ministry would appreciate receiving the names of your representative so we could inform the Philippine panel for this negotiation and maybe meet before actual negotiations. ', 'Arranz, Consuelo\nCorpuz, Dr. Onofre D. \nCultural agreement between the Republic of the Philippines and the United Mexican States ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(505, 'E2-0505AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, March 16) Memorandum Circular No. 1 to : Deans and Directors, Heads of Offices and Organizati', 'The 1979 Faculty Conference shall be held at the U.P. at Los Baños on 3-4 May on the theme, \"The University Structure in the Future.\" Its objectives are : \n1. To generate guidelines for the organization of the University toward 2000 A.D.\n2. To describe the alternative structural organization for the University in the future. ', 'Corpuz, Dr. Onofre D. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(506, 'E2-0506AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, May 19) Appointment as Consultant of the Building Research and Developmetn Staff (BRDS)', 'In view of the approval by the Acting Minister Aber P. Canlas of our request for professional and technical assistance in the field of Environmental Engineering, you are hereby appointed as Consultant of the Building Research and Development Staff (BRDS) of this Ministry effective May 1, 1979. \nAs such, you are entitled to an honorarium of Two Hundred Pesos (P200.00) per session with the BRDS but not to exceed P800.00 per month. ', 'Mallonga, Rosalio A. \nMena, Mariano M. \nMinistry of Public Works, Transportation and Communications ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(507, 'E2-0507AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, May 31) Appointment as Dean of College of Engineering', 'The approval of your appointment as Dean by the Board of Regents strikes a hopeful and confident note for the College of Engineering. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(508, 'E2-0508AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, June 6) Education 381 (Workshop in College Teaching) ', 'In reply to your letter dated June 4, 1979, please be informed that the College has scheduled Education 381 (Workshop in College Teaching) for the First Semester, AY 1979-80. The course will be taught jointly by Dr. Jovito B. Castillo, Chairman, Department of Professional Education and Dr. Edgardo Pacheco of the College of Engineering pursuant to the agreement arrived at in a meeting participated in by Dr. Aurora A. Miñoza, Director of Graduate Studies, Dr. Jovito B. Castillo, Dr. Edgardo Pacheco and the undersigned. ', 'Savellano, Julieta M. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(509, 'E2-0509AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, June 4) Education 381 (Workshop in College Teaching) ', 'I have the honor to request that Education 381; Workshop in College Teaching, be taught jointly by Dr. Jovito B. Castillo of your college and Dr. Edgardo S. Pacheco of the engineering faculty during the first semester of academic year 1979-1980. \nA preliminary plan for the joint offering of the course was mapped out during a meeting held yesterday and participated in by Dr. Julieta M. Savellano, Dr. Aurora A. Miñoza, Dr. Jovito B. Castillo and Dr. Edgardo S. Pacheco. The plan calls for Dr. Castillo to handle the lecture and Dr. Pacheco to take care of the laboratory part of the course. The course is intended for graduate students enrolled in our Engineering Education Program. ', 'Ramos, Paz G. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(510, 'E2-0510AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, June 18) Request for Dr. Ham an APO and UNIDO expert from the USA and Professor Hitomi, anoth', 'The Productivity & Development Center (PDC) of the Development Academy of the Philippines (DAP) in cooperation with the Asian Productivity Organization (APO) will have a Technical Expert Service (TES) on Group Technology from July 16 to 24, 1979. \nGroup Technology is a new approach to the manufacture of goods in batches and had been proven to be an essential mechanism in raising the level of productivity. Its significance in the mass production of goods is comparable to the introduction of line production. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nTolentino, Arturo L. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(511, 'E2-0511AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, June 25) Invitation to become a member of the Committee on Consulting Engineering ', 'The Philippine Insitute of Civil Engineering (PICE) invites you to be a member of the Committee on Consulting Engineering with Lamberto Un Ocampo of DCCD Engineering Corporation as our chairman. \nChairman Bert Ocampo has recommended to PICE the streamlining of grade classification of Civil Engineers as a Committee Project. \nThe Project consists of two (2) parts as follows : \nProject : CE\'s Professional Grade Classifications\nPart I : Grade Classification of Civil Engineers\nPart II : Salary Schedules of Civil Engineers ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nRoque, Rolando G. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(512, ' E2-0512AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, October 10) Invitation to send whatever information to be published in the Graduate School ne', 'The Graduate School of the University of the Philippines is launching a monthly newsletter which we hope to release within the first week of each month starting this October. \nThis project is expected to close the communication gap between the Graduate School and the thirty-two (32) units of the University System offering graduate programs, as well as to provide a forum for graduate faculty and graduate student dialogue. \nThe Graduate School Newsletter will be produced by the Graduate School staff, initially with Mr. Francisco E. Dumlao, as Editor; Dr. Emerenciana Y. Arcellana, as Adviser; and Dr. Joventino D. Soriano and Dr. Leopoldo Y. Yabes, as Consultants. \nIn this regard, we wish to invite your College/Unit to send to us whatever information you would want to be published. This invitation is also extended to your graduate faculty and graduate student association(s). Manuscripts preferably inEnglish should be submitted as soon as possible, and if possible not later than the last week of every month for publication in the succeeding month. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nDumlao, Francisco E.\nArcellana, Emerenciana Y. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(513, 'E2-0513AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, October 25) Excerpt from the minutes of the 920th meeting of the Board of Regents ', 'Financial matters previously discussed by the Finance Committee at its meeting on October 18, 1979, and submitted for consideration by the Board, the action of the Board being indicated at the end of each item :\nU.P. Proper\nCollege of Engineering\nIncrease in the living allowance of the graduate fellows of the College from P400 to P700 per month, effective second semester, AY 1979-80, subject to the following conditions:\n1) the graduate fellow shall render fifty (50 hours service per month during the period of his/her fellowship (assisting in the research and teaching activities of the College of Engineering); and \n2) The number of fellowship slots shall be reduced so that total graduate fellowship expenses, including the proposed increase, shall be within the available appropriation therefor. ', 'Abad, Gemino H.\nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(514, 'E2-0514AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, October 3) 2nd Indorsement ', 'Respectfully returned to the Vice President for Academic Affairs with the following information.\nDuring the first semester of schoolyear 1979-80 Dr. Edgardo S. Pacheco of our college opened an experimental class in ES 11 (Statics of Rigid Bodies) using the Personalized System of Instruction (PSI). This system of instruction is described in the announcement which is herewith attached. \nThe services of tutors are essential in the Personalized System of Instruction. Graduate fellows who are assigned to assist in teaching will serve as tutors in PSI classes. \nDr. Pacheco reported very encouraging results of the PSI experiment he is currently conducting. He will again teach ES 11 next semester using PSI. He also plans to write the study guides and other materials for ES 13 (Mechanics of Deformable Bodies I) so it can be offered using PSI during the first semester of school year 1980-1981. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(515, 'E2-0515AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, September 24) Increase of graduate fellows allowance from P400 to P700 per month ', 'I have the honor to recommend that the living allowance of graduate fellows in the College of Engineering be increased from P400.00 to P700.00 per month effective November, 1979. To be entitled to this increase, the graduate fellow must render fifty hours of service per month, assisting in the research and teaching activities of the College of Engineering. This service shall be rendered during the period of the fellowship. \nPresently, our graduate fellows are not required to render any service to the college. However, the living allowance of P400.00 per month is so small that, for a number of years now. there are fewer applicants than there are available slots. By increasing this allowance to P700.00 per month and at the same time requiring the rendering of service, we feel that the fellowship will become more attractive to graduate students and more beneficial to our college.', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(516, 'E2-0516AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, January 9) Encyclopedias recently published by MacMillan Publishing Company ', 'We would like to bring to your attention two encyclopedias recently published by Macmillan Publishing Company, New York, which should be in every engineering library : \n1. Encyclopedia of Statistics. Edited by Wm. H. Kruskal and Judith M. Tanur. 2 volumes, 1978. This is the most extensive reference work on statistics in print, covering the development of modern statistical methods and describing the operations, interpretations, and applications of the various statistical techniques. \n2. The Great Soviet Encyclopedia. 31 volumes, plus indexes. Vol. 1 to 22 already published; other volumes to be published within the next two years. The Russian edition, now being published in serial form, is the prime source of information in more than 600,000 libraries in the U.S.S.R and the Macmillan translation is the prime source in English on the Soviet Union. Of the more than 100,000 articles, 10,000 are on technology; 1,900 on mathematics; 3,500 on Chemistry; and 4,200 on Fine Arts and Architecture. ', 'Makabenta, Eduardo\nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(517, 'E2-0517AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, February 8) Engineering Week celebration', 'The college is all set to spark up the annual Engineering Week celebration. Highlighting the festivity is the Engineering March on Monday, February 11, at 9:00 AM to be participated in by the engineering community together with students from other colleges. If news hasn\'t reached you, these colleges worked for their own college week and made them coincide with ours so that February 11-15 virtually becomes a University Week. \nEnclosed is the program of activities for our week-long celebration, carefully planned to suit the interest and the needs of the engineering populace : the students, faculty, administration and non-academic personnel. With this year\'s theme -- PAGKAMULAT, PAGKAKAISA at PAGKILOS ng INHINYERA PARA SA SAMBAYANAN, we hope to come up with a successful and more meaningful affair. ', 'Medina, Ma. Rhodora T. \nMena, Dean Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(518, 'E2-0518AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, March 5) ', 'It is with pleasure that I grant permission for Dr. Salvador F. Reyes and Prof. Jose Ma. de Castro, both faculty members of the U.P. College of Engineering, to participate as member-consultants in your Ministry\'s Board of Engineering Review. We have their commitment to contribute actively to the discharge of the Board\'s functions and duties. \nRegarding your proposal to employ other civil engineering professors of the U.P. College of Engineering as consultants during the summer, this would have to be done on a case-to-case basis. I have been informed, however, about the willingness and enthusiasm of the Engineering faculty so long as no conflict with their teaching and other duties is entailed. ', 'Soriano, Emanuel V. \nMena, Marino M. \nPaterno, Vicente T. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(519, 'E2-0519AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, April 21) Quarterly Report # 6\nEngineering Education Project ', 'In line with our policy of keeping you abreast with the various Project activities, this quarterly report covering the months from January to March 1980 is hereby submitted for your information and perusal. ', 'Reyes, Ma. Lourdes T.\nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(520, 'E2-0520AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, April 28) Update on the International Conference on Energy and Environment ', 'The enclosed memorandum is an update on the International Conference on Energy and Environment that we are organizing on January 5-9, 1981 in Manila, Philippines. \nThere are several matters that require your immediate attention. Specifically, we urgently need your support and help in organizing some of the technical sessions for the Conference as discussed in Item 2 of the memorandum. We also need financial support for the travel expenses of some of the invited distinguished speakers. There is a possibility that we might be able to get some travel support from the National Science Foundation for some U.S. participants. However, for this we need to have the technical program complete with a list of probable speakers, their affiliations and the titles of their papers. Please have your ideas transmitted to me before June 15, 1980 so that I may prepare and submit a proposal to NSF by July 1, 1980. ', 'Koh, Severino L. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(521, 'E2-0521AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, June 16) Letter of apology ', 'I wish to apologize for whatever wrong I have committed in connection with my cross-registration form for one subject : Economics 102. My only explanation is that I was under tremendous pressure and was desperate to register at the earliest possible time. I assure that this has never happened before and will never happen again. ', 'Reyes, Angela Haya H. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(522, 'E2-0522AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, June 23) Training course offered by The Foundation for International Training for Third World', 'The Foundation for International Training is interested in offering a training course in consulting engineering to professional engineers in your country. We have begun to compile information for both a training manual and a background report on the engineering profession there. However, we would appreciate your co-operation in either answering the following questions about local aspects of the engineering profession, or directing us to any individual or organization capable of doing so. \nI. Organizations\nII. Engineering Education\nIII. Patterns of Consulting Work\nIV. Legislation and Policies ', 'Strudwick, Karen A.D. \nFoundation for International Training for Third World Countries ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(523, 'E2-0523AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, July 18) First Conference on Appropriate Technology in the Philippines', 'We are pleased to invite you and/or your representative to the \"First Conference on Appropriate Technology in the Philippines\" to be held on August 6 to 9 at the U.P. Institute for Small-Scale Industries (UP-ISSI) building at the U.P. Campus, Diliman, Quezon City. \nHosted by the Philippine Center for Appropriate Technology and Training (PCATT) and the University of the Philippines Institute for Small-Scale Industries (UP-ISSI), the conference is designed for advocates and/or practitioners of appropriate technology concepts. The four-day meet will focus on traditional and modern appro-tech systems as applied to such areas as manufacturing, food/agriculture and nonconventional energy sources. Photo exhibits and technology demonstrations have likewise been lined up to cap the event. ', 'Taylor, Eduardo M.\nGertes, Benjamin G. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(524, 'E2-0524AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, August 4) Invitation to become a technical speaker on the Fifth National Convention, Institut', 'The Institute of Integrated Electrical Engineers of the Philippines, the government-accredited association representing the more than 15,000 electrical practitioners in the country, will be holding its Fifth National Convention on December 4 to 7, 1980 at the Fiesta Pavilion of the historic Manila Hotel. Discussions will center on the theme \"Electrical Engineering and National Economic Priorities\".\nIn this connection, we have chosen you to be our Technical Speaker on, \"Engineering Education : Current Trends and Perspectives\". ', 'Bala, Juan L. Jr. \nEsguerra, Pastor B. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(525, 'E2-0525AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Subject : Invitation to become  a honored sponsor/ distinguished patron / a benevolent donor / a sym', 'The Office of Student Affairs of the University of the Philippines has started to pave a way to channel the boundless energies of fraternity members into positive and creative endeavors and away from destructive misadventures which end up with fratmen, or even innocent by-standers, maimed or killed. \nLast year, we initiated, with the enthusiastic cooperation of the fraternity leaders themselves, an inter-fraternity conference whereby the blueprint of a forum for all fraternity leaders to work out mutual problems and plan projects of common interest was successfully set up. \nThis year\'s crop of fraternity leaders wish to continue the worthwhile effort and seek to actualize the establishment of a really effective inter-fraternity council. \nWe are aware of your own deep concern for the physical safeties of our fraternity men and your desire to see bright, but otherwise restless, young men pursue meritorious activities that will re-inforce their formal education in the University. It is, for this reason, that we are inviting you to join hands with us in making a SECOND INTER-FRATERNITY CONFERENCE a reality. \nThe Conference was scheduled by the fraternity leaders to be held on September 12-14, 1980. We expect to have 90 fraternity members attending it, for which we estimate to spend P20,000.00.', 'Evangelista, Oscar L. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(526, 'E2-0526AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, September 19) Informing the arrival at the Philippines ', 'Plans for my proposed visit to the Philippines are begining to take shape and I am very much looking forward to meeting you. \nI thought I would give you some indication of my plans as I now see them. According to my present itinerary, I will arrive in Manila on the Philippine Airlines at 6:20 a.m., October 31, 1980. I will confirm this by cable later since airline schedules are prone to change. ', 'Plants, Helen L. \nMena, Marino M. \nDevarajan, B. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(527, 'E2-0527AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, October 22) Invitation to lecture : advance course in Wastewater Treatment Process Design ', 'In order to accomodate the several requests from our previous participants in the basic water pollution seminar, we are planning to hold an advance course in wastewater treatment process design. The venue will be on November 27, 28, and 29, 1980 at the Silahis International Hotel, Roxas Blvd., Metro Manila. The schedule of lectures is attached herewith for your ready reference. \nWe are inviting you to lecture on the following : \nTopic : Variations of the Activated Sludge System ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nPadero, Eduardo G. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(528, 'E2-0528AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, October 27) Subject : Electronics and Communications Research Laboratory', 'As you may recall, we have used the fifth floor space formerly occupied by the UP Broadcasting Station as an AD HOC electronics and communication research laboratory. As you may also know, UPIRC is now in a position to improve the said space and its facilities. Prior to committing the IRC\'s jointly improve, operate and use the laboratory. And that the use of the same shall be under the nominal control of the Dean of Engineering and the Director of the IRC, or their respective authorized representatives. Rules governing laboratory shall be jointly established by the two offices. \nFurthermore, the UPIRC will assign personnel at its own expense to staff the laboratory and be responsible for equipment and materials kept therein. ', 'Azarcon, Jose A. Jr.\nMena, Marino M. \nAlarilla, Luis M., Jr. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(529, 'E2-0529AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, November 13) Official mission representing the Spanish training and educational materials ind', 'I have the pleasure of informing you that from December 4th to December 11th an official mission representing the Spanish training and educational materials industry will be in Manila. The members of the Mission will be :\n1. ALECOP - Mr. Laurentino Gomez\n2. DIDACTES - Mr. Pablo Sanz\n3. DISTESA - Mr. Gregorio Rico\n4. EDUCTRADE - Mr. Jose Villa\n5. ENOSA - Mr. Manuel Santar\n6. CHAMBER OF COMMERCE, MADRID - Mr. Ramon Amat \nThe target of the visit of the members of the Mission is to gather knowledge on the educational system of the Philippines, the needs and sources of supply of training and educational material, as well as on the possibilities of export and joint manufacture of this equipment, and to search for qualified representatives. ', 'Martinez, Juan ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(530, 'E2-0530AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1980, November 26) 5th National Convention, Institute of Integrated Electrical Engineers of the Phi', 'We wish to confirm your schedule for presentation of your paper entitled \"Engineering Education : Current Trends and Perspectives.\"\nYou are going to be the first speaker for Technical Session III slated on Friday, December 5, 1980 to start at 2:00 p.m.', 'Mena, Marino M. \nManansala, Mario U. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(531, 'E2-0531AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, January 6) Meeting to discuss and finalize the proposed amendments of EIS System for elevatio', 'The EIA Staff reviewed the rules and regulations implementing P.D. 1586 which establishes the EIS System and came up with proposed amendments to the said rules and regulations. \nIn this connection, we have scheduled a meeting with all the consultants on Friday, 09 January 1981, at 1:00 P.M. to discuss and finalize the proposed amendments for elevation to the Council. Attached herewith are copies of the proposed changes and the corresponding revised flow chart for your perusal and comments. ', 'Remigio, Amador A. Jr.\nMena, Marino M. \nNational Environmental Protection Council ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(532, 'E2-0532AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, January 6)  Seminar on contemporary policy issues and methods of policy analysis - The Univer', 'The University of the Philippines Management Education Council will hold a one-and-a half-day seminar on contemporary policy issues and methods of policy analysis on January 22-23, 1981 at the Green Room, U.P. Institute for Small Scale Industries, Diliman, Quezon City. This will be the first in a series of seminar-workshops on different topics in public policy and management that UPMEC will sponsor to promote improvements in policy analysis, research and knowledge in the University and other institutions concerned. \nThe January seminar will address substantive and methodological issues of policy in the areas of education and energy, which represent comparatively old and new policy sectors but are of common and enduring concern to different segments of society. The seminar will be attended by some 50 participants representing University units, institutions and government agencies engaged or interested in policy-oriented research, teaching or service activities. ', 'De Guzman, Raul P. \nMena, Marino M.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(533, 'E2-0533AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, January 21) Proposal to install a duplicating machine equipment (xerox machine) ', 'We are pleased to submit this proposal to install a duplicating machine equipment (xerox machine) in your Department to satisfy the reprinting needs of your intelligent students.', 'Mena, Marino M.\nSevilla, Teodoro\nEscobar, Lucila C. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(534, 'E2-0534AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, January 22-23) Seminar on policy issues and methods of policy analysis \nEducation, Energy and', 'This Seminar features brief presentation on susbtantive issues of education and energy policy and discussions of the methods and problems of policy research and analysis. It aims to identify specific areas for further inquiry and improved methods of policy study as means toward better-informed policy and management. \nThe main speakers are well known in their respective fields and together bring a multidisciplinary perspective to the topics. In addition, to provide a comparative context for the discussion, UPMEC has invited Professor Yehezkel Dror, Professor of Political Science and Public Administration at the Hebrew University in Israel, author of Public Policy-Making Re-examined (1968) and The Compleat Policy Analyst and Handbook for Rulers (forthcoming), and a practising policy adviser. \nU.P. faculty members and other individuals and institutions interested in policy studies are invited to this seminar. Follow-up or \"echo seminars and workshops are also intended in the same or other fields of public policy and management. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(535, 'E2-0535AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, February 4) Invitation to become a Professional Member of Council of Technology and Allied Sc', 'We take pleasure of inviting you to be a Professional Member to the Council of Technology and Allied Sciences  of the Philippines (COTASP), knowing you to be qualified in this membership category. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(536, 'E2-0536AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, February 27) Invitation to participate on the monthly Natural Resources Management forum ', 'The Natural Resources Management Center (NRMC), an attached agency of the Ministry of Natural Resources (MNR), is sponsoring a series of monthly Natural Resources Management Forums with the objective of pooling together multi-disciplinary experts from concerned government and private agencies including the academic institutions to give their views and opinions on critical international and local issues on resource management. Further, this is aimed at evolving strategies and policy guidelines for the rational utilization, conservation and management of the country\'s natural resources. \nFor the past sessions of this series of forums, various issues, problems and strategies related to the management of the country\'s land resources, forestry, fishery, mangrove, wildlife, watershed, coastal zone, marine parks, development of mineral resources, development of solar energy in the Philippines, remote sensing for national development, MIS in the natural resources sector, transnational corporations, including the ASEAN industrial complementation have all been discussed by distinguished natural resource management experts. \nOn March 19, 1981, the discussion will be on The Hydraulic Control Structure - A Threat to the Fishpen Industry in Laguna de Bay. It will be held at the U.P. Asian Institute of Tourism (AIT) House from 4:00 to 6:00 in the evening. We have invited Mr. Bent H. Nielsen, Consultant to the Southeast Asia Fisheries Development Center, to be the Speaker of this Forum. A number of experts from the academic, government and private sectors will be invited to react on and further discuss Mr. Nielsen\'s paper. ', 'Roque, Celso R. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(537, 'E2-0537AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, February 27) A program for Earthquake Disaster Mitigation in Southeast Asia ', 'At the ASEAN Disaster Preparedness Seminar held early last year in Manila, we presented to the Office of US Foreign Disaster Assistance, Agency for International Development, a program proposal entitled \"A Program for Earthquake Disaster Mitigation in Southeast Asia\", a copy of which is herewith enclosed. The initial response of the US Government was the commissioning of a preliminary mission to draw up a detailed program and budget. The Mission, composed of Dr. Ed P. Arnold and Dr. Ted Algermissen of the US Geological Sulvery, will be in Manila early this March. \nPart of the activities of the Mission is to have a dialogue with representatives of some government and private organizations in the Philippines that may have interest and may be able to participate in the proposed program. In this connection, the Mission has requested us to organize a forum in which the Mission could discuss with the issues involed in the proposed program, to get an insight into reactions to some of the items contained in the proposal and into the question of participation of interested organizations. ', 'Kintanar, Roman L. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(538, 'E2-0538AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, March 23) Proposed \"Earthquake Disaster Mitigation Program for Southeast Asia\"', 'This is in connection with our previous invitation to a meeting with the US AID Mission on a preliminary survey regarding the proposed \"Earthquake Disaster Mitigation Program for Southeast Asia\". The said meeting was deferred due to some unavoidable circumstances. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nKintanar, Roman L. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(539, 'E2-0539AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, March 26) Request for documents regarding application of science and technology from the inst', 'I am writing to you as we need to find out about technological applications in which your institutions has been involved. \nI am presently making an assessment of the application of science and technology in the Asian region over the last 12 years. This work is being done for UNESCO, to prepare documentation for the 1982 Conference on the Applications of Science and Technology in Asia (CASTASIA II) on progress in the Asian region since CASTASIA I. \nTherefore, I am writing to you to request any documents your organisation has produced on the application of science and technology from your institution. We particularly need to know what kinds of technological applications have been made, the effect they had, and problems that the organisation may have encountered in applying scientific results. In addition, reports we are particularly interested in are those which embody case studies of what actually happened when a particular technology was applied. Copies of your annual reports would also be very useful to this UNESCO project. ', 'Hill, Professor Stephen C. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(540, 'E2-0540AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, May 15) Library Books and References \nEngineering Education Project ', 'Please find enclosed copies of the current book catalogues and engineering references published by McMillan Southeast Asia Ptd. Ltd for your reference and information. \nShould they suffice your present library book needs, kindly place your order to the said publisher and inform us accordingly so that we can facilitate the payment of your order. ', 'Cruz, Fabian N.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(541, 'E2-0541AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, May 21) Assistance to the College of Engineering (U.P.) for the Establishment of the National', 'Enclosed, for your files, is one signed copy of the revision (\"I\") which I have approved on behalf of UNDP under the terms and conditions specified in the general letter-agreement signed by Minister Sicat on 10 July 1979. This revision merely reflects the actual 1980 expenditures as reported by UNESCO and the consequential effects in the succeeding years. \nThe total UNDP contribution is decreased by US$88,594 to US$1,583,301 while the Philippine Government contribution remains unchanged at P13,309,320. The decrease is solely due to the recosting by UNESCO of the fellowships presently ongoing and those that are still for implementations. ', 'Morvan, Alain Y. \nVillavicencio, B.G.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(542, 'E2-0542AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, June 1) Request for help and indication on a possible candidate for the position of President', 'I am writing in behalf of Minster Gerardo Sicat who is currently on official trip abroad. Before the Minister left yesterday, he left instructions for me to relay to you his request for your help and indication on a possible candidate for the position of President of the Asian Institute of Technology. \nMinister Sicat assures you that your suggestions will be treated in strict confidence. ', 'Liguton, Jennifer P.T.\nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(543, 'E2-0543AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, September 17) Memorandum to : All Government Cooperating Agencies associated with UNDP projec', 'In celebration of the 36th Anniversary of the United Nations Day, we are requesting your office to kindly invite the government cooperating agencies of your project to join our UN Day Party to be held on 17 October 1981. \nIn this connection, we are attaching copies of the memorandum announcing the party for your distribution. \nYour cooperation in this matter will be highly appreciated. ', 'Hassing, Edu H. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(544, 'E2-0544AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, September 30) ', 'In reply to your letter of September 8 I am enclosing a calander of the College of Graduate Studies and Research as well as a calendar of our Biomedical Engineering group. I am also enclosing applications forms for admission to the Graduate School. The possibility of obtaining financial support for graduate students depends strongly upon the field the applicant chooses. There are areas where relatively more money is available and of course fellowships can be easier granted. Other areas are less fortunate. The best approach would be for the individual to submit an application form outlining the field in which he/she would like to work. The form is then circulated among the members of the department who express their view with regard to vacancies, availability of funds, etc. I would like to repeat that the reply depends very much upon the academic standing of the applicant and the recommendations he received from your school or other institutions in his home country. \nI would like to emphasise that the information I gave you refers basically only to Engineering. This does not mean that positions outside the College of Engineering are not available, but that there are fewer and more difficult to obtain. I received since my return two applications, one from a biochemist and one from a microbiologist. I passed these on to the respective departments but there were no vacancies for the coming year. The applications were incomplete and I am advising the applicants to submit an application in a formal way on the necessary forms in the hope that some positions might become available later on in other departments. ', 'Pollak, V. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(545, 'E2-0545AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, October 1) Invitation to become one of the speakers on the relevance of the present engineeri', 'The Engineering Student Council and the Ad Hoc Committee on the Science and Technology Movement will be sponsoring a symposium on the relevance of the present engineering education to genuine national development. \nWe would like to invite you as one of the speakers of the said symposium. We would deeply appreciate it if you can share our views on The Present Thrust of Engineering Education. ', 'Parra, Josephine A. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(546, 'E2-0546AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, November 19) AEESEA Student Award Scheme', 'Thank you very much for your letter of 9 November 1981 which I am answering in the absence of Mr. Storr who is on an overseas mission until the end of next week. \nIt has taken this secretariat over a year to develop the AEESEA Student Award Scheme to its present stage mainly because there are long periods of time in communicating by mail with so many people. We are still waiting for replies from some Voting Members of AEESEA with their comments and nominations of persons for judges at country level. It is important that Voting Members are actively involved as they are to be responsible for administration of the Scheme within their own countries. \nOur next step is to make some revisions to the Scheme and send it to Unesco, Paris for approval. After this it is hoped that the Scheme can be put into effect. ', 'Ward, Neville \nMena, Marino M. \nAssociation for Engineering Education in Southeast Asia ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(547, 'E2-0547AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, November 20) Support a Research Professor in Engineering ', 'Attached herewith is a proposal for UPERDFI to support a \"Research Professor in Engineering.\"\nIt is a fact that research in the College is not really as great as desirable. Despite availability of funds for research, our faculty shy away from them because the activity takes them away from more financially rewarding activities. The faculty cannot really be faulted for this attitude because man is an economic being and must support his family\'s ambitions. \nIn an effort to rectify the situation, this proposal would require the recipient to render only 3 hours a week for teaching but would undertake no other activity except research. A remuneration of P6,000 a month is proposed so that there will be no need for him to seek side lines to satisfy his financial needs. \nThe Research Professorship would probably require a Board of Regents action. There will probably be many other problems. Nevertheless, the idea is being presented for whatever it is worth. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nOrdillas, Meliton U. Jr. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(548, 'E2-0548AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1981, November 27) Thesis approval', 'I am sending thru my officemate, Ms. Ilda Gorriceta, the first draft of my thesis entitled \"A Study of Copper and Zinc Content of Green Mussels Collected in Coastal Waters Near Industrial and Rural Areas\". It is not a thick paper but I hope it will meet your approval. \nI understand that the Board of Regents meeting for the first semester will be in January. If it is possible, I would very much like to defend the paper before the meeting so I can qualify as a graduate for the first semester. \nMs. Gorriceta will be going back to Iloilo on the 6fh of December and if it is not much of a bother for you, can you kindly send back my paper thru her with your approval and comments?', 'Mena, Marino M. \nDe Castro, Teresa R.  ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(549, 'E2-0549AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, January 11)  Solar Energy Lecture / Seminars with Dr. Lehner, University of Stuttgart, German', 'I read with interest your article \"Program for Solar Energy Utilization in the Philippines\" in the \'Philippine Geographical Journal\'\nI have the pleasure to inform you that Prof. Dr. Gunther Lehner of the University of Stuttgart, Germany will come to Manila from March 4 to March 11, 1982 to conduct a series of lecture/seminars on Solar Energy. Please find enclosed some details on Dr. Lehner and his topics. \nThe following lectures are in the planning stage :\n1. UTILIZATION OF SOLAR ENERGY IN GERMANY, venue the Goethe-Institut, including a Solar Energy Exhibition to be opened by Dr. Lehner;\n2. SELECTIVE LAYERING FOR SOLAR ABSORBERS, Partner : PAGASA, Dr. Roman Quintanal;\n3. POTENTIAL AND PROBLEMS IN THE UTILIZATION OF SOLAR ENERGY; Partner : Bureau of Non-Conventional Energy, Dr. Ibarra Cruz;\n4. SOLAR CELL SYSTEMS, Partner : Physics Society of the Phils. venue University of the Philippines;\n5. CURRENT AND FUTURE PROSPECTS FOR THE COMMERCIAL AND INDUSTRIAL UTILIZATION OF SOLAR ENERGY, Partner : Asian Institute of Management, Dr. Mendoza. \nI have been informed that the U.P. College of Engineering is also deeply involved in Solar Energy Research. Please be so kind as to let me know at your earliest convenience whether your college is interested in coordinating one of the above mentioned lecture / seminars, or if you prefer to arrange a separate program with Dr. Lehner. There is no cost involved. Please be so kind as to give me a ring. ', 'Bretzler, Dr. Gerrit\nAbis, Dr. Leopoldo V. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(550, 'E2-0550AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, January 13) Recommendations of the Committee to Review Academic Progams in the U.P. System ', 'This is in connection with the 4 January 1982 Memorandum from this Office regarding the recommendations of the Committee to Review Academic Programs in the U.P. System. \nWe are transmitting herewith, for your comments, additional excerpts of the Committee report bearing on your unit. ', 'Mena, Dean Marino M. \nAlfonso, Oscar M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(551, 'E2-0551AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, January 18) Invitation for a talk regarding engineering ethics', 'As graduating students of Chemical Engineering we would like to acquire as much knowledge as we can about the profession we will be practicing soon.\nThus, we would appreciate your sharing with us your insights in engineering ethics, by a talk to our class of graduating students.\nWe are particularly interest in the following points.\n1. Government rules and regulations for chemical engineering profession;\n2. Engineering ethics in general\n3. Application of ethics to practical situations\nModels and visual aids are most welcome. A thirty-minute open forum may follow the hour-long talk. ', 'CH.E. 70 CLASS\nMuñoz, Jose C. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49');
