(552, 'E2-0552AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, January 23) Copy of the Project\'s Executive Summary Report (The feasibility of economically p', 'I am happy to announce that the study on Silvicultural Biomass and its Utilization for Energy Production jointly commissioned by the governments of the Republic of Finland and the Republic of the Philippines has been completed. The feasibility of economically producing commercial energy from biomass resources has been proved appropriate particularly in the intensification of commercial energy use brought about by higher growth levels in our country. \nIn behalf of our Chairman, I am transmitting to you herewith a copy of the project\'s Executive Summary Report which I feel would be of some importance to you in view of your involvement in major phases of national development as well as your position of knowledge in relevant fields. \nYour comments and/or suggestions would be greatly valued. Thank you. ', 'Tantoco, Bienvenido R. Jr. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(553, 'E2-0553AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, January 29) Raffle with the UP Engineering Library as the main beneficiary. The majority of t', 'The U.P. Geodetic Engineering Club is an academic organization based at the College of Engineering. Its main objective is to provide a common ground for G.E. students in their academic endeavours. Besides this, the organization also seeks to instill social awareness among its members and be of service to the whole studentry and community.\nIn pursuance of our objectives, we are planning to hold a raffle sometime between January and February, 1982, with the U.P. Engineering Library as the main beneficiary. The majority of the proceeds will go to the library for the much needed books and improvements in its facilities.\nIn this connection, we would like to seek your assistance in providing us with some of the prizes. A donation in cash or in kind will be most appreciated. Your donation will go a long way in maintaining and improving the quality of learning of the country\'s future engineers through an improved library. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nBarnabe, Jose Marie\nTolentino, Mario\nHernandez, Cristy R. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(554, 'E2-0554AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, February 16) confirmation on Dr. Gerrit Lehner\'s lecture on \"Potential and Problems in the Ut', 'As agreed with your secretary Nora, I herewith confirm that Dr. Lehner will give a lecture on \"Potential and Problems in the Utilization of Solar Energy\", on Monday, March 8, 1982 at 10 a.m. at the UP College of Engineering Bldg., Room 414. ', 'Bretzler, Dr. Gerrit', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(555, 'E2-0555AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, February 18) Invitation for a luncheon meeting with the CE staff and members of the graduatin', 'This is to confirm our invitation to you, to the CE staff, as well as to the members of the graduating class of EE, CE and ME for a luncheon meeting on Saturday, 20 February 1982 at 11:30 a.m. at the Asian Institute of Tourism. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nCapitol Industrial Construction\nDaquiz, Renato M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(556, 'E2-0556AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, February 25) Proposed Curriculum Development (Phase II) ', 'The technical committee on the Ladder-type Curriculum in the Mining Sciences Project of the Ministry held a meeting last February 5, 1982 to draw up details and comments on the proposed curriculum development (Phase II). It was pointed out that there is an increasing need for skilled manpower in the mining industry for the next (5) years or more. \nTwo options were considered for curriculum development. The first is the certificate program wherein a skilled worker will finish in a certain period of time after which he can go back to work in his company. It maybe noted that the certificate for masteral program has been abolished. The other option is the institutionalized training program to be participated by qualified candidates from the mining companies. \nAnother issue concerns the demands for mining workers abroad. The fluctuation of workers who have already undergone training in the curriculum might endanger the domestic supply of skilled miners. There is a possibility, however, of increased foreign exchange earnings due to this factor. \nIt was also suggested that there is a possibility that other technical/vocational schools could offer the Ladder-type Curriculum in their respective institutions unlike what has been originally proposed which limit the curriculum only to the University of the Philippines. \nIn this connection, transmitted herewith for your comments and recommendations is the project proposal by UPCB and BMG. Also enclosed are copies of the Survey of Skilled Manpower Requirements of the Mining Industry in Ilocos Region and the highlights of the workshop/seminar on Ladder-type Curriculum held in Baguio City on 6-8 September, 1978 for your reference. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nValerio, Jesus D. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(557, 'E2-0557AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, March 9) Modular or Ladder Type Curriculum', 'Dean, I have always been in favor of a modular or a ladder type curriculum even if the plan basically emphasizes the \"dropping out\" feature. \nIn U.P. Baguio\'s proposal, a number of things have to be considered.\n1. The graduates will basically be technicians of the trade school level. Under the CRAP criterion \"Is the program University level in nature?\" The proposal will be unacceptable. \n2. The proposal envisions the students to advance to the BS Geol or BSEM  degree programs after their 3rd year and then expect to graduate after only 1 or 2 years more, respectively. \n- To enter this quota degree programs, will the UPCAT be waived for them?\n- The BS programs require 67 units of gen. educ.; 53 units of engg sciences and service courses; 12 units of Spanish; 41 units of specialization courses. Will there be enough room for all of these? Even graduates of other Engineering courses like Met E find it very difficult to finish BSEM in 2 years. \n3. The course envisions answering a very wide variety of technical skills without or with minimum in service training in the mines. Technical skill can only be acquired through practice, never through lectures or books. If the proposal requires use of company production equipment, I can see very little excuse for dispensing with in-service trainng in from of the proposal. If company equipment will not be used, enormous equipment and physical facilities will have to be provided. Envisioning UP Baguio maintaining Bulldozers, Cranes, Hoists, Alimak raise climbers locomotions, a railway and a quarry to practice on boggles the imagination. ', 'Ordillas, M. U.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(558, 'E2-0558AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, May 4) One Day Seminar Work shop - \"Seminar-Workshop on the Report of the Management Review C', 'In its 943rd meeting on July 31, 1981, the Board of Regents has authorized President Edgardo J. Angara to \"conduct a comprehensive review and appraisal\" of the : (a) academic programs; (b) organizational structure and management; and, (c) land use and infrastructure development. Pursuant to this authority, the President issued Administrative Order No. 58 (August 18, 1981) creating the Management Review Committee to conduct \"an appraisal and audit of the organization and management functions of the University of the Philippines System, in order to achieve modern and progressive, effective and economical, and coordinated and simplified organization and management operations appropriate to a multi-campus University. \nThe MRC has already submitted its report to the President and there is now a need to get the reactions and recommendations of the various sectors of the University including the Central Administration Officials, Deans, Directors, Faculty Members, Non-Academic Staff, Administrative Personnel and Students. \nIn this regard, the MRC, PDS and the UPMEC are sponsoring a one-day \"Seminar-Workshop on the Report of the Management Review Committee on the Organizational Structure and Management of the University of the Philippines System\", to be held on 19 May 1982 (Wednesday) at the Seminar Room, Asian Institute of Tourism. The major topics to be discussed in the seminar are : (1) Concept of the University of the Philippines System; (2) Relation Units; (3) Organization and Management of Academic Units, including Research and Extension Centers / Institutes. The objectives of the seminar are : (1) To discuss the report of the MRC on the organizational structure and management of the University; (2) To identify and discuss other issues and problems related to the organizational structure and management of the University which were not resolved or covered in the report; and, (3) to formulate recommendations on the report of the MRC. \nThe seminar is the first of the series of seminars/discussions on the report of the MRC which the UPMEC in collaboration with MRC and PDS is planning to undertake. The other topics to be discussed in the future are : (1) Planning and Financing; (2) Manning and Personnel Management; (3) Library Administration; (4) Auxilliary Enterprises and Services; (5) Supply Management; (6) Records Management; (7) Building, Utilities and Grounds Administration; and (8) Community Services. ', 'De Guzman, Raul P. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(559, 'E2-0559AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, June 1) Seminar on the Management Review Committee Report on Manning and Personnel Management', 'The University of the Philippines Management Review Committee, Vice-President for Administration, Office of the President and the Management Education Council are sponsoring a one-day \"Seminar-Workshop on the MRC Report on Manning and Personnel Management\" to be held on 16 June 1982 (Wednesday) at the U.P. - AIT House, Diliman, Quezon City. The seminar-workshop is the sixth of a series of seminars/discussions on the MRC report. This seminar is intended to : (1) inform the various sectors of the University and get comments and reactions on the report of the Committee on Manning and Personnel Management; (2) Identify and discuss other issues and problems related to manning and personnel management which were not resolved or covered in the report; and, (3) Formulate recommendations on the report of the Committee on Manning and Personnel Management. ', 'De Guzman, Raul P. \nMena, Marino M. .', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(560, 'E2-0560AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, June 4) Resource justification and plan of operation for the Proposed Bachelor of Computer Sc', 'This is a proposal to institute a four-year undergraduate program, the Bachelor of Computer Science Program, to be jointly offered by the Department of Engineering Sciences, the Department of Electrical Engineering, and the Department of Mathematics. The program aims to implement a baccalaureate curriculum in computer science with emphasis on software design and to equip graudates of the program with reasonable mastery of the fundamental ideas of computer science and of the associated skills so that these graduates can be effective in practice and can overcome on their own the rapid onset of obsolescence so common in this field. Undergraduate students whose field of interest is computer hardware may instead pursue a B.S. in Electrical Engineering degree with senior option in Computer Engineering. The current masteral program in Computer Science shall be phased out in the meantime because present resources are inadequate to support both baccalaureate and masteral programs. \nStarted in school year 1975-76, the Master of Engineering in Computer Science Program is an existing joint graduate program of the Department of Engineering Sciences and the Department of Electrical Engineering of the College of Enginering. It was designed to provide training in the major fields into which the entire computer science discipline had differentiated during the late sixties and early seventies. The curriculum requires 36 units of coursework on software and hardware areas of the discipline, with particular emphasis on software. Holders of Bachelor of Science degrees in engineering, mathematics, statistics, and other natural sciences wre admitted to the program. The main objective of the program is to equip the students with the knowledge and skills that qualify or else upgrade their status as systems analysts, systems programmers, and at best, applications software, database or information system designers and administrators, complementary to their baccalaureate and work experience qualifications. ', 'Gregorio, Martin V. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(561, 'E2-0561AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, June 14) UNDP Questionnaire on TCDC Information Referral System (INRES) ', 'One of UNDP\'s major undertakings towards the promotion of technical cooperation among developing countries has been the establishment of an Information Referral System (INRES). In 1977 and 1978, with the cooperation of the governments involved, INRES produced and distributed directories of Technical Services available in developing countries for TCDC activities. Based on our collective experience to date, UNDP has further improved and redesigned the system. \nWe now plan to develop an enquiry facility at UNDP Headquarters, in New York that would permit quick and thorough search for relevant information in order to respond to enquiries received through cable or mail. To make INRES more responsive to TCDC needs, the improvements will concentrate on (a) expanding the coverage to a larger number of organizations and institutions; (b) broadening the information available within the areas of training/education, research and technological development, consultancy and expert services as well as scientific and technological information services; (c) inclusion of specific TCDC experience of organizations and institutions in any of the fields covered by INRES.\nTo collect the requisite information, a questionnaire has been designed and, in consultation with the Government\'s TCDC Focal Point, is being sent to selected institutions and agencies having the necessary capability and capacity for TCDC. \nYour institution/agency has been included among the above, and we would very much appreciate your having the enclosed questionnaire completed (following the attached detailed instructions for completing the forms) and returned to us as soon as possible but preferably no later than 30 June 1982. \nThe degree to which the TCDC Information Referral System will be able to respond effectively to enquiries and needs of institutions and agencies within the developing countries will very much depend upon the information obtained through these questionnaires. We would therefore be grateful for your cooperation in this exercise. ', 'Milley, Ross H. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(562, 'E2-0562AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, July 13) half-day \"Seminar on the Management Review Committee Report on Building, Utilities a', 'The University of the Philippines Management Review Committee, Campus Landscaping Office and Arboretum, Program Development Staff, and the Management Education Council are sponsoring a half-day \"Seminar on the Management Review Committee Report on Building, Utilities and Grounds Administration,\" to be held on 21 July 1982 (Wednesday) at the Vinzon\'s Hall Conference Room, University of the Philippines, Diliman, Quezon City.\nThe objectives of the seminar are : (1) To inform the various sectors of the University and get comments and reactions on the MRC report on building, utilities and grounds administration; (2) To identify and discuss other issues and problems related to building, utilities and grounds administration which were not resolved or covered in the report; and, (3) To formulate recommendations on the MRC report on building, utilities and grounds administration. ', 'De Guzman, Raul P. \nMena, Marino M. .', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(563, 'E2-0563AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, July 29) Abolition of the M. Eng\'g (Computer Science) program', 'Pursuant to the resolution adopted by the Board of Regents of the University of the Philippines System at its 946th meeting held on 22 December 1981 granting the President the power to formulate and adopt recommendations necessary and proper to effect reform of the academic programs as well as the reorganization of the structure and operaitons of the UPS; and considering, that the Committee to Review Academic Programs (CRAP) has submitted recommendations for the institution, revision and abolition of academic programs; and further that said recommendations have passed through the appropriate academic bodies, the following matters shall take force and effect at the end of sixty (60) days from date hereof, unless within said 60-day period, vetoed by the Board of Regents in a meeting called for that purpose : \nAbolition of the M. Eng\'g. (Computer Science) program. ', 'Gregorio, Martin V. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(564, 'E2-0564AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, August 5) half-day \"Seminar on the Committee on the University Police Force Report on Protect', 'The University of the Philippines Management Review Committee, Office of the President and the Management Education Council will hold a half-day \"Seminar on the Committee on the University Police Force Report on Protective Services\", on 11 August 1982 at the Seminar Room, Asian Institute of Tourism. \nThe above-mentioned Committee was constituted by President Edgardo J. Angara on 28 October 1981 to review and re-evaluate present University policy on the functions, responsibilities and authority of the U.P. Police Force. Dean Luis D. Beltran was the Chairman of the Committee, with Dr. Manuel F. Bonifacio, Prof. Merlin M. Magallona, Dr. Ledivina V. Cariño and Mr. Jose Fernando Alcantra, as members. \nThe objectives of the forthcoming seminar are : (1) To inform the various sectors of the University and get comments and reactions on the Committee on the University Police Force Report on Protective Services; (2) To identify and discuss other issues and problems related to Protective Services which were not resolved or covered in the report; and, (3) To formulate recommendations on the report on the Committee on the University Police Force. \nIn this regard, may we invite you (or your representative) to attend and share with us your views/comments on the report of the Committee. The UPMEC Secretariat will be calling on you for confirmation. ', 'De Guzman, Raul P. \nMena, Marino M.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(565, 'E2-0565AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, August 24) Ministry of Public Works and Highways requesting information on our course offerin', 'This is in reply to your letter dated August 10, 1982 requesting information on our course offerings on the design and maintenance of roads/highways, bridges and drainage which could be used for upgrading the expertise of your technical manpower, we are pleased to send herewith a copy of our course offerings in civil engineering on the above mentioned topics. However, these are formal course offerings. For some of your need, nonformal short courses may be desirable depending on the background of the participants, the level of training required and the time availability of the participants. Should you be interested in exploring the possibility of having short non-formal courses, you may ask your representative to see Dean Marino Mena or Dr. Ernesto G. Tabujara, Chairman of the Department of Civil Engineering. \nThe Master of Engineering Program aims primarily to provide opportunity for advancement in the field of engineering through professional competence and scholarly achievement. A minimum requirement of at least one year residence and 30 units of graduate courses must be fulfilled for the degree of Master of Science. For details, contact the Director, Graduate Division, College of Engineering, University of the Philippines, Diliman, Quezon City. ', 'Fadullon, Samuel T. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(566, 'E2-0566AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, September 2) \"SWAK \'82\", an Inter-Block Freshman Basketball Tournament', 'The U.P. Gamma Sigma Pi Fraternity, a university-wide fraternity based in the College of Engineering, is sponsoring \"SWAK \'82\", an Inter-Block Freshman Basketball Tournament. It started last August 26 and is expected to end on September 13, 1982. This activity is in line with the Fraternity\'s thrust of service for the freshment students. \nIn this connection, we are seeking your assistance in the form of a 30-inch trophy to be awarded for the runner-up. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nQuiwa, Jesse\nRañeses, Nestor ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(567, 'E2-0567AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, September 13) Invitation to participate in a workshop on the Ecological Information Decision ', 'The National Environmental Protection Council (NEPC) is currently involved in the development of analytical and evaluation techniques that incorporate ecological considerations in planning and decision-making. One such methodology called the Ecological Information Decision System (EIDS) is being tested by NEPC as to its suitability to land-use planning and decision-making in the country. The EIDS has been called the ecosystem approach to planning of human settlements to signify its heavy emphasis on ecological relationships and functions and the constraints these impose on the planning process. \nA major component of the EIDS is the development of a comprehensive list of ecological factors to be considered in ascertaining the suitability of various development sites to different land uses such as residential, industrial-commercial and agricultural uses. For each prospective land use, there will be certain factors of greatest importance and these can be selected. Moreover, there will be a ranking of importance and so the factors can be assigned numerical values. The output of the EIDS consists of land-suitability decision maps which are numerical overlays of ecovalue maps of the various ecological factors considered. \nIn connection with this, we are cordially inviting you to participate in a workshop on the EIDS to be held on 19-20 October, 1982 at the AIT House, Diliman, Quezon City. The objectives of the workshop are : (i) verification of the list of ecological factors developed; (ii) assignment of relative weights to each of the ecological parameters; (iii) determination of relevant land-use decision maps to be produced by the project. ', 'Roque, Celso R. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(568, 'E2-0568AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, September 21) Proposal : Institution of a Postgraduate Program in Energy Engineering ', 'We are sending you copies of the following : \n1.) Proposed postgraduate program in Energy Engineering, which includes the following : \na.) Ph.D. in Energy Engineering\nb.) Energy Engineering as a major field in our proposed M.S. in Engineering\nc.) Institution of graduate courses in Energy Engineering\n2.) Proposed Master of Science in Engineering program to replace our M.S. and Master of Engineering programs. \nOur official communication on the above items was coursed thru the Univerity Registrar. ', 'Alabastro\nEscoto', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(569, 'E2-0569AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The Beta Epsilon Fraternity is sponsoring the premiere of the movie \"Blade Runner,\" a science-advent', 'The Beta Epsilon Fraternity or Brotherhood of Engineers is the oldest college fraternity in the University of the Philippines. In its fifty three productive years of existence, the Brotherhood has always kept a tradition of service and excellence in all its undertakings. Being the sole recipient of the Wenceslao Vinzon\'s Award for Service, the highest award given to any campus organization, all its activities have been well applauded and acknowledged by the UP community. \nThe Beta Epsilon Fraternity is sponsoring the premiere of the movie \"Blade Runner,\" a science-adventure fiction movie starring Harrison Ford. The premiere is set on September 24 at the Meralco Theater at 7:30 pm. Part of the proceeds of this premiere will go to White Cross, Inc., an orphanage and child care center. \nThe Brotherhood hopes that you believe and support its objectives by being one of its advertisers in the souvenir program, which will be distributed on the premiere night.\nAs future engineers and builders of tomorrow, we have been trained by the Brotherhood to recognize the joy of service and the value of excellence. It is only with your support that we may continue to be of service to the University and the country. We are hoping for your kind consideration and support in this endeavor.  ', 'Abis, Bernardo F.\nTabujara, Ricardo A.III', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(570, 'E2-0570AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, October 28) \"Seminar-Workshop on Extension Services and Consultancy Services of the Universit', 'The University of the Philippines College of Business Administration, Office of the Vice-President for Planning and Finance and the Management Educaiton Council will hold a \"Seminar-Workshop on Extension Services and Consultancy Services of the University of the Philippines System\" on 15 November 1982 at Shin Nien Room, Asian Institute of Tourism, University of the Philippines, Diliman, Quezon City. \nThe objectives of the forthcoming seminare are : (1) To inform the various sectors of the University and get comments and reactions on the Report on Extension Services and Consultancy Services in the University; (2) To identify and discuss other issues and problems related to Extension Services and Consultancy Services, which were not resolved or covered in the report; and (3) To formulate recommendations on the report on Extension Services and Consultancy Services in the University. ', 'De Guzman, Raul P. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(571, 'E2-0571AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, November 16) Seminar on Productivity ', 'The National Engineering Center (NEC) with the support of the Educational Development Projects Implementing Task Force (EDPITAF) will be sponsoring a seminar on Productivity on December 8 to 10, 1982 to be held at the NEC Audio-Visual Room. For this seminar, which will be national in scope, emphasis will be given to providing the engineering faculty with the basic concepts of productivity, tools and techniques for problem/opportunity analysis as well as specific approaches and methods in productivity enhancement.\nAs a Participating Engineering School, we would like you to send three (3) representatives whom you think would benefit from this seminar. As usual, each participant will receive a stipend of P52/day and snacks and lunch will be provided. However, you will have to shoulder his/her/their transportation and accomodation expenses. ', 'Abis, Leopoldo V.\nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(572, 'E2-0572AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, November 16) Participate in a work-shop', 'I was delighted to receive your message mentioning that you would be able to participate in our Workshop next month, as well as in the meeting of Asian institutions for developing a concrete work-plan. I would be grateful if you could come prepared with the details of the work-plan as they apply to your University. It may be useful for you to discuss this work-plan with others in the Government of Philippines etc. \nI am also writing to you with a personal request. Last year when I was in the USA, my wife had bought some beautiful pieces from Manila, which unfortunately were lost in transit to the USA because her baggage was lost and never recovered. Do you think it would be possible for you to buy and bring with you a shell (kapees) lamp full length approximately 5 ft. for hanging from the ceiling and which can be folded up in a compact size? Also if you could please bring a set of golden shell (kapees) round table mats for eight settings. I do hope I have been able to explain what I mean, but these are very popular items made in the Philippines and I hope you would not have too much trouble buying them and bringing them with you. Needless to say I shall reimburse the amount of expenditure incurred by you. I would be most grateful for your help in this matter.', 'Pachauri, R.K. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(573, 'E2-0573AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1982, December 3) International Fellowship Program \nEngineering Education Project ', 'Since the Project is nearing completion, the Asian Development Bank (ADB) is currently conducting a Review Mission to assess the progress of Project implementation. In view of this and more particularly to review the International Fellowship program, we are enclosing forms on topics / courses covered by the fellowship; relevance of fellowship to the fellow\'s present job, among other things.', 'Cruz, Fabian N. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(574, 'E2-0574AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1983, August 1) Requesting assistance from the U.P. Engineering Research and Development Foundation', 'I received your letter dated 23 June 1983 requesting assistance from the U.P. Engineering Research and Development Foundation, Inc. (UPERDFI) in the amount of P250,000 for the purchase of ten (10) microcomputer units. One of the primary objectives of UPERDFI is to provide continuing support to the U.P. College of Engineering (UPCE) and therefore it shares your strong concern for the development of a sound and high-standard academic program in the field of Computer Science. ', 'Angara, Atty. Edgardo J. \nJuinio, Alfredo L. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(575, 'E2-0575AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1983, August 22) Induction of the Engineering Student Council', 'Allow us to thank you for your support during the elections and campaign.\nOn Monday, August 22 at 3:00 PM, will be the induction of the Engineering Student Council. It will be held at the 3rd floor lobby, and refreshments will be served at the Engineering Activity Room, 1st floor. You are cordially invited to attend. ', 'Felicio, Nestor L. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(576, 'E2-0576AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1984, January 30) Acquisition of fully-dedicated microcomputers for the Bachelor of Computer Scienc', 'We wish to inform you of the latest developments regarding the acquisition of fully-dedicated microcomputers for the Bachelor of Computer Science program. \nIn the current school year 1983-84, the program has been able to acquire one (1) unit of Fujitsu FM-8 microcomputer through a grant from ERDF and four (4) units of Taiwan-made Apple II from U.P. Foundation funds, both as local purchases. We had another request to import ten (10) FM-8 microcomputers which, unfortunately, was not approved by Minister J.C. Tuvera, Presidential Executive Assistant, in view of the present economic situation and that foreign exchange outflow is not warranted at the moment. We wish to provide you with the details of this request and suggest an alternative course of action to expedite the acquisition. ', 'Angara, Atty Edgardo J. \nLiongson, Leonardo Q.\nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(577, 'E2-0577AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1984, April 9) Annual report of the UP Management Education Council', 'The U.P. Management Education Council was established through Administrative Order No. 120 issued by the University President on October 11, 1973 and was subsequently confirmed by the Board of Regents on its 916th meeting held on July 1979. The Council is composed of deans, directors and heads of University units offering degree and non-degree programs in management education, as well as units extending support in the conduct of management education and training. \nTo provide the Council with technical and administrative support in the performance of its tasks, the Secretariat was formed in July 1977. Since then, the Secretariat has assisted in coordinating and monitoring the various programs and activities of the Council.\nThe Council also serves as an advisory body to the Office of the Vice-President for Planning and Finance. The Board of Regents at its 954th meeting held on October 22, 1982 approved the recommendation of the University President designating the Vice-President for Planning and Finance as the Chairman of the Council. ', 'Angara, President Edgardo J. \nDe Guzman, Raul P. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(578, 'E2-0578AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1984, April 25) Excerpt from the Minutes of the 967th Meeting of the Board of Regents held on April', 'On motion duly seconded, the Board approved the following matters from the University Council of : \nA. U.P. Diliman\n3. College of Engineering\na. Institution of a Diploma Program in Industrial Engineering and revision of courses in the Master of Science Program in Engineering \nb. Revision of Bachelor of Sciences (Industrial Engineering)\nc. Revision of Bachelor of Science (Metallurgical Engineering)', 'Gregorio, Martin V. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(579, 'E2-0579AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1984, May 24) Revision of the Metallurgical Engineering Curriculum', 'In the April 13th meeting of the University Council this year, the revision of the Metallurgical Engineering Curriculum was approved. Part of this curriculum is the course Met.E. 128 - (Mineral Processing Laboratory). Its co-requisites as stated are Met. E. 121 or Met. E. 127. The latter, Met. E. 127, was meant for Metallurgical Engineering students while Met. E. 121 was meant for Metallurgical Engineering students while Met. E. 121, however, was intended as Met. E. 120 if the course Met. E. 20 (Ore Dressing) had been renumbered to follow current University practice of numbering courses. This was a typographical error. The co-requisites should have been Met. E. 20 or Met. E. 127.\nWe are, therefore, requesting that the co-requisites for Met. E. 128 (Mineral Processing Laboratory) be changed so as to read Met.E. 20 or Met. E 127. The typographical error was discovered during the presentation of the proposed revision in the Mining Engineering curriculum to the University Cluster Committee for Science and Technology. ', 'Ordillas, Meliton U.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(580, 'E2-0580AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1984, September 27) Excerpt from the Minutes of the 971st meeting of the Board of Regents held on S', 'Matters approved by the Board of Regents upon recommendation of the President : \nPurchase of the following microcomputers : \n1. Two (2) microcomputers and a printer at a cost of P252,000 for easier and more accurate management of a student records in the University Registrar\'s Office. This will also be made available to individual colleges who may wish to computerize their own student records. \n2. Fifteen (15) microcomputers at a total of P400,000 for the B.S. Computer Science program. These additional units will boost the 11 microcomputers being used by 130 students currently enrolled in the Program. Enrollment is expected to incease by about 224 students next year. \n3. One (1) microcomputer and a printer at a cost of P145,000 to be used for computerizing personnel records in the Human Resource Development Office. Computerizing personnel records will be a great boon to University management since the tedious process of culling data from the files will be eliminated.', 'Mena, Marino M. \nGregorio, Martin V.', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(581, 'E2-0581AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, January 15) Comments on the Comprehensive Report on the System-Wide Conference on Graduate St', 'The concluding paragraph of the report might fail to give the reader an accurate picture of what transpired during the Conference. In fact, it can be misleading. An effort must be made to state more clearly the following : \n1. During the Conference Plenary Session, a motion to approve the recommendations of Workshop Groups A. B and C was not carried. What the Conference approved was the motion to receive the reports of the Workshop Groups and transmit the same to University authorities without recommending their approval or disapproval. \n2. The discussion in Group C was characterized by controversy and disagreement particularly on the question of a graduate faculty. The first resolution was passed only after it was clarified that the statement \"....the Graduate School shall have its faculty\" simply meant that faculty members teaching graduate courses shall be given additional designations as faculty members of the Graduate School. ', 'Pacheco, Edgardo S. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(582, 'E2-0582AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, February 11) Presidential Decree No. 1295 of 27th January 1978 established the National Engin', 'Presidential Decree No. 1295 of 27th January 1978 established the National Engineering Center (NEC) within the University of the Philippines at Diliman, Quezon City. Its objectives were set out as follows : \na. To meet the urgent needs of engineering schools and industry for professionals with advanced training in engineering. \nb. To develop innovative educational programmes, teaching materials and methods of instruction specifically designed for the Philippine setting which may serve as models for other engineering schools.\nc. To provide a pool of technical experts to which public and private entities may turn for assistance in the solution of their engineering problems.\nd. To develop technologies that utilize local resources and which are adapted to the needs of a developing country. \ne. To identify technology-oriented ecological problems and to support studies aimed at their solutions.', 'Ramos, Paz G. \nAbis, Leopoldo ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(583, 'E2-0583AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, January 28) 2nd Indorsement ', 'Respectfully returned to Vice Chancellor Paz G. Ramos, the attached communication regarding the holding of review classes, with the following comments : \n1. Firstly, the undersigned believes that educational institutions are universally recognized as the credentialing agent within our society. Such a credentialing responsibility extends beyond the traditional bachelor\'s, master\'s and Ph.D. degrees. Thus, any credentials to be awarded as a result of the accumulation of educational experience in the classrooms of academic programs, in-plant courses, short courses or correspondence courses should be from an educational institution. \n2. If the envisioned classes can be classified as part of a continuing education program for the purpose of upgrading the knowledge of the engineering graduate and preparing him to better practice his engineering profession, this is a responsibility of the academic institution.\n3. Pursuant to the premise in the No. 1 and subject to the conditions in No. 2, the undersigned has no objection to the offering of such short courses. For example, a short course in design can be offered to include the recent developments and strengthen the engineer\'s capability in this field. Similar courses can be developed in other areas of interest depending on the needs of the target groups. \n4. However, let us not call it \"review classes\". If the intent is just to review what the engineer already learned in his five-year BS program, the undersigned feels that it is not necessary.\n5. In summary, continuing education is a responsibility of the academic institution and should be institutionalized. ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(584, 'E2-0584AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, April 19) Engineering Shops (Welding Shop Section) was entered by robber (s)', 'I am reporting that the Engineering Shops (Welding Shop Section) was entered by robber (s) last night April 17, 1985, possibly between 7:00 p.m. to 6:00 a.m. the following day, April 18, 1985. This is the second time this month that the Shops has been robbed. The first incident was on April 11, 1985, which the undersigned has reported to the Dean, and the second time is April 17, 1985. \nThe equipment lost in this incident is : \na. One (1) set of OX-AC HOSE, complete with pressure gauge (tank and hose gauges) and mixing chamber components. Total cost of the above set is P1,600.00\nSince all the door entrances of the Engineering Shops were not tampered of forced open, and all the windows on the first floor are provided with iron grilles, the undersigned and his staff with the help of the investigating unit of the UP Police Force surmised that the possible point of entry are the windows without iron grilles on the second floor (mezzanine) of the Textile Building located on the southern end of the building. , facing Roces Avenue. This area is where the reserach program (Gasifier) of Dr. Ibarra Cruz is located. \nTo minimize the illegal entrance of unauthorized people in the Shop, the undersigned in consultation with Dr. Garcia recommends that these ungrilled windows be provided with iron grills. Approximate cost for iron bars including welding rods is about P13,000.00. This amount does not include cost for labor and installation. Maybe labor could be jointly provided by the personnel of the Engineering Shop and the M.E. Power Laboratory. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nMalabed, Bernardino\nHernandez, Manuel V. Jr.  ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(585, 'E2-0585AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, April 22) Graduate School Admission Form ', 'The following are my comments on the draft application for admission form coming from the Graduate School : \n1. The opening statement of the Memorandum Circular (\"In pursuance to the recommendation of the faculty at the Graduate Studies Conference ---\") is incorrect. The Conference did not make any recommendation. It simply received the reports of the Workshop Groups without acting on them. \n2. Item No. 19 of the proposed form specifies that the application form and supporting papers must be sent to the Dean of the Graduate School. This is an unnecessary step which will only prolong the processing of applications. The Dean of the Graduate School does not play any role in the admission process. Hence, applications for admission should be sent directly to the units concerned. ', 'Pacheco, Edgardo S. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(586, 'E2-0586AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, April 24) Ad Hoc Committee on Manufacturing Engineering submit the following consensus and re', 'The undersigned, in behalf of the other members of the Ad Hoc Committee on Manufacturing Engineering, respectfully submit the following consensus and recommendations concerning its tasks for your consideration : \n1. That Manufacturing Engineering is a field or discipline where expertise needs to be developed int he country today.\n2. That the U.P. College of Engineering should have a share inthe responsibility for training manpower in this field.\n3. That in consideration of the needs, the availability of academic programs in the field in other institutions, and the capabilities of the College, both existing and pontetial, the College can best make a contribution through graduate education. \n4. That an MS Program in Manufacturing Engineering appears to be appropriate, timely and attractive to offer\n5. That the MS (Mfg. Eng\'g) Program should be an interdisciplinary program that should draw the involvement of at least the ChE, EE, IE, ME and Met. E. departments. \n6. That the MS (Mfg. Eng\'g) Program should be open to any baccalaureate degree holder in engineering provided the usual admission requirements (grade average, etc.) are met. \n7. That the MS (Mfg. Eng\'g) Program should feature core courses in Product Design, Manufacturing Facilities Design, Materials Engineering, Human Resource Engineering, Engineering Economics, and Production Planning and Control. This should also conform with College requirements through the inclusion of a course on Numerical Methods and a course on Optimization (Applied Math). \n8. That the MS (Mfg. Eng\'g) program should offer specialization options and the suggested ones are as follows : \n(a) Machine Design\n(b) Product Design\n(c) Management of Manufacturing Systems\n9. That graduate courses in product design be made available in at least four departments namely ChE, EE, ME and Met. E. \n10. That a mechanism should now be put forth into motion to study the detailed design, resource requirements and feasibility of an MS (Mfg. Eng\'g) Program at the College. In connection with this, existing graduate courses should be reviewed to study the possibility of adopting those which would fit into the envisioned program. ', 'Mena, Marino M. \nDe la Peña, Fortunato T. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(587, 'E2-0587AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, June 6) Comments / Recommendations re Highlights of Recommendations on Graduate Studies ', 'A. Administrative Structures\nB. Graduate Faculty\nC. Graduate Students', 'Pacheco, Edgardo S. \nMena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(588, 'E2-0588AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, June 5) Highlights of Recommendations on Graduate Studies \n(Recommendations that need further', 'A. Administrative Structures\nB. Graduate Faculty\nC. Graduate Students', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(589, 'E2-0589AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, June 25) Request to purchase IBM Compatibles instead of Fujitsu FM-8\'s', 'We have just been informed by the Cashier\'s Office that the P250,000 authorized for \"equipment outlays\" by Malacañang for the purchase of eleven (11) microcomputers for the computer science laboratory has been transferred from the National Treasury to the PNB Diliman branch. \nIt was originally the intention to acquire Fujitsu FM\'8\'s with the funds, as reflected in earlier communications. ', 'Tabujara, Dr. Ernesto G.\nVea, Reynaldo B. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(590, 'E2-0590AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1985, September 9) Induction of Officers ', 'The UP Inter-Fraternity Council will hold its induction of new officers tomorrow (September 10, 1985) at 3:30 in the afternoon aat the Executive House, Diliman Campus. ', 'Silva, Albert S. \nGarcia, Ruben A. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(591, 'E2-0591AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1979, March 12) Academic Personnel Committee', 'Please be informed that in a referendum conducted today among the faculty members of the Department of Civil Engineering, the following are the newly designated members of the C.E. Academic Personnel Committee : \nProfessor Marina M. Mena, Chairman\nProfessor Rodolfo U. Bulatao, Senior Member \nProfessor Manuel Jabson, Junior Member ', 'Mena, Marino M. ', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49');
