(1003, 'E2-1003AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXI, Number 2 (6 copies)', '', '', 'March to April 2015', 'Tara, Tena! \nbalikUPDorm launched\nUPD student volunteers with former dorm manager Alma Tirona beside an Ikot jeepney used to visit the residence halls as part of the \"Tara Tena : balikUPDorm Grand Launch and Fellowship\" on Apr. 25. - photo courtesy of OVCSA\nby Haidee C. Pineda, images by Jefferson Villacruz\nFormer dormers and dorm managers had an afternoon of reminiscing and \"throwbacks\" at the \"Tara Tena : balikUPDorm Grand Launch and Fellowship\" held at the University Theater on Apr. 25 \nLagmay wins Plinius Medal\n7th SEADOM Congress at CMu\n15 countries participated\nBy Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nHeads of tertiary level music schools and institutions from 15 countries convened at the UP Diliman College of Music (CMu) for the 7th Southeast Asian Directors of Music (SEADOM) Congress to discuss music advocacy, music curriculum and research, music institution communication in Southeast Asia, professional development and community engagement, among others. \nUPD has 15 POSCO scholars by Haidee C. Pineda, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe Pohang Iron and Steel Company TJ Park Foundation (POSCO-TJPF), through its POSCO Asia Fellowship program, awarded scholarships to 15 UP Diliman (UPD) students for Academic Year (AY) 2015-2016.\nALYANSA leads USC 2015 election by Haidee C. Pineda\nAlyansa ng mga Mag-aaral para sa Panlipunang Katwiran at Kaunlaran (ALYANSA) once again dominated the UPD University Student Council (USC) election on Apr. 23, securing the top two posts and eight of the 12 council seats. \n3 Students reap BPI-DOST Science Awards by Albino C. Gamba, image by Leonardo Reyes\nRaiza Elmira S. Imperial (BS Chemistry), Steven Matthew C. Cheng (BS Electronics and Communications Engineering) and Xavier M. Puspus (BS Applied Physics) are this year\'s recipients of the Bank of the Philippine Islands (BPI)-Department of Science and Technology (DOST) Science Awards.\nRP : retirement haven \nText and image by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nLower cost of living and reminders of a nostalgic past : these are the two main reasons why some 8,000 South Koreans (Koreans) chose to retire in the Philippines. \nEconomics for better health\nText and image by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nSix out of 10 sick Filipinos die without seeing a doctor, revealed a 1990 study by the UPecon Foundation, Inc. (UFI) of the UP School of Economics (SE). \nUPD team to create first Filipino micro-satellite by Anna Regidor\nA team of UP Diliman (UPD) experts was tapped by the Department of Science and Technology (DOST) to steer the Philippines into its space age. \nNIP, 2 faculty receive NRCP honors\nThe National Institute of Physics (NIP) and two of its faculty members were honored by the National Research Council of the Philippines (NRCP) during the NRCP\'s 82nd General Membership Assembly on Mar. 11 at the Philippine International Convention Center. \nStat prof 1st Pinoy to win Cochran-Hansen Prize\nProf. Kevin Carl Santos of the UP Diliman (UPD) School of Statistics is honored with this year\'s Cochran-Hansen Prize of the International Association of Survey Statisticians (IASS). \nCS inaugurates IM classrooms\nTwo newly-renovated classrooms at the UP Diliman (UPD) College of Science (CS), Institute of Mathematics (IM), were turned over by Manulife Philippines to UPD on Apr. 1. \nAng mga babaeng martir ng UPD ni Kevin Brandon E. Saure, larawan mula sa UPD Gender Office\nMay limang kinikilalang babaeng martir ang nagmula sa UP Diliman (UPD). Ayon kay Prop. Bernadette Neri, tagapag-ugnay ng UP Diliman Gender Office (UPDGO), sila ay sina Ma. Lorena Barros, Purificacion Pedro, Tanya Domingo, Christine Puche at Recca Monte. \nCMC prof writes 30\nThe Department of Communication Research and the UPD College of Mass Communication (CMC) are deeply saddened by the passing away of Prof. Florinda de Fiesta-Mateo, PhD, on Apr. 18, after a lingering illness. She is survived by her husband, Dr. Ricardo J. Mateo Jr., and daughters Felicia Margarita and Alyssa. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1004, 'E2-1004AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXI, Number 3 (7 copies)', '', '', 'May-June 2015', 'Sunflowers and sunshine make UPD\'s first June graduation\n\"Rock star\" summa is new media darling\nBy Haidee C. Pineda, Images by Jefferson Villacruz\nRays of sunshine cascaded through the campus grounds as early as 6 a.m. on June 28 while sunflowers in full bloom adorning the University Avenue welcomed the graduates, parents, faculty, officials and other guests at UP Diliman\'s 104th General Commencement Exercises at the University Amphitheater. \n13 receive UPD\'s highest recognition by Chi A. Ibay, images by Jefferson Villacruz\nTwelve individuals and a residential area on campus received the Gawad Tsanselor, the highest recognition bestowed by UP Diliman for excellence and outstanding accomplishment.\nStat dean is SEARCA Regional Professorial Chair awardee\nParada ng Parangal highlights UPD\'s best by Anna E. Regidor, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes, Jefferson Villacruz\nUP Diliman (UPD) flaunted its best and brightest in a parade greeted with cheers and fanfare as students, faculty and staff achievers marched around the Academic Oval for the first ever Parada ng Parangal (Parade of Honor) on May 4. \nUPD honors 2015 student achievers by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nUP Diliman recognized 4,378 University Scholars in the undergraduate and graduate levels and those who distinguished themselves in various fields at the Parangal sa Mag-aaral 2015, May 6 at the University Theater. \nUPD honors retirees and service awardees by Albino C. Gamba Jr., images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nUP Diliman (UPD) honored 114 retirees for their loyalty and dedicated service to the University of the 2015 Parangal sa mga Retirado at 2014 Gawad Paglilingkod. \nUPD fetes international scholars, diplomats by Kevin Brandon E. Saure, image by Jefferson Villacruz\n\"The UP System is moving towards greater internationalization.\" UP Diliman (UPD) Chancellor Michael L. Tan put in sharp focus the international reception\'s theme of \"Building bridges across the globe.\"\n3 new deans for UPD; affirmations at home unit a first by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThree new deans were appointed by the Board of Regents (BOR) at separate meetings between April and May. Dr. Orville Jose C. Solon for the School of Economics (SE), Dr. Joefe B. Santarita for the Asian Center (AC) and Dr. Amihan Bonifacio-Ramolete for the College of Arts and Letters (CAL).\n\"Lual\" off to ICF in Wales by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nLual, a fiery, glowing sculptural kiln created by College of Fine Arts (CFA) professor and ceramicist Rita B. Gudiño, will represent the Philippines at the International Ceramics Festival (ICF) to be held in Aberystwyth, Wales, United Kingdom in July 2015. \nPag-uugat, Pag-uugnay, Pagyabong mga Katanungan ng Payabong na Iskolar ng Bayan \nMensahe ng Kinatawan ng mga Nagsipagtapos ni Ma. Patricia Reyes Riego de Dios, BS Psychology, 2015\nThe UP Way \nWelcome Remarks by Dr. Michael L. Tan\nPresident\'s Message to the Graduates of UP Diliman\nMensahe sa mga Magsisipagtapos ni Br. Armin A. Luistro\nNIMBB student wins top prize in int\'l. genomics competition by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nLiezel U. Tamon, a senior BS Molecular Biology and Biotechnology student, was awarded the prestigious 2015 Sanger Institute Prize Competition in May.\nBAA Batch 2004 pays it forward\nThe UP Diliman (UPD) Business Administration and Accountancy (BAA) Alumni Batch 2004 is providing two scholarship grants for academically-deserving but financially-challenged BAA students of the Cesar E.A. Virata School of Business. \nE-trikes on trial operation at UPD by Albino C. Gamba Jr., images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nTen electric tricycles are now providing transportation services around the campus on a two-month pilot test as part of a memorandum of agreement (MOA) between UP Diliman (UPD) and BEMAC Electric Transportation Philippines Incorprated (BEMAC).\nYes, sunflowers can bloom in the rain by Benito V. Sanvictores., image by Jefferson Villacruz, with report by Albino C. Gamba, Jr.\nCertified seed. This is the secret behind the sunflowers at UPD\'s recent graduation. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1005, 'E2-1005AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXI, Number 4 (3 copies)', '', '', 'July-August 2015', 'Pep Rally ushers in UAAP 78\nUP Diliman sends off its athletes in style\nThe Maroon and Lady Jins of the UP Taekwondo Team\nby Anna Regidor, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nIt was double the excitement on Aug. 28 as the UP community cheered its varsity teams at the Pep Rally 2015 and celebrated the formal launch of the official UP Fighting Maroons logo.\nUPD artists named Gawad CCP by Haidee C. Pineda\nFour UP Diliman (UPD) artists are among the 13 Gawad CCP para sa Sining. \nUPD has 5 new professors emeriti by Albino C. Gamba Jr., images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nThe UP Board of Regents (BOR), at its 1309th meeting on Jul. 22, approved the appointment of five UP Diliman (UPD) faculty members as professors emeriti. \n3 UPD faculty members are Outstanding Young Scientists by Albino C. Gamba JR., image by Leonardo A. Reyes \nThree UPD faculty members were named 2015 Outstanding Young Scientists (OYS) by the National Academy of Science and Technology (NAST) at the Manila Hotel on July 9. The ceremonies coincided with the 37th NAST Annual Scientific Meeting. \n27 faculty members are UP Scientists by Albino C. Gamba Jr., image by Jefferson Villacruz\nThe University of the Philippines (UP) recognized the hard work and exceptional research productivity of its faculty members by appointing 27 of them as UP Scientists of various ranks under the Scientific Productivity System (SPS) in ceremonies at the Ang Bahay ng Alumni on Aug 28. \nUPD preps for September GE confab by Mariamme D. Jadioc\nIn preparation for the UP Diliman (UPD) General Education (GE) conference on Sept. 28 and 29, the UPD Office of the Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs (OVCAA) held a pre-conference symposium on GE in August where faculty members discussed inputs and recommendations from colleges/units. \nUPD preps for September GE confab by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nIn preparation for the UP Diliman (UPD) General Education (GE) conference on Sept. 28 and 29, the UPD Office of the Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs (OVCAA) held a pre-conference symposium on GE in August where faculty members discussed inputs and recommendations from colleges/units. \nRaised fist is UP Fighting Maroons logo by Haidee C. Pineda, images courtesy of Dan Matutina\nA raised fist, symbolizing the University of the Philippines (UP) community\'s spirit of solidarity, is now the official logo of the UP Fighting Maroons.\nUP Filipiniana Dance Group shines in Koronadal festival by Kevin Brandon E. Saure\nAcclaim and a standing ovation greeted the UP Filipiniana Dance Group (UPFDG) at Koronadal, South Cotabato, when it brought its repertoire of Philippine folk dances to the Pyesta Kolon Datal 2015, from Aug. 9 to 18.\nBike sharing on campus by Anna Kristine E. Regidor\nGetting around the 493-hectare UP Diliman (UPD) campus is a daily challenge for many students, who often travel from one building to another as they go through their classes. One student group is attempting to make things better by creating a free bike-sharing system on campus. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1006, 'E2-1006AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXI, Number 5 (2 copies)', '', '', 'September-October 2015', 'UP Lady Shuttlers bag UAAP Season 78 title\nUP Women\'s Badminton Team with (center) team manager Pacito Co and (3rd from right) head coach Tosi Alcasid and coach Melvin Alcala. \nMga bilanggong politikal ginunita ni Haidee C. Pineda, mga kuha ni Leonardo A. Reyes\nGinunita ng mga alagad ng sining ang mga bilanggong politikal sa isang panayam na inorganisa ng Sentro ng Wikang Filipino (SWF) na pinamagatang \"Talasalitaan : Saysay ng Sining (Talakayan kasama ang mga Alagad ng Sining)\" na ginanap noong Okt. 9 sa Pulungang Claro M. Recto. \nOcon is Green Talents awardee by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nDr. Joey D. Ocon of the Department of Chemical Engineering is one of the recipients of the 2015 Green Talents Award from the German Federal Ministry of Education and Research (BMBF).\nA hidden gem : UPD Geology Museum by Albino C. Gamba Jr., image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nA room located at the ground floor, left of the main entrance of the UP National Institute of Geological Science (NIGS), houses a hidden gem for geology/geosciences enthusiasts - the NIGS-UP Geology Alumni Association or NIGS-UPGAA Geology Museum. \nAnthropology\'s big role in medical science by Mariamme D. Jadloc, image by Jefferson Villacruz\nAnthropology plays a big role in the medical sciences, said by Maria Eufemia C. Yap, a medical doctor and an official at the Ateneo School of Medicine and Public Health, at a roundtable discussion (RTD) at the Pulungang Claro M. Recto at Bulwagang Rizal on Oct. 2. \nConfucious Institute opens at UP by Anna Regidor, image by Jefferson Villacruz\nThere is a new bridge between the country and China.\nUAAP Season 78 begins\nBy Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\n\"Arkipelago,\" a story on the formation of the Philippine archipelago and the origins of the University Athletic Association of the Philippines (UAAP), opened UAAP Season 78 at the Araneta Coliseum on Sept. 5. \nUAAP Season 78 : Fighting Maroons snag 5 podium finishes by Kevin Brandon E. Saure with reports from Miguel Javier D. Palaña, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nWith the first semester games drawing to a close, the UP Fighting Maroons have successfully garnered one championship, two second place and two third place finishes as of Oct. 31. \nExpanded incentives for cultural performing groups; student artists by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nThe UP Board of Regents (BOR) approved on Oct. 29 the Incentive Program for Cultural Performing Groups and Student Artists of UP Diliman (UPD)\nFighting Maroons dominates UniGames Football by Kevin Brandon E. Saure\nThe UP Fighting Maroons Men\'s Football Team (UPMFT) snagged the championship crown in the 20th UniGames held in Bacolod City, Oct 24-30.\nUP Bike Share wins APEC online popularity award by Anna Regidor\nUP Bike Share, a bike-sharing service founded and run by UP Diliman students, won an online popularity award in a 2-day pitching competition held in Taiwan under the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC)\nMolave fitness center to rise by Haidee C. Pineda, image by Leonardo A. Reyes \nA health and fitness center (HFC) for use of dormers and the UP Diliman (UPD) community will be constructed at the Molave Residence Hall.\nManilakbayan 2015 sa Diliman \nTeksto at kuha ni Benito V. Sanvictores, Jr. \nKinupkop ng UP Diliman (UPD) ang halos 700 Lumad sa loob ng isang linggo bilang pakikiisa sa pagdiriwang ng National Indigenous People\'s Month o Buwan ng mga Katutubong Pilipino.', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1007, 'E2-1007AC', '29', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXII, Number 1 ', '', '', 'January-February 2016', 'Song, dance and laughter cap UPD month : Bodabil begins and ends Panahon ng Lualhati by Anna Regidor, Images by Jefferson Villacruz\nWith a star-studded bodabil-themed show on February 26 at the UP Theater, UP Diliman Month 2016 ended how it began. Entitled \"Seremonya ng Pagwawakas : Panahon ng Luwalhati,\" the program featured performances from UPD students, faculty and alumni. \nNew UPD Professors Emeriti appointed by Albino C. Gamba Jr. Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe UP Board of Regents (BOR), at its 1314th meeting on Jan. 29, appointed three UP Diliman (UPD) College of Science (CS) faculty members as professors emeriti. \nAlmoro is \"Applied Optics Journal\" topical editor by Albino C. Gamba Jr. Image by Dr. Percival F. Almoro\nThe Board of Editors of the Optical Society of America (OSA) appointed Dr. Percival F. Almoro of the National Institute of Physics (NIP) as Topical Editor for its Applied Optics Journal from 2016 to 2018.\n36 UPD students off to 7 countries by Noelle Camilla R. Rivera \nThirty-six students from various colleges will cross-register in UP and UP Diliman\'s international partner institutions in the second semester of Academic Year (AY) 2015-2016. Student exchange stints range from one to two semesters. \n23 new foreign students enroll at UPD by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nTwenty-three students from partner universities in the Asia-Pacific, Europe and the United States are enrolled as exchange or visiting students at UP Diliman (UPD) in the second semester of AY 2015-2016.\nUPD wins eng\'g tilt in Indonesia by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nFour graduating students of the Department of Industrial Engineering and Operations Research (DIEOR) won the first prize in the 7th Industrial Engineering Competition (IECOM) held in Bandung, Indonesia from Jan. 9 to 17. \nCS launches Admin bldg by Albino C. Gamba Jr. Image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe National Science Complex (NSC) project is finally complete. In simple ceremonies, the College of Science (CS) Administration Building, the concluding final structure of the NSC, was inaugurated on Feb. 15. \nParasitology expert at IESM by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nUPD, through the Institute of Environmental Science and Meteorology (IESM), College of Science, welcomed visiting professor Dr. Anindo Choudhury of St. Norbert College (SNC), USA.\nManuel Conde : defining a cinema for the Filipino by Haidee C. Pineda, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nIt was fate that brought Manuel Conde, one of the seven National Artists for Film, to filmmaking. When he missed the boat that would have taken him to Java, Indonesia to work as a junior geologist, he was invited by Carlos Vander Tolosa of LVN Pictures, Inc. (LVN) to be an assistant director. \nLamberto Avellana : creativity amidst commercialism by Albino C. Gamba Jr. Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nTrapped and shut in by the commercialism of the film industry, Lamberto V. Avellana asserted his patriotic sensibilities through some significant or meaningful films he made. \nUPD Month 2016 pays tribute to 4 National Artists by Anna Regidor, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nUP Diliman Month 2016 opened with great fanfare on Feb. 1, 6 p.m. at the University Amphitheater with a ceremony inspired by a Filipino theatre tradition, the Bodabil. \nGay theme in Montano\'s unpublished novel by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\n\"The Lion and the Faun,\" the unpublished novel of National Artist for Theater Severino M. Montano (1915-1980), is the first novel in the country with homosexual identity or consciousness, said Dr. J. Neil Garcia in his public lecture on Feb. 16. \nStamp, lecture and performances celebrate NVM Gonzalez by Chi A. Ibay, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nFour events commemorated Nestor Vicente Madali (NVM) Gonzalez, befitting his stature as National Arist for Literature : a lecture on his contributions to literature, the launch of a commemorative stamp and a dramatic interpretation of two of his works, \"The Bread of Salt\" and \"A Wanderer in the Night of the World.\"\nA \"dancing\" wanderer in the night of the world by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., Images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nIntimate moments, flamboyant steps, synchronized choreography and sign language highlighted the dance interpretation of NVM Gonzalez\'s \"A Wanderer in the Night of the World\" and four other poems. \nLiterature as puppet play by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nCombining traditional techniques with new technologies, Teatrong Mulat ng Pilipinas (MULAT Theater) staged a puppet show to bring to life \"The Bread of Salt,\" a short story by Prof. NVM Gonzalez, National Artist for Literature. \nGender-sensitive UP education : Solusyon sa opresyon ni Kevin Brandon Saure, mga kuha ng UP Diliman Gender Office\nAng pagtataguyod ng isang kampus na ligtas at malaya sa karahasang nakabatay sa kasarian ang dahilan ng muling pagtipun-tipon ng mga estudyante, kawani, fakulti at miyembro ng komunidad ng UP Diliman (UPD) para sa taunang One Billion Rising (OBR) 2016 na ginanap noong Peb. 12. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1008, 'E2-1008AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXII, Number 3 (5 copies)', '', '', 'May-June 2016', 'Blazing in glory : UPD Class 2016 \nUP Diliman has 1,291 Latin honors by Haidee C. Pineda, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nFolding fans, portable electric fans, umbrellas and shades became staple paraphernalia at UP Diliman\'s (UPD) 105th General Commencement Exercises as good weather, sunshine and sweltering heat bid the Class of 2016 farewell on Jun. 26. \nOmbudsman says give people hope by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images by Jefferson Villacruz\nOmbudsman Conchita Carpio Morales called on the graduates of the UP College of Law (CL) to give hope to people \"when all hope is lost\" and not turn the law into an instrument of oppression at the latter\'s recognition rites on Jun. 27 at the UP Theater. \nUP law grad tops Bar\nRachel Angeli B. Miranda, who is also a \"Philippine Daily Inquirer\" scholar, topped the bar exam with a rating of 87.40 percent. \nUPD pays tribute to \"frontliners\" by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nUP Diliman (UPD) honored 124 retirees comprising 41 faculty members, 15 Research, Extension and Professional Staff (REPS) and 68 administrative personnel at the 2016 Parangal sa mga Retirado at 2015 Gawad Paglilingkod, May 19 at the GT-Toyota Asian Center Auditorium. \nFC remembered; Parangal opens by Anna Regidor, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nMay 16 was a night of remembrance and beginnings at the Faculty Center (FC) as UP Diliman held the \"Seremonya ng Pag-alaala at Parangal sa Lingkod Komunidad\" to open Linggo ng Parangal 2016. \n13 pinarangalan sa 2016 Gawad Tsanselor ni Chi A. Ibay, kuha ni Leonardo A. Reyes\nLabintatlong miyembro ng akademikong komunidad ang binigyan ng Gawad Tsanselor, ang pinakamataas ng pagkilala ng UP Diliman para sa kahusayan sa pagtuturo, pananaliksik, pag-aaral at paglilingkod, sa palatuntunang ginanap sa Institute of Biology Auditorium noong Mayo 20. \nPutting premium on extension programs by Bino C. Gamba Jr., images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe Geography Field School (GFS) program of the Department of Geography, College of Social Sciences and Philosophy, and the KaSaMa Teachers Online Community of the National Institute for Science and Mathematics Education Development (NISMED) were the awardees of the first Parangal Para sa Programang Pang-Ekstensiyon. \nUPD lauds student achievers by Haidee C. Pineda, photos by Leonardo A. Reyes\nUP Diliman (UPD) honored 4,599 University Scholars in the undergraduate and graduate levels and students who distinguished themselves in various fields at the Parangal sa Mag-aaral 2016 at the University Theater on May 18. \nUPD graduates top Envtl Planning exams \nUP Diliman (UPD) graduate Kim Robert C. de Leon notched the top spot in the June 2016 Environmental Planning Licensure Examination where 542 out of 1,010 examinees passed. \nA commitment to nation building by Alfredo E. Pascual, President, University of the Philippines \nGood morning! With the sunflowers still abloom and the rain on hold until we finish the commencement exercises, I can say that the morning has broken, together with our hopes and gladness. Congratulations to the UP Diliman Class of 2016!\nDiwata ang Oble, Me and You \nAlexander Atrio Lim Lopez, BA Philosophy, Class Representative, UP Diliman 2016\nTo the Commencement speaker President Alfredo E. Pascual, chair of the Board of Regents Honorable Patricia B. Licuanan, members of the Board of Regents, Chancellor Michael Lim Tan, university administration officials, officials of constituent universities, deans and directors, faculty, fellow graduates, parents, and friends, good morning. \nSumma Cum Laude 2016\nMessage to the 2016 Graduating Class\nMichael Lim Tan, Chancellor, UP Diliman\nMga \"stars of the day\" : ang mga magsisipagtapos. The women and men behind today\'s stars : mga magulang, mga lolo\'t lola, tito\'t tita, kuya, ate, bunso at sa mga graduate student, mga asawa\'t anak. \nEnticing investors to RP by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nLowering of corporate income tax from the current rate of 30 percent to 25 percent can further promote domestic and foreign investments in the Philippines, said UP School of Economics (UPSE) professor Dr. Stella Luz A. Quimbo.\nCHE upgrades facilities by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nThe UP College of Home Economics (CHE) inaugurated the newly renovated CHE Gusali 2 Building and held the groundbreaking ceremonies of the CHE Complex Phase 1 on Jun. 9 at the CHE grounds. \n4 athletes of the year at UAAP 78 closing by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nThe University Athletic Association of the Philippines (UAAP) gave the Athlete of the Year to not one, but four athletes, at the awarding and closing ceremony of Season 78, making it a first in the history of the athletic association. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1009, 'E2-1009AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXII, Number 4 (3 copies)', '', '', 'July-August 2016', 'Gauging the risk on heritage sites \nTool to measure the vulnerability created by Anna Regidor, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe facade of the Church of San Pedro Apostol in Loboc, Bohol collapsed after the earthquake in 2013. \nIn October 2013, a magnitude 7.2 earthquake struck Bohol, killing 28 people and destroying some of the country\'s oldest and most iconic churches, including the Church of San Pedro Apostol in Bohol and the Basilica Minore del Santo Niño in Cebu.\nNAST honors 5 UPD faculty members by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nThe National Academy of Science and Technology (NAST) Philippines recognized five UPD professors for their outstanding contributions to science and technology in the country.\nUPD HASPAG launched by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nSeven performing arts groups were conferred the honorific title of \"Official Student Performing Arts Groups of UP Diliman (UPD)\" as 49 students were awarded scholarships at the launch of UPD HASPAG (UP Diliman Honorific Award for Student Performing Arts Group) and the revitalization of the UPD Performing Arts Scholarship Program (PASP), Aug. 26 at the Ang Bahay ng Alumni. \nMaking policy decisions on the Philippine scientific enterprise system by Maureen Anne Araneta, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nPouring outlay into research and development (R&D) should be a sound investment for economic growth. After all, scientific knowledge, when discovered and applied successfully, boosts labor productivity, creates wealth and enhances quality of life. The Philippines followed this premise by increasing budget allocation in the Department of Science and Technology (DOST) by 115.11 percent from 2009 to 2014. But why is the Philippines still dismally behind Singapore, Brunei Darussalam, Malaysia, Thailand and Indonesia in terms of Gross Domestic Product (GDP) per capita?\nMammals of Luzon book launched by Albino C. Gamba\nThe UP Institute of Biology (UPIB) in partnership with the Diliman Science Research Foundation and the Philippines Tropical Forest Conservation Foundation launched the book \"Mammals of Luzon Island : A Biogeographic Perspective in Evolution, Ecology and Conservation\" on Aug. 10 at the UPIB Auditorium. \nUPD researchers awarded as world-class by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nSix researchers from UP Diliman were among the 12 Filipinos honored as world-class by The Philippines Promising Star Awards 2016 of Thomson Reuters on Jul. 26.\n2 faculty receive DOST-NSTW awards by Albino C. Gamba Jr., image by Jefferson Villacruz\nDr. Gisela P. Concepcion of the College of Science (CS) and Dr. Alonzo A. Gabriel of the College of Home Economics (CHE) were among this year\'s recipients of the Department of Science and Technology- National Science and Technology Week (DOST-NSTW) Awards on Jul. 25 at the DOST compound. \nLatest UPD journals out\nThe latest issues of UP Diliman\'s (UPD) three referred journals \"Humanities Diliman\" (Vol. 13 No. 2), \"Science Diliman\" (Vol. 28 No. 1) and \"Social Science Diliman\" (Vol. 12 No. 1) are now online.\nWazing to the top by Anna Regidor\nThey say necessity is the mother of invention. In the case of popular global positioning system (GPS)-based navigation app Waze, frustration and a gift were the seeds that drove its creators to find a better way to navigate the busy streets of Tel Aviv, Israel. \nGitara ni Juan : making quality guitars for Pinoys by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nA team of faculty members, engineers and musicians from UP Diliman combined art, engineering and science to create a quality classical guitar for Juan Dela Cruz and which may hopefully revive the declining industry of guitar-making in the Philippines. \nRadio broadcaster wins Gawad Plaridel 2016 by Haidee C. Pineda, image by Leonardo A. Reyes \nFrancisca \"Babes\" Custodio, a veteran radio practitioner and DYVL\'s station manager from Tacloban City, graced the UP Film Institute\'s red carpet on Aug. 24 to receive the prestigious Gawad Plaridel 2016 award. \nConstantino remembered by Anna Regidor\nThe Department of Linguistics (DL) of the UP Diliman (UPD) College of Social Sciences and Philosophy celebrated the life and work of Ernesto Constantino, avid folklorist and a pioneering figure in Philippine linguistics last Aug. 25 with \"Paglingon,\" a lecture series held at the Bulwagan ng Dangal.\nPrepping for the changing times by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., image by Leonardo A. Reyes \nIn celebration of its 100th year of business education in the Philippines, the Cesar E.A. Virata School of Buisness (VSB), in cooperation with the ASEAN University Network for Business and Economics (AUN-BE), hosted a conference to discuss the impacts and prospects of the ASEAN integration in the region\'s business and economic community. \nKorean studies scholars at PKSS 2016\nFourteen participants of the Philippine Korean Studies Symposium (PKSS) 2016 met and were mentored by four renowned scholars of Korean studies last Jul 20 to 22 at Microtel, UP-Ayala Technohub. \nPaglibing kay Marcos binatikos\nTeksto at kuha ni Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \n\"Hindi bayani si Marcos.\"\nStudent mobility in UPD by Kevin Brandon E. Saure\nSixty UPD students are set to enroll as exchange students in partner universities in Asia and Europe for the first semester of academic year (AY) 2016-2017.\nPEP rally 2016', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1010, 'E2-1010AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXII, Number 5 (3 copies)', '', '', 'September-October 2016', 'Lakbayanis find temporary home at UPD\nLakbayan 2016 : Kampuhan sa Diliman by Anna Regidor, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nLakbayanis and the UP community dance together in front of Palma Hall on Oct. 12. \nCao is Metrobank awardee by Albino C. Gamba Jr., image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nUP Diliman Institute of Biology (IB) director Dr. Ernelea P. Cao is this year\'s recipient of the Metrobank Foundation Outstanding Teacher Award\n9 new professors emeriti are from UPD by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images from the School of Economics\nThe University of the Philippines (UP) has 13 new professors emeriti and nine are from UP Diliman (UPD). All noted experts in their fields, among them is a department secretary appointed to the Duterte administration, a former UP vice president and two former deans. \nLinguistics major wins speech tilt by UP Department of Linguistics\nMaria Concepcion Loren R. Chua, a BA Linguistics student of the College of Social Sciences and Philosophy (CSSP) bested 17 other competitors to win the Korean Ministry of Education Award at the 21st World Korean Speech Contest Jul. 30 in Bangkok, Thailand.\nUPD is top school in Psychometrician board\nUP Diliman is the top performing school in the Psychometrician Licensure Examinations held Sept. 12-14 with a 98.39-percent passing rate, according to the Professional Regulation Commission (PRC).\nUPD tops CPA exam\nThe University of the Philippines Diliman (UPD) was the top performing school in the October 2016 Board Licensure Examination for Certified Public Accountants (BLECPA), with all its 69 examinees passing. \n3-peat for UP Lady Shuttlers \nText and images by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nThree years. Same opponent. Same outcome. \nUP Lady Tankers recapture UAAP crown by Haidee C. Pineda, image by Michael Dwight Tan\nThe UP Women\'s Swimming Team (UP Lady Tankers) recaptured the University Athletic Association of the Philippines (UAAP) Championship title this season, beating the defending champion Ateneo de Manila University (ADMU) Lady Eagles in the finals of the competition held Oct. 24 at the Rizal Memorial Swimming Pool. \nCM celebrates Filipino music and artists \nText and images by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nShowcasing the rich musical heritage of the Philippines, the world and the institution itself, the UP College of Music (CMu) opened its year-long 100th anniversary celebration with a centennial concert and centennial awarding ceremonies Sept. 4 at the Abelardo Hall Auditorium. \nEnd senseless killings, now : Kalembang Kontra Bang! Bang! \nText and image by Kevin Brandon E. Saure\nWith the steady rise of death toll resulting from the Philippine government\'s war on drugs, the UP Center for Women\'s and Gender Studies (UPCWGS), together with LGBT organization Bahaghari, staged \"Kalembang Kontra Bang! Bang!\" (Kalembang) on Sept. 23 at the Carillon Plaza. \nBS Food Tech earns international accreditation by UP Department of Food Science and Nutrition\nThe International Union of Food Science and Technology (IUFoST) recently recognized the Bachelor of Science in Food Technology (BSFT) program of the UP Diliman College of Home Economics for achieving the IUFoST international standards for Food Science Course Curricula. \nMga Susing Salita : Pagbubuo ng diskurso sa konseptong Filipino ni Haidee C. Pineda, mga kuha ni Leonardo A. Reyes\nBakit ang mga PInoy mahilig sa mga salitang may \'paki-\'? May pagkakaiba ba ang salitang Moro at Lumad? Ano ang unang pumapasok sa isip kapag sinabihan kang mukhang Agta?\nCelebrating life at UP Diliman by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nLife at UP Diliman can sometimes be overwhelming for its constituents. \nUPD partners with LCP by Chi A. Ibay, image by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nThe University of the Philippines Diliman, through the Confucius Institute (UPD-CI), entered into a Memorandum of Understanding with the League of Cities of the Philippines (LCP) in \"teaching Chinese language and culture to schools\" of LCP member cities on Oct. 4 at the Office of the Chancellor. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1011, 'E2-1011AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXII, Number 6 (4 copies)', '', '', 'November-December 2016', 'UPD Lantern Parade 2016 : harmonious diversity \nEng\'g grabs top spot by Haidee C. Pineda, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz \nFirst prize winner : Bakunawa by the College of Engineering \nBOR approves 2 new OICA programs by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nThe UP Board of Regents (BOR) approved two new programs \"to enhance the artistic engagements\" of UP Diliman (UPD) students at its 1323rd meeting on Dec. 16. \nUP Law Dean to succeed PAEP as President\nReprinted Nov 15, 2016 at http://www.up.edu.ph/\nThe Office of the Secretary of the University and of the Board of Regents announced Nov. 15 the selection of University of the Philippines College of Law Dean Danilo Lardizabal Concepcion as the new President of the University of the Philippines.\nBy George! Asuncion is 8th SOLAIR dean by Mariamme D. Jadloc, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nDr. Ronahlee A. Asuncion was formally installed as the eighth dean of the School of Labor and Industrial Relations (SOLAIR) at affirmation rites on Dec. 16 at the School\'s Isabelo delos Reyes Auditorium. \nDe Leon affirmed as Engineering Dean by Anna Kristine E. Regidor, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nNew College of Engineering (COE) dean Rizalinda L. de Leon likened the next three years of her term to an artist weaving a fabric at her affirmation ceremony on Nov. 15 at the Engineering Theater.\nUnified action for disaster prevention by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., image by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nAfter typhoon Yolanda in 2009, the earthquake in Haiti in 2010 and the earthquake and tsunami in Japan in 2011, people became more conscious of the need for disaster risk reduction and management (DRRM). Recognizing how destructive natural phenomena can be, 10 academic units at UP Diliman (UPD) organized the conference \"Disaster and Disciplines\" on Nov. 18 at the GT-Toyota Asian Center Auditorium. \nLights and music open Christmas at Diliman by Anna Kristine E. Regidor, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nLights and music filled the air in the night of Dec. 2 as UP Diliman (UPD) opened the Christmas celebrations in \"Pag-iilaw : Hagkan ang Gabi,\" by switching on the decorative lights on campus at Quezon Hall with performances relfecting the University\'s sentiments to the current political climate. \nWhat\'s new with Diwata by Anna Kristine E. Regidor\nFollowing the historic launch of Diwata 1, the first Filipino-made microsatellite, plans are now in place to launch a second microsatellite in the first half of 2018, tentatively named Diwata 2. \nTeam UP-Philippines shines at international competition by Haidee C. Pineda, image by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nThe University of the Philippines Vaisty Pep Squad (UP Pep) teamed up with the UP Filipiniana Dance Group and bagged six medals at the Asian Cheerleading and Dancesport Champsionships (ACDC) in Jakarta, Indonesia from Nov. 26 to 27. \nEPDP partners with DOE on Philippine energy programs by Jean Lau Wang, Energy Policy and Development Program \nThe Energy Policy and Development Program (EPDP) of the School of Economics UPecon Foundation conducted a policy briefing for the Department of Energy (DOE) on Dec, 19 at the UP Bonifacio Global City Campus. \nGabriel receives JIRCAS award by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nNoted scientist and Food Science and Nutrition professor Dr. Alonzo A. Gabriel received another accolade, this time fromt he Japan International Research Center for Agricultural Sciences (JIRCAS) of the Japan Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1012, 'E2-1012AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXIII, Number 1 (5 copies)', '', '', 'January to February 2017', 'UP Diliman Month 2017 : A celebration of folklore as art and study by Anna Regidor, images by Leonardo A. Reyes \nRamon Magsaysay Awardee Ligaya Fernando-Amilbangsa with the AlunAlun Dance Circle at the closing ceremonies\nWith 7,641 islands and over 100 ethnolinguistics groups, the wealth of the Philippines\' folklore was at the heart of UP Diliman (UPD) Month 2017, with activities in both the visual and performing arts as well as a full academic conference devoted to the subject in the whole of February.  \nNIP prof\'s paper 1 of best at EPL by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nA research paper that went against the present consensus regarding the decoherence phenomenon in quantum mechanics has been selected as one of the best papers of 2016 and is part of the booklet Highlights of 2016 published by the Euro Physicsl Letters (EPL). \nUPD wins Shell Eco-marathon \nText and image by Anna Regidor\n\"Siglo,\" the electric vehicle created by Team Dagisik University of the Philippines, won 1st Prize in the Shell Eco-marathon Philippines 2017, held Feb. 4 and 5 at the Clark International Speedway in Pampanga. \nAIT : soaring to greater heights by Benito V. Sanvictores, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nDr. Edieser D. Dela Santa was formally affirmed as the seventh dean of the UP Diliman Asian Institute of Tourism (AIT) on Feb. 8 at the Isabelo delos Reyes Auditorium of the School of Labor and Industrial Relations (SOLAIR)\nEEEI inaugurates smart laboratory by Anna Regidor\nThe Electrical and Electronics Engineering Institute (EEEI) of the College of Engineering (CoE) inaugurated the UP-Samsung Instructional Laboratory on Jan. 30.\nK\'wentong bayan mahalaga sa kabataan ni Mariamme D. Jadloc, mga kuha ni Leonardo A. Reyes \nMahalaga ang k\'wentong bayan sa paghubog ng sangkamalayan ng kabataang Filipino. Ito ang paksang ipinunto ni Prop. Felipe P. de Leon Jr., dating Tagapangulo ng National Commission for Culture and Arts (NCCA) at kasalukuyang propesor ng Aralin sa Sining sa Kolehiyo ng Arte at Literatura ng UP Diliman (UPD), sa \"Sampaksaan sa K\'wentong Bayan,\" Peb 23 sa UP NISMED Auditorium.\nCassettes 100 : Maceda comes alive by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nFaculty, students, staff and other guests were enthralled by a hundred performers weaving through the audience in choreographed rhythmic steps, in an almost clockwork pattern, while holding MP3 players at the UP Vargas Museum. \nBai Bigkay is Gawad Tandang Sora awardee \nText and images by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr.\nBai Bibyaon Ligkayan Bigkay, a lumad (national minority) woman leader, received the 3rd Gawad Tandang Sora award from the UP Diliman (UPD) College of Social Work and Community Development (CSWCD) on Feb. 23 at the CSWCD Bulwagang Tandang Sora. \n5 for CSWCD 2017 Service Awards \nText and image by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nOne faculty member and four staff received the 2017 Service Awards from the UP Diliman (UPD) College of Social Work and Community Development (CSWCD) on Feb. 24 at the CSWCD Bulwagang Tandang Sora. \nSanSinukob\nPhilippine myths on the universe\'s origin by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Jefferson Villacruz\nUP Diliman\'s (UPD) celebration of the National Arts Month kicked off on Feb. 1 with the unveiling of Sansinukob, an installation art exhibit in three sties : at the UP Lagoon, UP Amphitheater and College of Mass Communication (CMC) Hill. \nPuppets and Shadows of love and war by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., images by Haidee C. Pineda\nUsing rod puppets, shadows, dance drama and music, Teatrong Mulat ng Pilipinas (Mulat) staged the immortal epic \"Ramayana\" on Feb. 18 and 19 at the Institute of Biology Auditorium at UP Diliman (UPD) in celebration of UPD Month 2017. \nFolk music takes center stage in Himigsikan 2017 by Kevin Brandon E. Saure, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nConcurrent with the theme \"Salaysayan : K\'wentong Bayan, Kaalamang Bayan\" of the UP Diliman Month 2017, two artists serenaded the UP community for the two-part Himigsikan 2017 held at the University Theater Canopy, 6 p.m. of Feb 10 and 24. \nStat prof wins SAS Philippines paper competition by Albino C. Gamba Jr. with reports from Jessa Lopez\nProf. Francisco N. delos Reyes\' research won the grand prize in the faculty division of the SAS paper competition held at the Annual SAS Philippines Academic Analytics Conference on Feb. 9 at the One Esplanade Events Place, Pasay City. \n\"Ang Unang Aswang\" adapted to full-length dance prod by Mariamme D. Jadloc \nThe UP Dance Company (UPDC) once again conquered the stage as it presented Rody Vera\'s \"Ang Unang Aswang\" on Feb 25 and 26 and Mar. 4 and 5 at the College of Architecture (CA) amphitheater. \nCoE grad is TOSP 2016 awardee \nArizza Ann S. Nocum, a UP College of Engineering (CoE) magna cum laude graduate, is one of the 2016 Ten Outstanding Students of the Philippines (TOSP).\nReuben Ramas Cañete, PhD : scholar, critic, artist (1966-2017)\nAbridged from the Asian Center original\nThe students, staff and faculty of the Asian Center, University of the Philippines Diliman, are deeply saddened by the passing of their teacher, colleague, and mentor, Reuben Ramas Cañete, Ph.D., last 17 February 2017. He was 50. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1013, 'E2-1013AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXIII, Number 2 ', '', '', 'March-April 2017', '14 tumanggap ng Gawad Tsanselor 2017 by Chi A. Ibay, mga kuha ni Leonardo A. Reyes\nGawad Tsanselor 2017 awardees with UP Diliman administration officials.\nLabing-tatlong kasapi ng Unibersidad ng Pilipinas Diliman (UPD) at isang pook sa kampus ang nagtamo ng Gawad Tsanselor 2017, na ipinagkaloob sa palatuntunang ginanap sa Awditoryum ng Linangan ng Biyolohiya, ika 6- ng gabi noong Abril 27. \n63 students are performing arts scholars by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., images by Jefferson Villacruz\nSixty-three UP Diliman (UPD) students were conferred the honorific title UP Performing Arts Scholar under the Performing Arts Scholarship Program (PASP) and received their certificates of scholarship for the second semester of Academic Year (AY) 2016-2017 on Apr. 25 at the Balay Kalinaw. \nUP paper in top-read articles by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \n\"Scientific Reports,\" an online open access scientific mega journal published by the Nature Publishing Group, named the paper of UP Diliman scientists which showed that light could be slowed down as one of its 100 most-read articles in 2016.\nDiwata launch : 1 year later by Anna Regidor, images by the PHL-Microsat Program\nThe Philippine Microsat Program (PHL-Microsat) celebrated the first anniversary of Diwata-1s launch into space last Apr. 27 with a showcase of space technologies, including a live demonstration of the Philippine Earth Data Resource Observation (PEDRO) facility housed at the DOST-Advanced Science and Technology Institute (ASTI).\nPolicy changes benefit more retirees and service awardees by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nPolicy changes to enhance benefits for UP Diliman (UPD) retirees and service awardees were implemented in this year\'s Parangal sa Retirado at Gawad Paglilingkod held Apr. 26 at the GT Toyota Auditorium. \nBack to blue : ALYANSA dominates USC elections by Haidee C. Pineda\nBenjie Allen D. Aquino, Alyansa ng mga Mag-aaral para sa Panlipunang Katwiran at Kaunlaran (ALYANSA) standard bearer, was elected chairperson of the UPD University Student Council (USC) defeating Student Alliance for the Advancement of Democratic Rights in UP (STAND UP) standard bearer Ben Galil R. Te in elections held Apr. 6. \nUPD celebrates foreign ties, academic cooperation by Kevin Brandon E. Saure, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nInstead of the usual closed-door, intimate fete, this year\'s Chancellor\'s International Reception was an open-to-the public engagement with the theme \"International Engagement : Harnessing Global Experiences.\"\nUPD honors the cream of the crop by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nUP Diliman\'s (UPD) best and the brightest - its University Scholars (US) in the undergraduate and graduate levels and those who distinguished themselves in various fields - were recognized at the Parangal sa Mag-aaral 2017 at the University Theater on Apri. 27. \nTwo programs recognized for extension services by Albino C. Gamba Jr., images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe extension program of two units of the College of Science (CS) were recognized at the Parangal Para sa Programang Pang-Ekstensiyon 2017, held on Apr. 25 at the Malcolm Auditorium, College of Law. \nLeonardo Liongson, 68 by Anna Regidor\nRetired professor and hydraulic expert Ricardo Leonardo Q. Liongson of the UP College of Engineering (COE) passed away on Apr. 5, Wednesday after a 2-year battle with pancreatic cancer. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49');
INSERT INTO `records` (`id`, `accessionNo`, `boxNumber`, `title`, `placeOfPublication`, `publisher`, `dateOfPublication`, `descriptionContent`, `type`, `paper`, `abstract`, `keywords`, `filePath`, `fileName`, `accessLevel`, `status`, `dateEncoded`, `updatedAt`) VALUES
(1014, 'E2-1014AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXIII, Number 3 (3 copies)', '', '', 'May-June 2017', 'Serve with compassion : UPD class 2017 by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes, Jefferson Villacruz\nThe unique symbolism of the academic ritual-shifting of the sablay from right to left - during the 106th General Commencement Exercises at the University Amphitheater. \nUP Diliman\'s (UPD) eventful 106th General Commencement Exercises held on Jun. 25 at the University Amphitheater was the talk of the town with 36 summa cum laude (SCL) graduates, a stirring valedictory speech by a Maranao student and the conerment of an honorary degree on a cabinet secretary. \nCHE professors recognized by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nProf. Maria Patricia V. Azanza, PhD and Prof. Casiana Blanca Villarino, PhD, both faculty members of the College of Home Economics\' Department of Food Science and Nutrition (CHE-DFSN), received accolades from the Philippine government and from a non-profit international organization, respectively. \nUP confers honorary degree on Diokno by Chi A. Ibay, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe University of the Philippines Diliman (UPD) conferred an honorary Doctor of Laws degree on Department of Budget and Management (DBM) Secretary Benjamin E. Diokno at its 106th General Commencement Exercises held June 25 at the University Amphitheater.\nEmbracing aging : a study of Pinay migrants of NZ by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nA study on the views on aging of Filipina migrants to New Zealand found that some older women have more relaxed beauty standards and still consider themselves successful in their lives. \nSouth China Sea : harmony or hostility? by Benito V. Sanvictores, Jr. \nTwo Chinese scholars presented opposing views on China\'s territorial claims on the South China Sea (SCS) in a public lecture at the UP Asian Center.\nPagmamalasakit ng Isang Iskolar ng Bayan by Arman Ali Ghodsinia \nTo my fellow graduates and to our esteemed teachers, to our parents, family and dear friends, I would like to begin by greeting all of you with words of peace : \"Assalamu\'alaikom\" (or peace be with you).\nCommencement Address by Benjamin E. Diokno, PhD\nSecretary, Department of Budget and Management\nMessage to the Class of 2017 by Michael Lim Tan, Chancellor, UP Diliman\nAng ating panauhing pandangal Kalihim Benjamin Diokno; ang dating Pangulko ng UP Dr. Emmanuel Soriano, Pangulo Danilo L. Concepcion, mga opisyal ng administrasyon ng UP, mga kaguruan, mga magulang, lolo at lola, asawa\'t anak, kabarangay at nag-alay ng dugo at pawis at ang mga inalayan ng dugo at pawis, ang class of 2017, magandang umaga sa inyong lahat, maayong buntag sa atong tanan. Assalamo alaikum. \nGhodsinia : what makes a summa? by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., Image by Jefferson Villacruz\n\"I am grade conscious student, but I am the balanced type,\" Arman Ali Ghodsinia said. He was the class representative at the 106th General Commencement Exercises held June 25. Ghodsinia, a summa cum laude (SCL) graduate of Molecular Biology and Biotechnology (MBB), has a weighted average grade of 1.173.\n2 new OVCAA heads appointed by Chi A. Ibay, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nProf. Evangeline C. Amor, PhD and Prof. Ma. Theresa T. Payongayong, PhD, have been appointed to head the offices of the Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs and the University Registrar, respectively. \nNAST honors 3 UPD professors by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nThe National Academy of Science and Technology (NAST) Philippines recognized three UPD professors for their outstanding contributions in the advancement of science and technology in the country. \nNew housing rules for 2018 by Anne Regidor, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe UP Diliman (UPD) Housing Office will implement a new policy on Jan 1, 2018 requiring all retiring employees occupying UPD housing units to file a one-time request of extension before they can be allowed to stay. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1015, 'E2-1015AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXIII, Number 4 (5 copies)', '', '', 'July-August 2017', 'FWA 2017 : UPD welcomes freshies by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe freshmen for AY 2017-2018 at the Freshie Welcome Assembly held at the University Theater on Aug 7.\nThe Freshie Welcome Assembly (FWA) is a yearly tradition organized by the Office of the Vice Chancellor for Student Affairs (OVCSA) to familiarize freshmen with the administration officials and treat them to performances from UP Diliman\'s (UPD) homegrown talents.\nGabriel, 2017 Metrobank awardee by Albino C. Gamba Jr. \nNoted food scientist and College of Home Economics (CHE) professor Dr. Alonzo A. Gabriel is one of the 10 recipients of this year\'s Metrobank Foundation Outstanding Filipinos Award. \nRemembering Posadas by Albino C. Gamba Jr., images by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nUP Diliman (UPD) held a necrological service to honor its fifth chancellor, Dr. Roger D. Posadas, on Aug. 24 at the Loyola Memorial Chapel along Commonwealth Avenue, Quezon City. \nBetter linkages, better economies by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nTo succeed, there should be better integration among member states of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) Economic Community (AEC).\nAging in RP by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nOlder Filipinos are generally not materially well-off, not well-educated and about half consider themselves to be of average health, but have poor use of health services. \nAging in the Philippines: Findings from the 2007 Philippine Study on Aging by Grace T. Cruz, Josefina N. Natividad, Melissa L. Gonzales, Yasuhikoi Saito\n1 in 3 Pinays use traditional over modern contraceptives by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nA recent study on Filipino women who use contraceptives showed that in the past 10 years, one in every three relied more on traditional contraceptive methods of rhythm and withdrawal than modern methods. \nUPD brings green mining to the barrio by Anna Regidor \nThe Small-Scale Mining (SSM) Industry comprises up to 75 percent of the country\'s gold production, and from 2007-2008, contributed P32 billion to the Gross Domestic Product. \nJournalism vs. fake news by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\n\"Journalism\'s best weapon against lies is to be transparent, thorough and provocative.\"\nRoadworks to last until 2018 by Anna Regidor, image by Jefferson Villacruz\nMotorists and commuters in UP Diliman can expect more traffic on campus in the coming months as the rehabilitation and repair of pipelines and roads will continue well into 2018, especially in the residential areas. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1016, 'E2-1016AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XIII, Number 5 (4 copies)', '', '', 'September-October 2017', 'Concert caps CMu centennial by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nUP Dance Company\'s performance during the College of Music\'s Centennial closing concert. \nCapping its centennial anniversary celebration, the UP College of Music (CMu) staged a full house closing concert featuring its faculty and resident performing groups on Sept. 15 at the Abelardo Hall Auditorium.\nNew deans appointed by Haidee C. Pineda, Bino C. Gamba Jr., images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe UP Board of Regents approved the appointments of Prof. La Verne C. Dela Peña, PhD and Prof. Perry S. Ong, PhD as deans of the College of Music (CMu) and the College of Science (CS), respectively, at its 1331st meeting on Oct. 18. \nDe Ungria awarded 2017 Dangal ng Bayan by Prof. Joselito Florendo \nDr. Maria Corazon A. De Ungria, head of the DNA Analysis Laboratory of the UPD Natural Sciences Research Institute, received the Dangal ng Bayan (DnB) Award at the Outstanding Government Workers Awards Rites on Sept. 20 at the Malacañang Palace. \nScience kit for STEM students developed by Bino C. Gamba Jr. \nA low-cost and portable handheld device coupled with sensors has been developed by researchers from UP Diliman (UPD) and UP Los Baños (UPLB) to upgrade the Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics (STEM) strand of the K to 12 program of the Department of Education (DepEd).\nSocMed redefines news by Mariamme D. Jadloc, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe shift towards social media (SocMed) as the main platform for discussion and information has led to a redefinition of news. This was the premise of the lecture \"Social Media as Site of News and Political Discourse\" by Prof. Clarissa C. David, PhD, at the Pi Gamma Mu Inaugural National Conference on Oct. 13 at the NISMED auditorium. \nDigong vs. the Catholic Church by Anna Regidor, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nPresident Rodrigo Duterte is known for his colorful language and sometimes incendiary commentary, but is any of it truly harmful?\nSilencing the media and the \"truth\" by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., image by Raymund Creencia\n\"Journalists must advocate to end impunity.\" UP College of Mass Communication (CMC) Prof. Danilo A. Arao repeated the call of Joel Simon, Executive Director of the Committee to Protect Journalists (CPJ), in his lecture \"Making Sense of the Senseless\" at the CMC Research Brownbag Series on Aug. 30 at the CMC Auditorium. \nLakbayan 2017 in song by Anna Regidor, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nMembers of national minorities banded together for a night of music, culture and protest on Sept. 18 as the Office of the Chancellor presented \"Hugpungan 2017,\" a 2-part concert special held at the University Theater as part of \"Lakbayan 2017 : Kampuhan sa Diliman.\"\nMga artista-iskolar, pinarangalan ni Kevin Brandon E. Saure, mga kuha ni Leonardo A. Reyes\nPitumpu\'t limang mag-aaral ang ginawaran ng parangal ng Office for Initiatives in Culture and the Arts (OICA) sa ilalim ng UP Diliman (UPD) Performing Arts Scholarship Program (PASP) at UPD Visual Arts and Cultural Studies Scholarship Program (VACSSP), Okt. 9 sa The Forefront, University Theater.\nUPD Christmas program announced\nThe UP Diliman (UPD) Office of the Chancellor announaces the 2017 year-end program with the theme \"UP Diliman : Paaralan, Palaruan.\"\nHumanities Diliman\nVol. 14 No. 2 out\nThe July to December 2017 issue of \"Humanities Diliman\" (HD Vol. 14 No. 2) has a new editor-in-chief (EIC) and is now available online. \nLatest Social Science Diliman now online\nThree articles commonly derived from the larger idea of society and four book reviews are featured in the latest issue of \"Social Science Diliman\" (SSD/Vol. 13, No. 1) that is now available online. \nIndie at delubyo : mga susing salita \nTeksto at mga kuha ni Haidee C. Pineda\nDalawang eksperto mula sa magkaibang disiplina ang nagbahagi ng kanilang kaalaman tungkol sa mga salitang \"indie\" at \"delubyo\" sa seminar na \"Mga Susing Salita : Pambansang Seminar sa Pagbuo ng Diskurso sa Konseptong Filipino\" na inorganisa ng Sentro ng Wikang Filipino (SWF).\nPasyal 2017 : UP Diliman Art Trail now available \nText and image by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \n\"Pasyal\" : UP Diliman Art Trail (\"Pasyal 2017\"), a monograph and map tandem featuring historical buildings, public art and open spaces at UP Diliman (UPD), is now available at the Office for initiatives in Culture and the Arts (OICA).\nUPD celebrates life by Raymund Creencia, Trisa De Ocampo, Hanzvic Dellomas, Jo-ev Guevarra, images by Raymund Creencia\nFaculty, staff and students of UP Diliman (UPD) celebrated life in a series of activities held at the UP Sunken Garden, Academic Oval and Main Library, Sept. 27 in \"Celebrate Life @ UPD.\"\nPi Gamma Mu-UP holds 1st conference\nIn celebration of the Pi Gamma Mu Honor Society-Philippine Alpha Charter\'s 85th anniversary, the Society held its first national conference on Oct. 13 and 14 at the NISMED auditorium.', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1017, 'E2-1017AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XIII, Number 6 (2 copies)', '', '', 'November-December 2017', 'Lantern Parade 2017 : advocacies amid revelry by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes, Jefferson Villacruz and Haidee C. Pineda\nAs early as 4 p.m. on Dec. 15, students, faculty, staff, residents and spectators converged at the Oblation Plaza and around the Academic Oval to participate and/or witness the parade of big colorful floats ingeniously created by this year\'s participants. The parade officially started at 5 p.m.\nBooks of UPD faculty win NB awards by Haidee C. Pineda \nBooks published in 2016 by Prof. Jose Wendell P. Capili, PhD of the College of Arts and Letters (CAL) and Prof. Nick Deocampo of the College of Mass Communication (CMC), won in two categories of the 36th National Book Awards (NBA). \nICE bldg. inaugurated \nText and images by Anna Regidor\nThe UP College of Engineering Institute of Civil Engineering (COE-ICE) inaugurated its main building at the ICE complex on Nov. 18.\nAssembly of natural products scientists held by Bino C. Gamba Jr., image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe international summit 15th Asian Symposium on Medicinal Plants, Spices and Other Natural Products (ASOMPS), and the 22nd Natural Products Society of the Philippines (NPSP) Convention were jointly held from Dec. 6 to 8 at the Intel Center of Science Innovation Room of the UP Diliman (UPD) National Institute of Physics. \nFederalism in RP : reform than overhaul by Mariamme D. Jadloc, photos courtesy of Prof. Crisline Torres-Pilapil\nCAL profs win Aliw Awards by Haidee C. Pineda\nUP College of Arts and Lettesr (CAL) professors Pedro \"Edru\" R. Abraham Jr., Glecy C. Atienza, Banaue Miclat-Janssen and Dexter M. Santos won in various categories at the 2017 Aliw Awards on Dec. 19. \nUPD conducts IC design training by Anna Regidor, image by Diana Ruth Arcega\nFaculty members from the Electrical and Electronics Engineering Institute (EEEI), academics from higher education institutions and representatives from local semiconductor companies enhanced their skills and knowledge in integrated circuit (IC) design with the Taiwan Integrated Circuit Design Training.\nCAL profs win Aliw Awards by Haidee C. Pineda\nUP College of Arts and Letters (CAL) professors Pedro \"Edru\" R. Abraham Jr., Glecy C. Atienza, Banaue Miclat-Janssen and Dexter M. Santos won in various categories at the 2017 Aliw Awards on Dec. 19. \nEye-opening start for Christmas by Anna Regidor, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nUP Diliman opened the 2017 holiday celebrations on Nov. 24 with Pag-iilaw, the yearly ceremony where Christmas lights on campus are traditionally switched on. \nChristmas and the \"Messiah\" by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr., images by Jefferson Villacruz\nThe College of Music (CMu) once again celebrated the Yuletide season through the institution\'s much anticipated event, Handel\'s \"Messiah,\" on Dec. 7 and 8 at the CMu Abelardo Hall Auditorium. \nSandwich revs up Pag-iilaw by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nTwo words describe Sandwich\'s mini concert at Pag-iilaw 2017 : electrifyingly nostalgic, figuratively and literally. \nHomegrown talents at Session Avenue by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nRain before the show started did not dampen the mood of the performers, crew and spectators alike as \"Session Avenue\" focused the spotlight on homegrown UP Diliman talents last Dec. 1. \nBolstering digital humanities in RP by Kevin Brandon Saure and Shech Pacariem, images from the Philippine Performance Archive\nFaculty, staff, researchers and students from various UP constituent units (CUs) gathered for a 2-day digital humanities symposium, \"The Humanities and the Digital : Archiving and Pedagogy,\" Nov. 15 and 16 at the Microtel Technohub, Quezon City. \nMore roadworks by Anna Regidor, images from DPWH Metro Manila 3rd District Engineering Office\nThe Department of Public Works and Highways (DPWH) is rehabilitating several key roads leading to and near the Office of the University Registrar as part of a larger plan to connect the Engineering Complex to the main campus and improve the flow of traffic. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1018, 'E2-1018AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXIV, Number 1 (3 copies)', '', '', 'January-February 2018', 'The body demystified by Haidee C. Pineda\nGuests viewing \"(Com) modified Bodies\" exhibit at the Asian Center. \nFour events focusing on the body comprised of an exhibit, symposium, book launch and film showing were held at the UP Diliman (UPD) GT-Toyota Asian Center on Feb 13 as part of the 3-month celebration of the \"Kat(h)wan : UPD Festival of Culture and the Arts 2018\" (UPDFOCA)\nRemembering Billy by Haidee C. Pineda, images by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nThe UP Diliman (UPD) community mourned National Artist for Sculpture Esabelio Napoleon \"Billy\" Veloso Abueva who passed away on Feb. 16 at the National Kidney and Transplant Institute in Quezon City. He was 88. \nThe Asian body as a performer by Kevin Brandon E. Saure, images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nScholars, practitioners and enthusiasts of theatre and performance gathered for the International Federation for Theatre Research (IFTR) Transregional Conference 2018 themed \"Bodies in/and Asian Theatres\" at the GT-Toyota Auditorium and Hall of Wisdom at the Asian Center, Feb 20 to 23. \nA royalty-free license grant of the green mining technology by Bino C. Gamba, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nUP Diliman (UPD) formally granted the Department of Science and Technology-Cordillera Administrative Region (DOST-CAR) and the Benguet Foundation of Small Scale Miners, Inc. (BFSSMI) a royalty-free and non-commercial license of an environment-friendly technology developed by the Department of Mining, Metallurgical and Materials Engineering of the College of Engineering. \nClaudio affirmed as 12th CSWCD dean\nText and image by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nDr. Sylvia Estrada Claudio was affirmed as 12th dean of the College of Social Work and Community Development (CSWCD) by UP Diliman (UPD) Chancellor Michael L. Tan on Feb. 21 at the CSWCD grounds. \n1987 Constitution : revise or amend? \nText and images by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nIt would be better to amend than revise the 1987 Philippine Constitution because any wrong move will affect our future and bind us for a very long time. \nKat(h)awan tickles by Anna Regidor, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nIt is a good night when the spoken word meets dazzling dance numbers and a multi-awarded artist is given tribute by UP Diliman\'s (UPD) highest official. \nThe body demystified by Haidee C. Pineda\nFour events focusing on the body comprised of an exhibit, symposium, book launch and film showing were held at the UP Diliman (UPD) GT-Toyota Asian Center on Feb. 13 as part of the 3-month celebration of the \"Kat(h)awan : UPD Festival of Culturte and the Arts 2018\" (UPDFOCA)\nGays and Philippine comedy by Chi A. Ibay, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nFrom \"Facilica Falayfay: (1969) to \"Zsazsa Zaturnnah\" (2006) and \"Beauty and the Bestie\" (2015), gays have become an endeared and enduring figure in Philippine comedy. \nThe body is a probing tool by Mariamme D. Jadloc, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Kevin Brandon E. Saure\nThe body is a medium of empiricism , an investigative instrument.  \nThe body is a probing tool by Mariamme D. Jadloc, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Kevin Brandon E. Saure\nThe body is a medium of empiricism, an investigative instrument. \nFlash mob opens FOCA\nPublic performances were simultaneously staged at 3 p.m. on Feb. 1 in four different locations at the University of the Philippines Diliman (UPD) to open this year\'s 3-month Festival of Culture and the Arts (FOCA).', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1019, 'E2-1019AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman : the community newspaper of UP Diliman, Volume XXIV, Number 2 (2 copies)', '', '', '', 'Lawas caps Kat(h)awan by Anna Regidor, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \n\"Pagpamulak\" by Lee Paje.\n\"Lawas,\" three site specific art installations on campus closed Kat(h)awan : Bodies, Culture, Society, UP Diliman\'s 4-month Festival of Culture and the Arts on Apr. 11.\n9 professors emeriti appointed by Anna E. Regidor, images by Leonardo A. Reyes and Jefferson Villacruz\nThe UP Board of Regents (BOR), at its 1334th meeting on Apr. 6, appointed 16 new faculty members as Professors Emeriti, nine of whom are from UP Diliman (UPD). \nAlfonso receives PCS award \nProf. Grace Javier Alfonso, PhD, received the 2018 Excellence in Communication Award from the Philippines Communication Society (PCS) on Apr. 30 at the Polytechnic University of the Philippines Bulwagang Balagtas in Manila. \nHokkaido University nook opened by Chi A. Ibay, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nA delegation from Hokkaido University (HU) in Japan and officials of the University of the Philippines formally opened the HU nook at UP Diliman (UPD) on Mar. 6.\nA boost for red seaweed industry by Bino C. Gamba, image by Jefferson Villacruz\nPlentex Aquafarms Corporation (PAC) entered into a memorandum of agreement (MOA) with UP Diliman (UPD) for the commercial licensing of the technologies for the cultivation, propagation, processing and extraction of the red seaweed Halymenia durvellei.\nUPD, HS map structures by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nMore than 65,000 houses and buildings were mapped by 16 schools from five local government units (LGUs) with assistance from the UP Diliman Department of Geography of the College of Social Sciences and Philosophy (CSSP-Geog) and UP NOAH Center from February to April this year. \nDokkaebi, multo, diyosa atbp. ni Haidee C. Pineda, mga kuha ni Leonardo A. Reyes\nItinampok sa Talasalitaan, isang regular na panayam na isinasagawa ng Sentro ng Wikang Filipino (SWF), ang paksa tungkol sa mabababang mitolohikal na nilalang ng Korea at Pilipinas kung saan tinalakay ang kasaysayan, kultural at pulitikal na konteksto, at saysay nito sa panitikan. \nNLP director appointment questioned by Anna Regidor\nWhat does it mean when the person occupying the highest and most influential post in a profession is not licensed?\n71 named UP Scientist by Albino C. Gamba Jr., images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nThe University of the Philippines recognized the hard work and exceptional research productivity of its faculty members by appointing 71 as UP Scientists of various ransk under the Scientific Productivity System (SPS) in ceremonies on Mar. 21 at the Ang Bahay ng Alumni. \nYellow-blue tandem to lead USC by Kevin Brandon E. Saure\nJose Rafael \"Yael\" Toribio of the Nagkakaisang Iskolar para sa Pamantasan at Sambayanan (KAISA UP) has been elected Chairperson of UP Diliman\'s University Student Council (USC) for Academic Year (AY) 2018-2019 on Apr. 27. \n100 companies join UJF 2018 \nText and images by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nMore than 100 companies and organizations participated in this year\'s University Job Fair (UJF) held Apr. 10 to 13 at the Ang Bahay ng Alumni. They came from different sectors like academe, banking, business process outsourcing, communications, energy, food, manufacturing, online selling, pharmaceutical and real estate, among others. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1020, 'E2-1020AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman. Volume 1-2, Number 1', '', '', 'October-December 2018', 'Academic\nActing like gods by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. Image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nHumans could live for 500 years due to medical breakthroughs and a rise in biomechanics. This was claimed by a \"Daily Mail Online\" article in March 2015, said Leonardo A. de Castro at the recent Forum on Science, Technology and Society at the UP College of Education Benitez Theater. \nCutting-edge by Anna Regidor, Image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nCloser to the stars, safer on land\nThe Philippines is now one-step closer to the stars as it ventures into establishing its own space agency. \nThe Source by Haidee C. Pineda\nAng aklat pambata sa panahon ng gadgets \nBago pa nauso ang mga iPad, iPhone, android phone, Xbox, programa sa cable, Netflix at Cartoon Network, namulat ang karamihan sa mga batang Pinoy sa mga kuwento nina Maria Makiling at Juan Tamad. \nIn Focus By Mariamme D. Jadloc, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nMap Rights Wrongs : the 1734 Murillo Velarde map \nChina never controlled the South China Sea (West Philippine Sea) at any time in history; as proven by the 1734 Murillo Velarde map. \nManila to London and back : the story of a map\'s travels by Mariamme D. Jadloc, illustration by Brent Antigua\nThe journey of the mother of all Philippine maps back home again four years ago. \nInsider by Haidee C. Pineda, illustration by Brent Antigua\nMental health in UPD \nThe Republic Act (RA)11036 or Mental Health Act, was finally signed into law by Philippine President Rodrigo R. Duterte on Jun. 20. \nIn Focus by Bino C. Gamba\nHow\'s the weather?\nNestled in the 30-hectare area of the UP National Science Complex, there at the southeast portion of the UP Diliman (UPD) campus is the Synoptic Laboratory (SL) of the College of Science, Institute of Environmental Science and Meteorology (IESM). ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1021, 'E2-1021AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman. Volume 2, Number 1-2', '', '', '2019', 'Insider by Anna Regidor, Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nData Privacy : Everyone\'s Concern \nIn 2016, a Manila public school teacher was scammed by a person after he uploaded a photo of his newly earned professional ID card in Facebook. This photo was used to take out loans amounting to P800,000 from three different banks.\nAcademic by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nAdapting to change \nImages by Leonardo A. Reyes\nInfographic and photo manipulation by Jacelle Isha B. Bonus\nResponding to the changing educational and economic situation worldwide, the UP Diliman (UPD) University Council (UC) approved the 2017 New UPD General Education (GE) Program at its 142nd Special Meeting immediately after the UPD GE Conference on Mar. 20, 2017 at the National Institute of Physics Auditorium.\nCutting edge by Anna Regidor\nWhen the grass is the greener\nPhotos courtesy of Ma. Chela Cenia\nIn 1996, tragedy struck the province of Marinduque when the drainage tunnels of the open pit where the Marcopper Mining Corporation had been keeping its tailings ruptured, spilling tons of toxic mine waste into the Boac River, killing plant and animal life and turning the water an iridescent blue. \nThe Source by Chi A. Ibay\nSo how many Filipinos are really poor and hungry?\nCoach Bo \nImages by Jefferson Villacruz\nIn Focus by Haidee C. Pineda and Kevin Brandon E. Saure\nHitting rock bottom is not strange for the UP Men\'s Basketball Team (UPMBT) for many years. \nExploring RP Archaeotourism \nPhoto courtesy of Jacl G.L. Medrana \nAcademic by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nThis February, the University of the Philippines (UP) celebrated its 70th year of transfer from Manila to its Diliman Campus. \nAMR Prevalence and Global Public Health\nInsider by Bino C. Gamba\nThe World Health Organization declares that antimicrobial resistance [AMR] is a growing serious threat to global public health. \nMRSA isolates in UPD by Bino C. Gamba\n\"Staphylococcus aureus and Methicilin-resistant S. aureus (MRSA) carriage in Public Computer Service Providers and Utility Jeepneys in UP Diliman\" was first published in the January-June 2018 issue of \"Science Diliman.\"\nAcademic by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nThe University of the Philippines Diliman (UPD) has always been a venue for concerns and causes of various publics. \nA Haven for HR Defenders \nImages by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr.\nPhoto Manipulation by Jacelle Isha B. Bonus\nFor the Record \nPhotos compiled by Danielle Sydney G. Cariaga\nPhotos courtesy of UP Diliman Main Library\nInfographic by Brent Antigua \nNostalgia\nIn 1948, under the stewardship of UP President Bienvenido Gonzalez, much of UP was transferred from its campus in Manila to a bigger campus in Diliman, Quezon City. \nUP Diliman Month through the years ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1022, 'E2-1022AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman. Volume 2, Number 3', '', '', '2019', 'Insider by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nOn Dec. 17, 2011, flashfloods caused by typhoon Sendong ravaged Cagayan de Oro City leaving depth and destruction on its path. \nPreserving UPD\'s soul. Images by The UP Wild. Infographic by Brent Antigua.\nIt is easier to forget numbers and details but how a person or a place made you feel stays with you. \nIn Focus by Anna Regidor\nBalancing biodiversity and building by Anna Regidor \nProtecting biodiversity in UP Diliman (UPD) is difficult because protecting and preserving it is complex and ties to many different disciplines and aspects of life on campus. It often comes into conflict with huma activity and progress. \nUP Technical Working Group for Biodiversity Management \nThe Source by Haidee C. Pineda \nWhat is AAP@UPD? Images by Jefferson Villacruz and Leonardo A. Reyes \nAspiring University of the Philippines Diliman (UPD) students may now choose to apply for an Associate in Arts (AA) degree in the Arts and Letters Cluster, a 2-year pre-baccalaureate program, following the UP Board of Regents\' (BOR) approval at its 1345th meeting on Jul. 31. \nProfile by Bino C. Gamba Jr. \nMapping PSA\'s course\nImage by Jefferson Villacruz\nThe implementation of the Philippine Identification System (PhilSys) and the Community-Based Monitoring System (CBMS) are the top priorities of Claire Dennis S. Mapa as the new National Statistician and head of the Philippine Statistics Authority (PSA). \nChildren and empathy. Images by Leonardo A. Reyes\nAcademic by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nDo children have empathy?', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1023, 'E2-1023AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman. Volume 3, Numbers 1-4', '', '', '2020', '#TatagUP\nTugon ng UP Diliman sa Hamon ng COVID-19 by Bino C. Gamba, Chi A. Ibay, Mariamme D. Jadloc, Haidee C. Pineda, Anna E. Regidor and Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nLife, as most Metro Manila residents knew it, began its drastic change on Mar. 8, when President Rodrigo R. Duterte signed Proclamation No. 922, which formally declared a state of public health emergency in the Philippines and suspended classes in public and private schools in the National Capital Region (NCR) from Mar. 10 to 14. \nCoronavirus Pandemic Timeline\nOn December 31, 2019, the World Health Organization (WHO) reported cases of pneumonia detected in Wuhan, China. According to Wuhan Municipal Health, the cases occurred between Dec. 12 and 29. The virus was still unknown. \nAs of October 26, 2020, COVID-19 had infected 43,345, 944, with deaths at 1,159,093. In the Philippines, cases stood at 370,028 with 6,977 deaths. \nInnovations\nInnovation is what drives the units under the Science and Technology cluster, and from March to December, 2020, 24 of the 30 projects listed under the #TatagUP banner were from colleges in this cluster. \nKnowledge Creation\n\"Knowing the enemy is winning half the battle.\"\nDonations and Fundraising\nUPDate was able to document 36 donation/fundraising drives.\nUtak at Puso laban sa Covid\nAng Pesteng Pag-ibig\nRio Alma\n26 Abril 2020\nHard Lockdown sa Tundo\nRio Alma\n4 Mayo 2020\nInitiatives\nPublic service is in the DNA of every UPD constituent, and throughout the years, various units, colleges and even student organizations began initiatives to address the pandemic. \nInsider by Anna Regidor\nUPHS : at the frontlines \nPrior to the COVID-19 pandemic, the UP Health Service (UPHS) was a constant if not overlooked feature of the campus.\nOutreach\nHeeding UP Diliman Chancellor Fidel R. Nemenzo\'s call to \"continue to look out for each other,\" members of the UPD community organized a number of outreach activities to address the pressing concerns brought by the pandemic and the ensuing hard lockdown. \nAng Balangkas ng UPD COVID-19 Task Force\nSimula Nobyembre 2019, naging laman ng mga balita\'t pahayagan ang noo\'y bagong virus na pinangalanang n-COVID-19. \nIn Focus nina Sir Anril P. Tiatco at Jem R. Javier (Hango sa Juan Jr at Rosario Halili-Quintos Professorial Chair ni Prop. Adeline Pacia)\nThe Source by Rio Alma\nDumalaw si Walt Whitman sa Filipinas \nSino ba naman ang mag-aakalang sisikat si Walt Whitman?\nThe Source by Romanlito S. Austria\nNang unang ibinaba ang \"lockdown\" noong Marso, pangamba at pagkabahalang dulot ng pandemyang COVID-19 ang sumaklob sa bawat puso at isip ng mga tao. \nInsider \nIsolation and Opportunity \nMarika Daphne I. Amaro, 3rd year BA Anthropology, CSSP\nDuring March and April, I was in denial and uncertain about what will happen next. \nCoby Camento \n3rd year B Sports Science, CHK\nDuring this Community Quarantine, I always make myself busy by doing household chores because I often wake up early, and I must help my parents clean the house.  \nNikolo Perez\nMS Marine Science, MSI\nThe year 2020 is the worst year of my entire life\nPaolo Salazar\n3rd year BS Tourism, AIT\nAt the start of the community quarantine, my daily routine was repetitive. \nLexandra Abdon\nUniversity Extension Associate I, UP College of Engineering Library\nAdmittedly, the past months of the community quarantine have not been easy. \nLucky E. Dela Rosa\nCAL-BA Philippine Studies June 2020 graduate and former Ipil Residence hall dormer\nAng dormitoryo ng totoong buhay\nMarissa Rullan\nStaff, College of Fine Arts\nNaranasan mo na bang mag-register sa mga prepaid mobile data load?\nFatima Sapno\nOffice of the Vice Chancellor for Community Affairs\nThe community quarantine can be as difficult for our furry friends as it is for us workers from home. \nNeil Patrick S. Ferrer, MSC, CSCS\nSenior Lecturer, UP College of Human Kinetics\nThe Source by Eloisa May P. Hernandez\nUPD during lockdown', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1024, 'E2-1024AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman. Volume 4, Numbers 1', '', '', '2021', 'Cutting edge by Anna Regidor\nMaya-2 takes flight \nMaya-2, the second cube satellite (cubesat) designed and developed by Filipino scholars has arrived at the International Space Station (ISS) following a successful launch earlier this week. \nImage courtesy of PHL-Microsat\nIn Focus ni Mariamme D. Jadloc\nIsang \'di malilimutang yugto sa kasaysayan ng Unibersidad ng Pilipinas (UP) at ng bayan ang Diliman Commune. \nDiliman Commune Timeline\nImages and Information/Materials Courtesy of UPD Office for Initiatives in Culture and the Arts \nInfographic by Jefferson Villacruz\nFor the record by Dr. Francisco Nemenzo Jr. \nThe continuing relevance of academic freedom*\nA seminar on the theme \"Academic Freedom and Contemporary Philippine Reality\" cannot evade politically sensitive issues; otherwise academic freedom will just be, in the words of Angela Davis, \"an empty concept which professors use to guarantee their right to work undisturbed by the real world, undisturbed by the real problems of society.\"\nProfile by Bino C. Gamba\nPhilSA\'s new recruit\nThe country\'s space agency has a new recruit!\nAcademic by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nFQS changed country\'s labor landscape\nThe First Quarter Storm (FQS) proved to be an eye opener not only for the students but also for the Philippine workforce and has contributed to changing the landscape of the labor movement in the Philippines. \nACF 2021 opens \nImages by Jacelle Isha B. Bonus\nIt was a somber evening of poetry and song last Feb 1, 5:30 p.m. in UP Diliman (UPD) as it opened its annual Arts and Culture Festival (ACF) with \"Barikada Singkwenta : Pagpupugay at Paggunita (a late afternoon vigil)\" near the Oblation Plaza to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the Diliman Commune. \nInsider by Anna Regidor\nAcademic by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nStudying humor, seriously \nImages courtesy of Prof. Maria Rhodora G. Ancheta, PhD\nFilipinos are known as fun-loving and are always smiling. \nAcademic by Mariamme D. Jadloc\nAng kasaysayan ng demokratikong konsultasyon sa UP \nMarahil lubhang pangkaraniwan na lamang na nagaganap ang konsultasyon o demokratikong pagsangguni sa iba\'t ibang sektor ng akademikong yunit o komunidad tuwing may nakatakdang pagpapalit ng pamunuan sa UP kung kaya\'t di na ito masyadong napapansin. \nInsider by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nBunga ng malaking pinsala sa Kamaynilaan pagkatapos ng Ikalawang Digmaang Pandaigdig noong 1945, nangailangan ang Unibersidad ng Pilipinas na humanap ng lugar upang maging bago nitong tahanan. \nAng \"Lupang Hinirang\" ng UPD\nImages courtesy of Office for Initiatives in Culture and the Arts\nFirst Quarter Storm Timeline\nThe Philippines in the 1960s\nIn Memoriam \nLilia Quindoza-Santiago\nRene P. Felix\nLilia Arbues Torres\nDaisy B. Atienza\nCelia D. Laguyo\nAmelia Lapeña-Bonifacio\nEva Marie A. Ratilla\nAurora Roxas-Lim\nLeon M. Payawan Jr. \nLaura Samson\nMaureen C. Pagaduan\nFelicia Delos Santos\nRoberto Verzola\nCynthia Dionisio-Turingan\nRandolf M. Bustamante\nNoli N. Reyes\nPrimitivo C. Cal\nRenato S. Velasco\nAlonzo A. Gabriel\nAileen S. P. Baviera\nAjit Singh Rye', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1025, 'E2-1025AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman. Volume 4, Numbers 2', '', '', 'April to June 2021', 'Academic by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nVictory at Mactan revisited \nWhat were the weapons used? \nImages courtesy of the UPD Office for Initiatives in Culture and the Arts \nInsider by Anna Regidor\nThe sophistication of pre-Spanish Visayans\nEven before the arrival of the Spaniards on Philippine shores, the inhabitants of what is now known as the Visayas region had a complex society composed of thriving communities.\nThe Source ni Mariamme D. Jadloc\nAng mga sasakyang pantubig ng sinaunang Pinoy\nTampok sa panayam na \"Annotations on the Monleon Illustrations of Philippine Indigenous Boats,\" ang husay at tibay ng mga gawang sasakyang pantubig ng mga sinaunang Filipino hanggang sa panahon ng pananakop ng mga Kastila. \nImages courtesy of the UPD Office for Initiatives in Culture and the Arts \nIn Focus by Bino C. Gamba\nConquer. Control. Impose.\n\"Through the instruments of urbanism and architecture, the Spanish colonial authorities therefore cemented their territorial and spiritual takeover in the archipelago.\"\nImage courtesy of Prof. Gerard Lico, PhD and the UPD Office for Initiatives in Culture and the Arts \nIn Focus ni Mariamme D. Jadloc\nSa nakaraang gawaing online ng Likhaan : Lundayan ng Tradisyunal na Sining at Kultura noong Mayo 15, naibahagi ni Prop. Cecilia S. De La Paz, PhD ang kanyang pananaliksik ukol sa mga pista sa Lucban, Quezon, partikular ang Pahiyas. \nImages courtesy of Prof. Cecilia S. De La Paz, PhD and Rdee De La Paz\nMga pista ng Lucban bilang panlipunang diskurso ni Mariamme D. Jadloc\nSa Lucban, ang pista ni San Luis Obispo na ginaganap tuwing Agosto 19 ay taimtim o solemn ang pagdiriwang. \nImages courtesy of Prof. Cecilia S. De La Paz, PhD and Rdee De La Paz\nAcademic by Mariamme D. Jadloc \nChristianity through the lens of Anthropology \nImages courtesy of the UPD Office for Initiatives in Culture and the Arts \nDIscussions on Christianity through an anthropological perspective was what the forum \"Of Crosses and \'Culture:\' An Anthropological Look at 500 Years of Christianity in the Philippines\" (Of Crosses and \'Culture\') was largely all about. \nAcademic by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nStudying language, understanding people\nWhat language will the Spaniards use to communicate with the natives?\nImages courtesy of the UPD Office for Initiatives in Culture and the Arts \nSagip K9 rescues campus dogs \nInsider by Anna Regidor\nWhen one thinks of a K9 dog, the image of a large, imposing pure-breed such as a German Shepherd or a Bloodhound sniffing luggage for bombs or roaming disater-struck areas looking for survivors usualy comes to mind \nImages by Jacelle Isha B. Bonus', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1026, 'E2-1026AC', '', 'UPdate Diliman. Volume 5, Numbers 1-2', '', '', 'January-June 2022', 'A call to shape the country\'s future \n\"More than looking for our identity, we should aspire for an efficient justice system and genuine land reform, said retired professor Floro C. Quibuyen, PhD of the UP Diliman (UPD) Asian Center (AC).\nAcademe by Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nIn Focus by Mariamme D. Jadloc \n3D mapping QC for DRRM\nAt the international virtual conference Counter-mapping the City organized by the UP Diliman (UPD) Department of Geography (DGeog), a participatory three-dimensional mapping (P30M) of Quezon City (QC) barangays was presented by Emmanuel Garcia, a professor at DGeog. \nInsider by Dianne Pasia (UPIS Intern) with Anna Regidor \nUPIS MCTV turns romantic \nUP Integrated School (UPIS) students reminisced about love and loss in the first episode of the UPIS Media Center\'s (MC) MCTV media series. \nInsider by Ronnel Fernando (UPIS intern) with Bino C. Gamba\nYoung voters attend voter education forum \nClose to 600 young voters attended the online forum Vote Right 2022 : The Voter Education Launch on Feb. 22. \nAcademe by Jonas Markus B. Dula (UPIS Intern) with Benito V. Sanvictores Jr. \nTeaching and learning ethics the Gen Z way \n\"How can I make my Gen Z students understand the importance of ethics?\"\nIn Focus by Anna Regidor\n#PILIpiLUNAS2022 charts course to COVID-19 recovery\nThere is great change happening in the Philippines, with a new administration set to take the reins of the national government and the country slowly starting to emerge from a two-year running pandemic that exposed the cracks and weaknesses in the Philippine economy. \n#PILIpiLUNAS2022 launches agenda\nAfter more than a year of debate, discussion and discovery, the UP Diliman (UPD) Task Force on a Blueprint for Building the Nation (Task Force Nation Building / TFNB) launched #PILIpiLUNAS2022 Governance Agenda : Pag-angat at Pagsulong tungo sa Magandang Buhay at Bukas on Apr. 29. \n#PILIPILUNAS 2022 GOVERNANCE AGENDA : A Public Launch\nPag-angat at Pagsulong Tungo sa Magandang Buhay at Bukas\n#PILIpiLUNAS2022 in 2021\nAs the country moves to rebuild the nation amid the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic and in preparation for the new administration, five webinars were held from August to December 2021. \n4 more from #PILIpinLUNAS2022\nThe UP Diliman (UPD) Task Force on a Blueprint for Building the Nation (Task Force Nation Building / TFNB) continued its webinar series with the sixth installment of #PILIpiLUNAS2022 : Pagbangon at Pagsulong sa Magandang Buhay at Bukas. \nInt\'l confab presents counter-mapping of RP locals \nThe Source by Mariamme D. Jadloc \nEfforts by Filipino researchers on mapping local communities were highlighted at the second plenary session of the Counter-mapping the City International Virtual Conference held in March 2022. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1027, 'E2-1027AC', '', 'UPdate Magazine. Volume 1, Numbers 1 (7 copies)', '', '', 'March-August 2014', 'Pride of place; Boldness of vision by Chancellor Michael L. Tan\n(Editorial note : Chancellor Tan\'s vision paper was prepared in January 2014, one of the requirements in the search process for a new chancellor.)\nUP Diliman : resources and challenges \nUP Diliman (UPD) is the largest CU (constituent university) of the UP System. The following facts and figures (as of 2nd semester AY 2013-2014) can be interpreted as resources, as well as challenges, of Diliman.\nRe-engineering academics : Dr. Benito M. Pacheco\nFor one with a lot on his plate, Dr. Benito M. Pacheco seems largely undaunted. \nStrengthening the culture of research : Dr. Fidel R. Nemenzo by Bino C. Gamba, images Leonardo A. Reyes, Jefferson Villacruz\nThe new UP Diliman (UPD) Vice Chancellor for Research and Development (VCRD) is Prof. Fidel R. Nemenzo from the Institute of Mathematics (IM) of the College of Science. A graduate of UPD\'s BS Mathematics program, Nemenzo obtained his MS and Doctor of Science degrees from Sophia University, Japan. \nImproved efficiency : Prof. Viriginia C. Yap by Mariamme D. Jadloc, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\n\"Improved efficiency.\" These are the buzzwords of the Office of the Vice Chancellor for Administration (OVCA) in the second term of Prof. Virginia C. Yap. \nCandid conversation with an \"accidental\" chancellor\nThe Diliman Information Office staff asked the new chancellor for a no-holds barred tell-all interview and he agreed to this, one afternoon after a photo shoot with his new administration. We present edited excerpts. \nBibingka leadership : Dr. Neil Martial R. Santillan by Haidee C. Pineda, image Leonardo A. Reyes\nBarely a week in office, Dr. Neil Martial R. Santillan, the new Vice Chancellor for Student Affairs (VCSA), already hit the ground running and delivered his first speech - the welcome remarks at the opening of the Freshman Orientation program (FOP) on May 6. \nCreating vibrant spaces : Dr. Nestor T. Castro by Anna Regidor, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nTwo minutes have passed inside the Office of the Vice Chancellor for Community Affairs (OVCAA). The assistant confides that he\'s very hands-on, taking the time to get to know and understand each office under the OVCCA well. \nRediscovering naivete by Teresa Paula De Luna, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\n\"Never lose your naivete.\"\nAcademician, public servant, administrator by Soledad Natalia M. Dalisay, image by Jefferson Villacruz\nDr. Michael L. Tan\'s appointment as 10th Chancellor of the University of the Philippines Diliman (UPD) is a milestone : he was the first from the College of Social Sciences and Philosophy (CSSP).', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1028, 'E2-1028AC', '', 'UPdate Magazine. Volume 1, Numbers 2 (2 copies)', '', '', 'September-December 2014 ', 'UP Diliman : Paglulugar, Pagpopook ni Michael L. Tan \nSa simula, itong kapuluang tinatawag nating Pilipinas ay wala pa. Ngunit sa patuloy na pag-inog ng daigdig, patuloy rin ng pagkilos ng mga lupa at mga platong kontinental. Milyung-milyong taon na patuloy na pagkilos ng mga dambuhalang lupain pati na rin ang mga bulkan sa ilalim ng karagatan ay nag-uudyok ng mga paggalaw upang dahan-dahang mabuo ang kapuluang ito. \nDiliman place name connections by Maria Bernadette L. Abrera, image by Jefferson Villacruz\nIn the story of the Katipunan and Diliman\'s role in the revolution, some interesting facts emerged that pointed to connections not only of events but also of places on account of their names. \nLearning, unlearning, relearning by Frederick Paulo Tomacder, image by Jefferson Villacruz\nOn a warm afternoon with the sun\'s orange glow flooding the lobby, bags, balikbayan boxes and electric fans crowd a guard\'s table. Eager freshmen make a slow procession to the dorm\'s admission office. \nRemembering the 1971 Diliman Commune by Judy M. Taguiwalo\nThe 1971 Diliman Commune occupies a special niche in the history of the University of the Philippines in its role as social critic. The Commune, as I wrote three years ago, \"showcas(ed) the power of the militant solidarity of the UP community against military incursions into the university. \nMicrocosm of Concensus and Dissensus (A conversation with Francisco Nemenzo on the Claro M. Recto Hall)\nThe Faculty Center is the first structure in the University of the Philippines Diliman (UPD) dedicated to house faculty members. It was UP President Carlos P. Romulo\'s \"response to the faculty\'s need for comfort and convenience,\" as described in Sites and Symbols. \nUP Diliman nating mahal : paraiso ng sining by Amihan Bonifacio-Ramolete, mga larawan Leonardo A. Reyes, Jefferson Villacruz\nMatatagpuan sa Lungsod ng Quezon ang luntiang kampus ng Unibersidad ng Pilipinas Diliman (UPD) na kanlungan ng mga kasapi ng akademiko at di-akademikong komunidad-isang kabalintunaang maituturing sa pusod ng mabangis na lungsod na nalalambungan ng samu\'t saring polusyon at kaguluhan. \nThe journey of UP Pampanga by Julieta C. Mallari, image by Leonardo A. Reyes\nIf pages of the history of the UP Diliman Extension Program in Pampanga (UPDEPP) are to be turned, there emerges an image of tumbleweed being tossed to and fro in sharply broken rhythms of confusing movement. \nFireflies by J. Neil Garcia ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49');
