(1172, 'E2-1172AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1957, September 12)', 'Mr. Paul B.W. Gollong, Manager, Armour Research Foundation of Illinois, Institute of Technology, 10 West 35th Street, Chicago 16, Illinois\nDear. Mr. Gollong : Dean Ortigas of the State University mentioned your desire to know who from the Philippines are attending the International Industrial Development Conference Co-Sponsored by Time-Life International and the Stanford Research Institute. He requested the IDC to obtain the information and to transmit these directly to you. I personally welcome the assignment because it gives me the opportunity to renew acquaintances with you. As far as we could determine, the following compose the Filipino Group Attending the Conference : Ramon V. Del Rosario, President, Philippine Investment-Management Consultants, Inc.; Carlos Palanca, Jr., General Manager, La Tondeña, Inc.; Roberto T. Villanueva, President, Philippine Chamber of Industries; Alfonso Calalang, President, Security Bank & Trust Co., Member, Board of Directors, Philippine Association; Leonides Virata, Vice-President-Treasurer, Philippine American Life Insurance Co. Except for Mr. A. Calalang who was officially designated representative of an organization invited to the conference, it is our impression that these gentlemen are going at the invitation extended to them individually by the sponsors of the conference. I would like to take this opportunity to inform you that I am a member of a team of eight officials from private and government agencies that will go on an ICA sponsored trip to the U.S., U.K., Continental Europe and Japan on an 8-10 week observation of the development and implementation of product standards. The trip has been scheduled to start in October, 1957. Should our itinerary bring us close to the Chicago area, I hope to be able to call on you at ARF. My personal regards, Sincerely, Hugo B. Fernandez, Deputy Director', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1173, 'E2-1173AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1957, May 22) ', 'Dean C.A. Ortigas, College of Engineering, University of the Philippines, Diliman, Quezon City, Philippines. Dear Dean Ortigas : With the passing months, I fear, perhaps wrongly, that interest in the Industrial Research Center will wane. Although it is pleasing to read from your letter of May 7th that practically all parties involved in this program are supporting it, it would seem to me that early action is necessary if a program is going to be realized. Fortunately, you are directly on top of the situation, and thus the program probably has a better than even chance of being initiated. Thinking that you might be interested in another article from the \"Wall Street Journal\", relating to science, the April 24th issue speaks about scientists and their ventures into industry. The clipping is enclosed. I had a touching letter from Mrs. Magsaysay in which she expressed her appreciation for our words of sympathy. Since I, myself, had not writted to her, I can only assume that you, Dr. Marañon, or Dr. Arguelles, forwarded our expression of sympathy which we sent to you. Our sincere thanks for this good gesture. Sincerely, Paul B.W. Gollong, Manager ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1174, 'E2-1174AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1957, May 3)', 'Dean C. A. Ortigas, Director, Industrial Research Center, University of the Philippines, Quezon City, Philippines\nMy dear Dean Ortigas : Shortly, Dr. R. F. Humphreys, Assistant Director of the Armour Research Foundation is leaving for Burma to advise on the Atomic Energy Program of that country. En route, he will stopover in Manila, arriving June 5th on PAA Flight No. 833. He will stay at the Manila Hotel until the 7th and then proceed to Burma. Although his stay will be brief, I believe that a meeting with you would be most interesting. Thus, I have asked him to contact you upon his arrival. A brief biography on him is enclosed. Sincerely, Paul; B.W. Gollong, Manager', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1175, 'E2-1175AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Biography of Dr. Richard F. Humphreys, Assistant Director, Armour Research Foundation of Illinois In', 'Dr. Richard F. Humphreys, assistant director of Armour Research Foundation of Illinois Institute of Technology, Chicago, is recognized as one of the nation\'s leading atomic scientists. In his capacity as assistant director, Humphreys is responsible for the development of new areas of technical research at the Foundation. These new areas are being developed in the nine research departments that comprise Armour Research Foundation, an independent, not-for-profit organization which annual conducts approximately $12 million in sponsored research for industry and the government. It was largely through Humphreys\' efforts that the Foundation was able to enter the nuclear reactor field and to install the world\'s first reactor for industrial research. As a scientist, Humphreys has gained a widespread reputation as an expert in the areas of ultracentrifugation of isotopes, cyclotron research, and nuclear reactions. Humphreys joined the Foundation in 1949 as assistant manager of the physics research department and became manager in 1951. Prior to 1949, he was an associate professor of physics at Yale University where he served on the faculty for nine years. He was acting director of the Sloane Physics Laboratory at Yale and also served as consultant on underwater sound research for industyr and the government. Humphreys has co-authored a textbook on \"First Principles of Atomic Physics,\" and has published papers in Physical Review, Review of Scientific Instruments, and numerous other scientific journals. A Rector scholar at DePauw University, Greencastle, Ind., he was awarded a bachelor of arts degree in physics in 1933. He received his master\'s degree from Syracuse University in 1936 and his doctorate from Yale University in 1939. Active in civic affairs, Humphreys is chairman of the radiological defense committee of the Chicago Civil Defense Corps and has served as a member of the isotopes advisory committee to the health commissioner. He is a director and past president of the Physical Club of Chicago. His professional memberships include the American Physical Society, American Association for the Advancement of Science, American Association of Physics Teachers, and Sigma XI. A native of Greenville, O., he attended high school at Martinsville, Ind., where his mother, Mrs. R.T. Humphreys still resides. Humphreys lives at 3101 S. Wabash Ave., Chicago', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1176, 'E2-1176AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1957, April 26) ', 'Dean C.A. Ortigas, Member, Interdepartmental Committee on Atomic Energy, Manila. Dear Dean Ortigas : During my absence to attend the 10th World Health Assembly in Geneva, you are hereby designated Acting Chairman of the Interdepartmental Committee on Atomic Energy. You should preside over the meetings of the Committee and sign all communications pertaining to the Committee\'s activities, except routine correspondence which may be signed for the Committee by the Commitee Secretary. The subsequent meetings of the Committee may continue to be held in the Office of the Secretary of Health. Very truly yours, Paulino J. Garcia, M.D. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49');
