(1370, 'E2-1370AC', '', 'U.P. General Alumni-Faculty Homecoming and Reunion ', 'U.P. Diliman Campus, Quezon City ', 'Ang Bahay ng Alumni', 'June 19, 1999', '1. Call to Order\n2. Proposed Resolutions Approved by the U.P. Alumni Council at its Meeting on June 18, 1999 for Consideration and Approval by the UPAA Members : \n(a) Resolution No. 1 : \"To call for the conduct of studies on policies and conditions that generate and sustain poverty\" \n(b) Resolution No. 2 : \"To call upon the University of the Philippines to review its student scholarship scheme to enhance its service particularly to the poor and deserving students\"\n(c) Resolution No. 3 : \"To stress the need to respect and adhere to universally accepted and basic values especially in governance\"\n(d) Resolution No. 4 : \"To express the sense that tremendous corruption in government is anti-poor and that any poverty reduction or elimination policy must have anti-corruption component\"\n(e) Resolution No. 5 : \"To create a committee of the U.P. Alumni Council for the effective implementation of the resolutions approved by the U.P. Alumni Association\"\n4. Other Matters\n5. Adjournment ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
