(1379, 'E2-1379AC', '', 'Jesus J. Vergara Professorial Chair Lecture \nGetzmo : an email based web browser by Mark J. Encarnacion, Department of Computer Science, University of the Philippines. 11 January 2001, 5:30 PM, Melchor Hall, Room 319', '', '', 'January 11, 2001', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1380, 'E2-1380AC', '', 'Nomination Guidelines for Outstanding Unit in Extension Service', '', '', '', 'Criteria\n1. Extension service aligned with the mission of the institution\n2. Effect/impact of extension work on the organization/community served\n3. Introduction of innovative approaches\na) for interdisciplinary collaboration\nb) for cost-effectiveness introduced\nc) in content of materials (flyers, manuals, etc.)\nd) in nature of activities\ne) in other aspects\n4. Collective efforts of the unit\'s personnel/staff in the conduct of extension work', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1381, 'E2-1381AC', '', 'University of the Philippines to Ricaredo D. Demetillo : Poet, Humanist, Scholar ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1382, 'E2-1382AC', '', 'UP REPSA, Inc. ', '', '', '', 'UP REPSA, Inc. is duly registered with the Securities and Exchange Commission\nThe UP REPSA, Inc. is a non-stock, non-profit organization duly registered with the Securities and Exchange Commission on September 9, 1997. Its members consist of research, extension and professional staff of the University of the Philippines System. \nUP REPSA is an organization whose members come from the research, extension and profssional staff of the entire UP system. \nUP REPSA\'s objectives are : \n* to organize the research, extension and professional staff of the University of the Philippines in the pursuit of common scientific, economic, social and political interest; \n* to safeguard the rights and to advance the welfare of the REPS, as well as to work for the re-orientation of science for the people through sustained education activities among science and technology workers and the people as a whole; \n*to work for the development of scientific programs suited to the needs and interests of the common people;\n*to make a unified stand on issues, problems and events of national/sectoral concern;\n*to make proper sectoral representation in various policy making bodies of the University\nUP REPSA Activities\nSince establishment, the following activities have been held : \n*Election of Officers for the System and for each Autonomous Unit.\n*Holding of the First UP-REPS Conference last October 15-16, 1998 at the D.L. Umali Hall of UP Los Baños, with the theme \"Gearing UP-REPS Toward the 21st Century\"\n*Submission of the \"Proposals for New Guidelines in Determining Rank and Salary Grade of UP-REPS\" to the UP Administration. ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1383, 'E2-1383AC', '', 'Pangkalahatang Pagbabalik at Muling Pagtitipon ng mga Nagsipagtapos at mga Guro sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas', '', '', 'Hunyo 19, 1999', 'Ang Asosasyon ng mga Nagsipagtapos sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas ay malugod na inaanyahan kayo sa Pangkalahatang Pagbabalik at Muling Pagtitipon ng mga Nagsipagtapos at mga Guro sa Unibersidad ng Pilipinas sa ganap na alas singko ng hapon, Sabado, Ika 19 ng Hunyo, 1999 sa Bahay ng Alumni, U.P. Diliman, Lungsod Quezon ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
