(1387, 'E2-1387AC', '38', 'Proceedings of The South East Asia Regional Seminar & Workshop on Higher Engineering Education Network\nSeminar and Workshop 25-27 February 1997\nBandung, Indonesia\n\nOrganized by : Directorate General of Higher Education, Ministry of Education and Culture, ', '', '', 'February 25-27, 1997', 'Group photograph\nForeword from the Director General of Higher Education\nForeword from Japan International Cooperation Agency\nForeword from the Rector of Institut Teknologi Bandung\nExecutive Summary\nList of Committee Members\nPart I Keynote Presentations\nIr. Satryo Soemantri Brodjonegoro, Ph.D. (ITB)\nEngineering Research Activities and Development in Indonesian Universities\nProf. Dr. Nishino Fumio (Saitama University)\nJapanese Cooperation with Developing Countries for Human Resources Development\nProf. Dr. Gotoh Keishi (TUT)\nInnovation in The Japanese Universities Especially Faculties of Science and Engineering\nProf. Dr. Hayakawa Norio (NUT)\nRising Concern Global Environment and Possibility Network Formation - Viewed Through The Project GAME (GEWEX Asian Monsoon Experiment)\nMr. Yuuji Otake and Mr. Takehiro Susaki\nJICA Contribution and ASEAN Higher Engineering Education Network\nProf. Oei Ban Liang, Ph.D. (ITB)\nSome Networking Concepts in South East Asia\nProf. Dr. Tsutsumi Kazuo (TUT)\nTUT\'s Contribution & Expectation on SEA HEENET\nPart II Country Reports\nCountry Report, Malaysia\nMasjuki H.H. Ph.D., Mohd. Hamdi A.S. M.Sc., Moh. Rom T., Ph.D.\nCurrent Status of Engineering Education in Malaysia \nCountry Report, Philippines\nReynaldo B. Vea, Ph.D., Jonathan D.L. Salvacion, Ph.D.\nThe Foundation for Engineering Education Development (FEED, Inc.)\nCountry Report, Singapore I\nAssoc. Prof. L.W.C. Wong\nInformation Technology Infrastructure for Engineering Education & Research in Singapore\nCountry Report, Singapore II\nAssoc. Prof. T.S. Lee\nGlobalisation of Engineering Education and Research in Singapore\nCountry Report, Thailand\nProf. Dr. Panitan Lukunaprasit, Prof. Dr. Ekasit Limsuwan\nThai Higher Education and Research Network (THERNET)\nCountry Report, Indonesia\nProf. Dr. Ir. Sularso\nBodies Providing Coordination and Linkages in Engineering Higher Education\nPart III Project Reports\nProject Report of Transportation Studies, Philippines\nDr. Hussein S. Lidasan, Dr. Yoji Kawakami \nProject Report of the National Center for Transportation Studies JICA Project Regarding Network\nProject Report of Pathumwan Project, Thailand\nMr. Montree Mangklasawad, Dr. S. Okamoto\nThe Development of Mechatronics Engineering Course at Bachelor Degree Level in Pathumwan Technical College\nProf. Dr. Somnuke Praparntanatorn, Dr. Uruya Weesakul\nThammasat University, Faculty of Engineering JICA Project Regarding Network\nProject Report, HEDS - JICA Project Indonesia \nDr. Ir. Faiz Albar\nHEDS - JICA Project 1990 -1996\nPart IV Commissions\n1. Discussion Result of Commission I, Networking Concepts\n2. Discussion Result of Commission II, Networking Function and Framework\n3. Discussion Result of Commission III, Action Plan\nPart V Conclusions of the Seminar and Workshop Annexes\nAnnex 1 List of Participants\nAnnex 2 List of Resource Persons\nAnnex 3 List of Observers', 'Proceedings ', 'Executive Summary of SEA HEE Seminar Organizing Committee \n', 'Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA) in cooperation with Institut Teknologi Bandung held the first South East Asian Seminar/workshop on Higher Engineering Education Network at the Institut Teknologi Bandung, Indonesia February 25-27,1997, aiming to exchange information, human resources, education and researches in the region. Around eighty delegates from six countries, Indonesia, Malaysia, Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Japan attended the seminar/workshop. However, the frame, the scope, the functions, and the activities of this Network were not definitive yet at that moment. So, at the workshop, all the participants intensively discussed and debated those topics. \nThis proceeding includes all the contents presented at the seminar/workshop as well as the agreements and consensus\'s reached through the individual communications with each country delegate after the seminar/workshop, which are in the executive summary. The executive summary describes the conclusions derived from three commission meetings on February 26 and the conclusion session on February 27, and the agreements and consensus integrating the individual communication results with each country delegate.', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
