(1413, 'E2-1413AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2002, July 30) MEMORANDUM NO. DCB 02-031', 'TO : Deans and Department Chairs of Concerned Colleges/Units/Departments\nFROM : Demetria C. Bongga\nVice Chancellor for Research and Development\nSUBJECT : 12th BIWAKO Prize for Ecology\nDATE : 30 July 2002 \n1. The Shiga Prefectural Government in Japan is inviting candidates to apply for the 12th Biwako Prize for Ecology in accordance wtih the rules stated in the attached prize invitation guidance pamphlet. The Biwako Prize provides research grants to individuals engaged in the study of ecology or related sciences dealing with aquatic and/or watershed environments. The prize is awarded annually to an individual who has achieved academically or socially significant research and who is expected to continue to advance this research at a similar level of accomplishment.\n2. Nominations shall be made through channels. Deadline for submission of nominations (2 copies) to OVCRD is September 15, 2002. \n3. Details about the 2002 Biwako Prize for Ecology and the nomination procedures are found at the attached announcement and at the following webpage : http://www.ovcrd.upd.edu.ph/dcbmemo31.htm \nPlease disseminate the invitation to your students, faculty and research staff. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1414, 'E2-1414AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2002, July 1) Re : Nomination of Candidates for the 2002 Biwako Prize for Ecology ', 'Dear Sir/ Madam :\nThe Shiga Prefectural Government in Japan has consistently promoted programs that further humanity\'s sustainable coexistence with environment. In 1991, the Shiga Prefectural Government established the Biwako Prize for Ecology in its desire to play a greater role in environmental conservation and to make a greater contribution to the international community. \nThe Biwako Prize is aimed at supporting individuals engaged in the study of ecology or related sciences dealing with aquatic and/or watershed environments. The prize is awarded annually to an individual who has achieved academically or socially significant research and who is expected to continue to advance this research at a similar level of accomplishment. \nOn the 12th occasion of the awarding of the Biwako Prize for Ecology, we consider it essential to seek further development of this prize by continuing our commendation of high-level researchers as appropriate to the purpose of the award. To more accurately reflect the deepening and expansion of the research content of ecological studies, we have decided to revise our system and extend the screening period from three months to over six months, and change the management/commendation cycle for the prize from the present one year to two years, thereby improving the selection and management activities for this award. \nRelated to this, we hereby invite candidates to apply for the 12th Biwako Prize for Ecology in accordance with the rules stated in the enclosed prize invitation guidance pamphlet. We look forward to receiving many recommendations of suitable candidates. \nThe announcement of prize recipients will be made in May 2003 and the award ceremony will be held on July 1st, 2003 (\"Lake Biwa Day,\" the environmental conservation day for prefectural residents as set by the Basic Environmental Ordinances of Shiga Prefecture).\nWe would also appreciate it if you could notify related organizations or research bodies under your jurisdiction regarding the invitation of candidates to apply to become recipients of the Biwako Prize for Ecology.\nI would be very grateful if you would circulate the information on the Nomination of Candidates for the 2002 Biwako Prize for Ecology among academic societies, research institutes, and related organizations in your country to encourage the nomination of candidates for the prize. I would be also appreciated if you could notice the applications term is until October 30, 2002. \nThank you very much for your attention to this request.\n\nYours sincerely, \n\nYoshitsugu Kunimatsu\nGovernor\nShiga Prefecture', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
