(1424, 'E2-1424AC', '', 'The President of the University of the Philippines and The Chancellor of UP Diliman\ncordially invite you to the 90th General Commencement Exercises\nwith the theme\nPANAWAGAN PARA SA PAGBABAGO : KATAPATAN AT PANANAGUTAN SA BAYAN and the Conferment of the De', '', '', 'April 22, 2001\nSunday\nUniversity Amphitheater\n3:15 in the afternoon', '', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1425, 'E2-1425AC', '', 'Engineering Freshman Convocation 2001 ', '', '', 'June 14, 2001\nUP Film Center\n8:00 AM', '', '', 'Engineering Freshman Convocation 2001\nProject Proposal\nI. Rationale\nII. Objectives of the Project \nA', 'Edgardo G. Atanacio\nDean\nCollege of Engineering\n\nDear Sir,\nThe Engineers and Men for the College and Country would like to invite you to take part in the upcoming gathering of Engineering family - the Engineering Freshman Convocation 2001 to be held on June 14, 8:00 AM at the UP Film Center. \nThe Engineering Freshman Convocation is an opening exercise where we welcome and inspire the students. Also, this will be an opportunity for you to meet the students you would guide in the next few years on their goal to become the country\'s top engineers. And to show the Freshmen the lighter side of being an Engineering student, live performances and fun games will be sponsored by different organizations. Souvenir programs, survival guides, and special items will also be given to the new students. \nIn this light, we would like to request a short message from you to be printed in the souvenir programme of the Engineering Freshman Convocation 2001.\n\nSincerely yours, \n\nVictor Pobre\nProject Coordinator\nconvo@emc2fraternity.org ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1426, 'E2-1426AC', '', 'BPI Science Awards 2001 Awarding Ceremonies ', '', '', '', '', '', '(2001, January 25) BPI Science Awards 2001 Awarding Ceremonies ', 'Department of Electrical and Electronics Engineering\n\nProf. Edgardo G. Atanacio\nDean\nCollege of Engineering \n\nSubject : BPI Science Awards 2001 Awarding Ceremonies \n\nDear Sir, \n\nI am glad to invite you to the BPI Science Awards 2001 Awarding Ceremonies on February 13, 2001, 2:00 PM at the Engineering Theater, 3rd Floor, Melchor Hall, UP Diliman. The awardees for this year are Mark Ian Arcedera (BS Computer Engineering) and Joseph Ryan Victoria (BS Computer Engineering) from the College of Engineering and Clarina dela Cruz (BS Physics) from the College of Science. \nI would like to request that you will deliver the Welcome Address to the audience. During last year\'s awarding ceremonies, you also deliver the Welcome Address. \nYour presence would inspire the awardees and the students and faculty members from the Colleges of Engineering and Science that will attend the ceremonies. \n\nIf you have questions, please don\'t hesitate to contact me at local 5612 or 5845 or email at mile@eee.upd.edu.ph\n\nThank you very much\n\nSincerely yours, \n\nMichael Angelo A. Pedrasa\nCoordinator\nUP-Diliman BPI Science Awards 2001\n\nNoted by : \n\nDr. Rowena Cristina L. Guevara\nChairman\nEEE Department ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1427, 'E2-1427AC', '', 'Fine Arts Week ', '', '', 'February 19 to 23, 2001\n', '', '', '(2001, January 24) Fine Arts Week', 'Prof. Edgardo G. Atanacio\nDean\nCollege of Engineering\n\nDear Sir/Madam :\n\nWe, the students of the University of the Philippines College of FIne Arts are celebrating our annual FINE ARTS WEEK, on February 19 to 23, 2001 with the theme ArtReach : On Common Ground. This is a weeklong festivity, featuring art workshops, exhibits, art talks and fora, film showings and intramurals. ArtReach intends to bring together individuals from different fields. This year, we go beyond the range of the visual arts by reaching out and delving into various areas of specialization, such as literature, music and dance. \n\nWorkshops on photography, printmaking, caricature, beginner\'s airbrush, and body casting will be conducted two weeks before the Fine Arts week proper in order to allow the active participation of students, staff and faculty members. The registration of the different workshops is from January 15 to February 2, 2001. \n\nWe also like to invite you to the Student-Faculty and Connecting Lines Exhibits, wherein artworks of students, faculty members and guest artists are displayed and opt for sale.\n\nEnclosed in this letter is the Calendar of Activities. Please do not hesitate to get in touch wih us for more information, through the following people : \nJoseph Vergel - (0919) 5652858\nMarielle Nadal - (0917)9779213\nProf. Pete Castaneda / Prof. Mitzi Aguilar- Reyes -43448222\nProf. John Santos -4347981\n\nWe look forward in celebrating with you our Fine Arts Week 2001. Thank you very much.\n\nSincerely yours, \n\nJOSEPH VERGEL\nUPCFASC Chairman\n\nMARIELLE NADAL\n2nd Year Batch Representative, Head of Fine Arts Week 2001\n\nNoted by : \n\nProfessor Mitzi Aguilar-Reyes\nUPCFA Student-Faculty Relations Officer\n\nProfessor Leonilo Doloricon\nUPCFA Dean ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1428, 'E2-1428AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2001, January 8)', 'Prof. Edgardo G. Atanacio\nDean - College of Engineering\nUniversity of the Philippines\nDiliman, Quezon City 1101\n\nDear Dean Atanacio,\n\nMapua Tech will hold its 76th Foundation Week this coming January 22-27,2001. The theme of this year\'s affair is Mapua Tech at the Frontiers...at the Frontlines. One of the activities that will be held during this week is the Launching of the Mapua Research Journal, a semi-annual research journal of the Institute. \nThe Mapua Tech will launch the \"Mapua Research Journal\" on the 23rd of January 2001 at 9:30 AM at the Audio Visual Room 2 of Mapua Tech. We are inviting you to grace this very important milestone for the Mapua Institute of Technology. This event will mark the beginning of Mapua Tech\'s reinvention as a Research Institution. \n\nKindly confirm your attendance with Ms. Evelyn Gamboa or Ms. Aida Quinacman through 527-3681 (telefax) or 527-7916 loc. 740.\n\nThank you very much.\n\nYours sincerely, \n\nDr. Bonifacio T. Doma, Jr.\nAssociate Editor, Mapua Research Journal\nDean ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
