(1434, 'E2-1434AC', '', 'Facsimile Advice - Recognition of Donors ', '', '', '', 'I. National Anthem\nII. Welcome Address - Prof. Edgardo G. Atanacio, Acting Dean\nIII. Awarding of Certificates of Recognition to the Graduating Students\nIV. Awarding of Medals to the Honor Students\nV. Presentation of Awards \n1998 Undergraduate Science and Technology Creative Works Competition\nRomago Award for Excellence in Electrical Engineering\nRomago Award for Excellence in Mechanical Engineering\nDominador I. Ilio Award for the Most Outstanding All-Around Graduating Student of the U.P. College of Engineering\nRamon Khu Memorial Award (Class Valedictorian)\nVI. Message from the Representative of the Graduating Students - Mr. Wyant S. Chan \nVII. Recognition of Donors - Dean Alfredo L. Juinio and Engr. Cerlito San Juan\nVIII. Keynote Address (to be introduced by Prof. Edgardo G. Atanacio) - Hon. William G. Padolina\nIX. Introduction of the Graduating Class into the UPAE - Engr. Cerlito San Juan\nX. Hymn : U.P. Naming Mahal ', '', '', '', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1435, 'E2-1435AC', '', 'BPI Science Awards', '', '', '', '', '', '(1998, January 20) ', 'Engr. Edgardo Atanacio\nDean, College of Engineering\nUniversity of the Philippines\nQuezon Hall, Diliman\nQuezon City\n\nDear Engr. Atanacio\n\nGreetings from the Bank of the Philippine Islands!\n\nThis year, we are celebrating the 10th year anniversary of the BPI Science Awards and we would like to express our heartfelt thanks to your university for being our partner in this undertaking. \n\nThe celebration of this milestone in our effort to encourage students to excel in these specialized fields is made more meaningful since it coincides with our commemoration of the centennial year. We, in the Bank of the Philippine Islands, are hopeful that our modest efforts in recognizing the achievements of outstanding students in science and engineering will contribute to our shared task of nation-building. \n\nWe would like to invite you to the 1998 BPI Science Awards ceremonies for UP DIliman on February 11 (Wednesday), 9:00 am at the College of Science Auditorium. The guest of honor during the awards will be Fernando Zobel de Ayala.\nAgain, we express our sincerest appreciation for your cooperation. We look forward to seeing you during the awards rites and to working with you again for the continued success of the BPI Science Awards. \n\nVery truly yours, \n\nVERONICA L. TAPIA\nVice President\nBPI Corporate Communications and BPI Foundation, Inc. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1436, 'E2-1436AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1998, January 27) ', 'Dean Edgardo G. Atanacio\nCollege of Engineering\nUP Diliman\n\nDear Dean Atanacio, \n\nWarm Greetings!\n\nThe University Center for Women\'s Studies is co-sponsoring with the National Centennial Commission-Women Sector and the Women\'s Studies Association of the Philippines the National Symposium on \"History Makes Women/Women Make Herstory\" on March 9-10, 1998 at the Bahay ng Alumni. This is in collaboration with the Department of History, CSSP and the Women and Development Program of CSWCD.\n\nThe objectives of the National Symposium are : \n\n- To examine the critical issues stemming from the gender-blindness of Philippine historiography;\n- To provide an alternative framework for viewing women\'s roles and contributions in the making of Philippine history; \n- To explore various feminist methodologies, including historiography, in the weaving of a Philippine \'herstory\";\n- To attempt a feminist reconstruction of Philippine history (focusing on the centennial);\n- To encourage the making of regional/local \"herstories\" in tandem with the national one;\n- To showcase women\'s historical creativity through exhibits, cultural presentations, and bazaars; and\n- To orient and prepare the participants for the forthcoming international conference in December 1998. \n\nWe cordially invite you and the members of the faculty to participate in this historic affair. Enclosed is the symposium brochure which describes various activities you may be interested to join. \n\nThe symposium can accomodate only 500 participants. We will therefore register participants on a \"first come, first served\" basis. \n\nPlease address all inquiries and communications to the University Center for Women\'s Studies at UP Diliman. Our telephone numbers are 920-68-80 and 920-53-01 local 4931. Esel Laxa-Panlaqui or Wanet Lacsamana will gladly take your call. \n\nVery truly yours, \n\nSYLVIA H. GUERRERO\nDirector ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
