(1447, 'E2-1447AC', '', '1999 BPI Science Awards\nAwarding Ceremonies ', '', '', '', 'I. Invocation\nII. Pambansang Awit\nIII. Welcome Address\nIV. Opening Remarks\nV. Messages\nVI. Presentation of Awards and Unveiling of the Roster of BPI Science Awardees\nVII. Intermission Number\nVIII. Introduction of Awardees and Project Demonstration\nIX. Response\nX. Closing Remarks\nXI. Reception', '', '', 'The BPI Science Awards\nShaping the future through science\n\nThe Bank of the Philippine Islands (BPI) believes that the Development of Science and Technology is vital in the advancement of any country.\n\nAlong this line, BPI, through its Foundation, has created a program geared to recognize young men and women from all over the Philippines who excel in the specialized fields of science. Conceived in 1989, the Annual BPI Science Awards serve as encouragement for budding scientists and researchers to strive towards helping the country make technological breakthroughs. \n\nPHILOSOPHY\n\nScience and Technology are the real engines of progress. History and experiences point to the fact that the modern world is shaped by advances in these fields. Outstanding science students are worthy of recognition in view of their potential contributions to industry and nation building. \n\nOBJECTIVE\n\nThe objective of the awards is to recognize and give incentives to students who excel in specialized fields of science, namely, Mathematics, Physics, Engineering, Chemistry, Biology and Computer Science. An awardee must have consistent scholarly academic records in his chosen field and must be recommended by the school. \n\nPARTICIPATING SCHOOLS \n\nThe awards are given to the top 3 junior and senior students of the following universities : \n- Ateneo de Davao University\n- Ateneo de Manila University\n- De La Salle University\n- Silliman University\n- St. Louis University Baguio\n- University of the Philippines Diliman\n- University of the Philippines Los Baños\n- University of San Carlos\n- University of Santo Tomas\n- Xavier University \n', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1448, 'E2-1448AC', '', 'Seventeenth Scholars\' Recognition Convocation', '', '', 'Wednesday, February 3, 1999\n3:00 p.m.\nMalcolm Hall, College of Law\nUniversity of the Philippines\nDiliman, Quezon City ', 'Programme\nProcessional\nEntrance of Colors\nPambansang Awit\nReading of Citation and Presentation of Awards\nResponse from Awardees\nMusical Number\nIntroduction of the Guest Speaker\nInspirational Message\nClosing Remarks\nU.P. Naming Mahal\nExit of Colors ', '', '', 'Background\nTo participate in the 1983 observance of the Diamond Jubilee of the University of the Philippines and to celebrate the Golden Anniversary of its founding, the U.P. Chapters of the Honor Society of Phi Kappa Phi extended an invitation to the U.P. Chapters of Pi Gamma Mu International Social Science Honor Society and Phi Sigma Biological Honor Society to sponsor a joint activity on campus. \nThe first cooperative effort was a convocation honoring outstanding senior held January 21, 1983 at Malcolm Hall, College of Law. This was envisioned to become a regular annual undertaking.\nIt is hoped that recognition of exemplary seniors will help achieve the objectives of these societies, encourage the awardees to continue to strive for excellence in all their endeavors, and serve as inspiration for emulation by other students. \nPI GAMMA MU\nThe International Social Science Honor Society\n- The International Honor Society of Pi Gamma Mu is a non-profit corporation organized to promote social science. it was founded in 1924 by Dean Leroy Allen of Southwestern College and Dean William A. Hamilton of the College of William and Mary. It has more than 160 active chapters worldwide. \n- The Philippines Alpha Chapter, the first in Asia, was established in the University of the Philippines on June 27, 1932 with an initial core of 11 members. It celebrated its Golden Jubilee in 1982 and by then its membership had grown to more than 6,000. The honor society counts among its membership the cream of the graduates of the University. \n- The Society\'s motto - COGNOSOCIETIES VERITATEM ET VERITAS VOS LIBERABIT - is translated, \"Ye shall know the truth and the truth shall make you free.\"\n- Pi Gamma Mu endeavors to inspire in its honored members social service to humanity and life interest in the study of human association. It seeks also a synthesis of all branches of social sciences into a philosophy of human society and human welfare. \nTHE HONOR SOCIETY OF PHI KAPPA PHI\nAn International Honor Society\n- The first honor society to recognize superior scholarship in all fields of study and to elect into membership the highest ranking students from all branches of learning. \n- Founded at the University of Maine at Orono in 1897 by three state university presidents to fill the need for an interdisciplinary honor society. \n- Chapter No. 045, established at the University of the Philippines in 1933 by 14 scholarly leaders, four of whom eventually became presidents of the University. \n- The motto of the Society - PHILOSOPHIA KRATEITO PHOTON (\"May the love of learning rule mankind\") - express a goal rather than an accomplishment. \n- The primary objective - the recognition and encouragement of superior scholarship in all academic disciplines, fosters an abiding love of learning. \nPHI SIGMA\nBiological Honor Society\n- Devoted to the promotion of research and academic excellence in the biological sciences. \n- Charges its members to assume leadership in all activities appropriate to a biologist, to maintain high scholarship, to promote active research among its members, and to acquaint others with the results of all worthy achievements in biological fields. \n- Founded at the Ohio State University, Columbus, Ohio, 17 March 1915. \n- Alpha Chi Chapter installed at the University of the Philippines, 12 March 1949; Dr. Herbert E. Warfel, installing officer, with officers and members drawn from the U.P. Biological Society, College of Arts and Sciences. \n- The society\'s motto - ALETHEIA EK TES GES - is translated, \"Truth shall spring out of the earth and righteousness shall look down from heaven\" (Psalm 85:11)\n- Member, American Association of College Honor Societies and American Institute of Biological Sciences; associate member, American Association for the Advancement of Science.', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
