(1453, 'E2-1453AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, November 17) Partnership between the University of the Philippines and Silicon Graphics Compu', 'Prof. Edgardo Atanacio\nDean - College of Engineering\nUniversity of the Philippines\nMelchor Hall, UP Diliman, Quezon City\n\nDear Sir,\n\nGreetings! With the establishment of the partnership between the University of the Philippines and Silicon Graphics Computer Systems (SGI) through the donation of the Silicon Graphics PowerCHALLENGE XL Supercomputer installed at the UP Computer Center, as the Philippine representatives of SGI, we are currently on a campaign to heighten the awareness and usage of this valuable resource to the various departments and colleges through the university. \n\nIn light of this, we would to schedule a seminar focusing on the usage and application of this resource to your college/department. The seminar will focus on the following aspects : \n- An introduction to the SGI Power CHALLENGE XL\n- What Resources Are Availabel\n- How It Can Be Applied To Your College/Department\n- Advantages of the System\n- How You Can Avail Of This Resource\n\nWe can contact you at your most convenient schedule or you can call us at the following contact information for any inquiries, questions or comments that you may have : \n\nTel. No. : 927-1078, 926-9697, 920-8577\nTele/Fax : 926-9697\nE-Mail : is3@info.com.ph\n\nThank you very much, \n\nSincerely, \n\nMr. Vicente A.V. Lautchang\nPresident/CEO\n\ncc : Mr. Roel M. Ocampo\nDirector / UP Computer Center\n\nDr. Rhodora V. Azanza\nDean - College of Science ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1454, 'E2-1454AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, October 30) Evaluation of colleges and universities in the National Capital Region (NCR) in r', 'Republic of the Phlippines\nOffice of the President of the Philippines\nCOMMISSION ON HIGHER EDUCATION\nNATIONAL CAPITAL REGION AREA\n\nDr. Edgardo Atanacio\nDean, College of Engineering\nUniversity of the Philippines\nDiliman, Quezon City\n\nDear Dr. Atanacio : \nThe Commission on Higher Education (CHED) will conduct an evaluation of colleges and universities in the National Capital Region (NCR) in relation to their application for government authority to operate programs. To undertake this task, the Commission is seeking the assistance of experts from the academe, industry and professional associations. These experts shall be organized as Quality Assessment Teams (QATs) in the different clusters of disciplines. \nIn this regard, since UP is a center of excellence in the field of engineering education, we would like to request for assistance from your institution by allowing some of your faculty to be involved as members of NCR-QAT which will evaluate colleges and universities offering engineering programs. May we request one expert in the field of Electronics and Communication Engineering, one Industrial Engineering, one Electrical Engineering and two Computer Engineering. The conduct of ocular inspection of schools is scheduled starting this November 2000. \nBefore the conduct of inspection (which is about one day per school), they will be provided with the evaluation criteria and instrument be used.\nShould you have any queries, we can be contacted at telephone nos. 3735551 and 3735553 or telefax no. 3735552.\nThank you and we look forward to your positive response. \n\nVery truly yours,\n\nAMELIA A. BIGLETE\nDirector IV', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1455, 'E2-1455AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, November 10) Computation of the costs incurred by the EEE laboratory which is presently house', 'Technology Management Center\nOffice of the Chancellor\nUniversity of the Philippines Diliman\n\nDR. EDGARDO ATANACIO\nDean\nCollege of Engineering\nUP Diliman\n\nThrough : DR. ROWENA GUEVARRA\nChair, Department of EEE\n\nDear Dean Atanacio, \n\nEnclosed please find our computation of the costs incurred by the EEE laboratory which is presently housed at the UP TMC.\n\nWe propose that the College of Engineering shoulder two (2) of TMC\'s monthly electricity bills this year. This will likely result in a credit balance in your favor which we can apply to the lab\'s costs next year. \n\nIn any case, you may need this information in view of the fact that each unit is being requested to obligate its funds by 15 November.\n\nPlease tell us if the foregoing is acceptable. \n\nThank you. Warmest regards. \n\nTruly yours, \n\nHELEN S. VALDERRAMA\nDirector ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1456, 'E2-1456AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, October 5) Requestion permission to submit the following parameters ', 'UNIVERSITY OF THE PHILIPPINES\nDiliman, Quezon City 1101\n\nDr. Emerlinda R. Roman\nChancellor\nUniversity of the Philippines Diliman\nDiliman, Quezon City\n\nThrough : Dr. Amelia P. Guevara, Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs \n\nDear Chan. Roman :\nAfter due consultation with the departments, we are requesting permissions to submit the following parameters to the Office of Admission for use in deciding the admission to our college starting Academic Year 2001-2002:\n\nBS Program\nChemical Engineering\nCivil Engineering\nComputer Engineering\nComputer Science\nElectrical Engineering\nElectronics and Communications Engineering\nGeodetic Engineering\nIndustrial Engineering\nMaterials Engineering\nMechanical Engineering\nMetallurgical Engineering\nMining Engineering\n\nThank you. \n\nVery truly yours, \n\nEDGARDO G. ATANACIO\nDean ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1457, 'E2-1457AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, October 10) ', 'College of Engineering Library\nUniversity of the Philippines Diliman\n\nProf. Edgardgo G. Atanacio\nDean, College of Engineering\nU.P. Diliman, Quezon City 1101\n\nDear Dean Atanacio : \nWe would like to endorse the appeal of Mr. Ranilo G. Salustiano to transfer to NEC (National Engineering Center) which he has reiterated several times. \n\nMr. Salustiano, then Utility Worker II (SG 3), was transferred, vice Mrs. Elsie Opinaldo, from the NEC (National Engineering Center) to the College of Engineering Library on January 11, 1993 during the incumbency of Dean Francisco L. Viray. With our recommendation, he was promoted to Clerk III in August of the same year. The U.P. Administrative Committee awarded him a Vocational Fellowship for academic year 1993-94 while he was working with the Library. In 1997, we accommodated his request to go on study leave to finish the B.S. Secondary Education major in Math which he did under the Scholarship Program of the Civil Service Commission. On the same year, from Clerk III (SG 6), he was promoted to Data Entry Machine Operator II (SG 8). \n\nDespite our consistent efforts to help him upgrade his educational qualification and job position as well as to train him in library work, we are releasing him from his library responsibility in order to facilitate his projected transfer. \n\nWith the possibility of the transfer of Mr. Salustiano, we would like to request for Mrs. Elsie Opinaldo, who holds a master\'s degree in Library Science, as a replacement for him. We anticipate a favorable consideration of this request. \n\nVery truly yours, \n\nYOLANDA C. GRANDA\nHead College Librarian\n\nc: Ranilo G. Salustiano, DEMO II', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1458, 'E2-1458AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, October 5) ', 'Office of the Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs\n\nDEAN EDGARDO G. ATANACIO\nCollege of Engineering\nUniversity of the Philippines\nDiliman, Quezon City\n\nDear Dean Atanacio :\n\nThe Academic Personnel and Fellowships Committee (APFC) during its meeting held on September 27, 2000 deliberated on your recommendation for the automatic promotion of MR. ANDRE PUBLICO from Associate Professor I to Associate Professor 4 effective upon approval.\n\nThe Committee deferred ation on your recommendation and would like to request for an updated curriculum vitae, list of researches and publications for the past 5 years, an assessment of his overall teaching effectiveness, (please refer to Memo No. ERR-115 copy attached) and other proofs of merit as basis for Dr. Publico\'s automatic merit promotion to Associate Professor 4. The BOR approved guidelines on automatic promotion states that faculty members already having the rank of Associate Professor when they started their PhD degree shall be given rank promotion or salary increases on their respective merits. \n\nPlease send us the above documents soonest so that we can process his appointment accordingly. Thank you. \n\nTruly yours, \n\nAMELIA P. GUEVARA\nChairperson, APFC ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1459, 'E2-1459AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, August 7)', 'Office of the Chancellor\n\nMEMORANDUM NO. ERR-115\n\nTO : Deans and Heads of Units\n\nSUBJECT : Inclusion of Updated Bio-Data and List of Researches/Publications (last 5 years) with 2 copies of Latest Picture (2x) in the Recommendations for Tenure of Faculty\n\nIn order for the Academic Personnel and Fellowships Committee (APFC) to assess carefully and objectively recommendations for tenure for faculty, please include an updated bio-data of each, indicating researches/publications for the last 5 years, an assessment of the overall teaching effectiveness of each of the faculty and 2 copies of latest picture (size 2x2).\nFor strict compliance. \n\nEMERLINDA R. ROMAN\nChancellor ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1460, 'E2-1460AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, October 3) ', 'Dear Dr. Roman,\nI wish to request your agreement to the temporary release of Dr. Genandrialine Peralta, Faculty-in-Charge, Environmental Engineering Program of the University of the Philippines, to serve as consultant in Beijing, China from 9 October to 8 December (Phase 1) and 12 November to 7 December 2000 (Phase 2). The terms of reference are as follows : \nPhase No. 1 \n(1) to collaborate with the the local study team and international experts in the analysis and interpretation, and reporting of data on environmental quality and health impacts for the project on environment and people\'s health in China; \n(2) to collaborate with the WR in implementing the project, particularly the technical aspects of the project, and facilitate communication with the Regional Office Manila on the progress of the project; \n(3) to explore future collaborative activities with relevant authorities in China in the area of assessment of environmental health impacts and risks; and \n(4) to prepare a report at the end of the assignment\nPhase No. 2\nTo continue on with the same terms of reference as in Phase 1. The World Health Organization will be responsible for travel costs, salary and daily subsistence allowance for the duration of the assignement, including travel time. \nYour kind consideration of this request and your early reply would be appreciated.\n\nYours sincerely, \n\nShigeru Omi, MD, Ph. D. \nRegional Director ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1461, 'E2-1461AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, October 26) ', 'University of the Philippines\nOffice of the Vice-Chancellor for Student Affairs\nOFFICE OF SCHOLARSHIPS AND STUDENT SERVICES\nRms. 301 to 306, 3rd Floor, Vinzons Hall\nDiliman, Quezon City\n\nProf. Edgardo G. Atanacio\nDean, College of Engineering\nU.P. Diliman\n\nDear Prof. Atanacio : \nThis is to acknowledge your recommendation for the award of UPERDFI-sponsored scholarships to the students listed opposite each grant. Please note our comments on each recommendee : \nName\nCuison, Manuel Jr. P.\nDCCD Scholarship\nFernandez, Flenn Fiel\nAntonio Tan Scholarship\nFuentes, Marizanne O. \nAsia Indusries Scholarship \nGangan, Eman John P. \nUP Engineering Class \'35 Scholarship\nLegaspi, Sarah Jane L. \nPilipinas Shell Scholarship\nLucas, Anna Marie L. \nPantabangan Dam Scholarship\nMagtuba, Helen M. \nPhilips Group of Companies Scholarship\nParfan, Ronald Derick P. \nTransport Training Center Scholarship\nParreno, Kristina\nAsia Industries Scholarship\nTalampas, Cherryl Ann R.\nAlfredo Junio Scholarship\nTalubo, Joan Pauline\nAsia Industries Scholarship\nTenorio, Gilybert A.\nAsia Industries Scholarship\nWing, Jeanette A. \nAntonio Miranda Scholarship \n\nVery truly yours, \n\nBELLA M. VILLANUEVA\nChief', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1462, 'E2-1462AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, October 23) Constitution of a Selection Committee for the Gawad Chansellor for Outstanding In', 'University of the Philippines\nDiliman\nQuezon City\n\nOFFICE OF THE CHANCELLOR\n\nMEMORANDUM NO. ERR-165\nFOR : Dean Edgardo G. Atanacio, Chair\nCollege of Engineering\n\nDr. Henry J. Ramos\nCollege of Science\n\nProf. Ferdinand G. Manegdeg\nCollege of Engineering\n\nSUBJECT : CONSTITUTION OF A SELECTION COMMITTEE FOR THE GAWAD CHANSELOR FOR OUTSTANDING INVENTION AND INNOVATION\n\nAs part of the celebration of the Diliman month in February 2001, we will be launching the Gawad Chanselor to recognizing the outstanding accomplishments of our faculty, staff and students. In this regard, please constitute yourselves into an Ad Hoc Committee, with Dean Edgardo G. Atanacio as Chair, to select the OUTSTANDING INVENTION AND INNOVATION OF U.P. DILIMAN. \n\nFirst, Second and Third Prize will be given during the Recognition Ceremony to be held on February 23, 2001. \n\nSpecifically, your committee is tasked with the following :\n1) To review/revise the 1999 guidelines/criteria/forms (please see attached).\n2) To evaluate the qualifications of the nominees based on the revised criteria.\n3) To recommend to the Chancellor the awardees for the OUTSTANDING INVENTIONS AND INNOVATIONS through the Office of the Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs (OVCAA). \n4) To prepare a draft of the citation for the awardees.\n5) To submit committee report by accomplishing the appropriate forms. These forms will be sent to you later. \n\nAlso, during your committee meetings/deliberations, snacks/meals may be ordered from the University Food Service. Kindly just sign the charge slip as Committee chair and indicate the members of your committee. Each committee may enlist the support of one (1) administrative staff who will assist in committee activities. \n\nPlease find attached the timetable which you are enjoined to observe. \n\nIf you have any further questions, you may get in touch with : \n\nDr. Amelia P. Guevara\nVice-Chancellor for Academic Affairs\nChair of the Committee on Gawad Chanselor\nTel. no. 928-28-89 or Local 4820\n\nThank you very much for your cooperation.\n\nEMERLINDA R. ROMAN\nChancellor ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1463, 'E2-1463AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Gawad Chanselor Schedule of Activities', 'Finalization of membership of sub-committees - October 19, 2000\nAppointment of committee members by the Chancellor/Distribution of copies of 1999 guidelines/criteria - October 23, 2000\nDeadline of submission of revised criteria/nomination forms to OVCAA - November 8, 2000\nDistribution of announcement/guidelines/nomination forms - November 15, 2000\nDeadline for submission of nominations for the Gawad nominees to OVCAA - December 15, 2000\nSubmission of Gawad Committee reports to OVCAA - January 30, 2001\nFinal selection of awardees by Chancellor\'s Executive Staff - February 5/8, 2001\nAnnouncement of Awardees - February 12, 2001\nEditing of citations & printing of award certificates - February 7 - 20, 2001\nAwarding Ceremony - February 23, 2001 ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49');
