(1464, 'E2-1464AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Nomination Guidelines for Outstanding Invention and Innovation ', 'I. Criteria\na) Novelty/Originality\nNovelty of the idea\nb) Usefulness/Practicality\nUsefulness or practicality of the invention or innovation\nc) Technical Feasibility\nWorkability of the invention or innovation\nd) Commercial feasibility\nPotential marketability of the invention\nII. Guidelines\na) Any invention/innovation done between July 1998 to June 1999 by faculty members, REPS, administrative staff, or students of U.P. Diliman, individually or as a group, may be nominated for this prize. \nb) Nominations must be coursed through the head of unit/organization and submitted to the Office of the Chancellor through the Office of Extension Coordination, 2nd Floor, Quezon Hall with the following :\n1) Nomination letter addressed to the Chancellor of U.P. Diliman\n2) Description and relevant information about the work being nominated\n3) Justification for the nomination in terms of the competition criteria\n4) Inventor\'s curriculum vitae\n5) Photographs and pertinent documents, if any\nc) Deadline for submission of entries will be on Thursday, September 30, 1999 5:00 pm. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1465, 'E2-1465AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, October 2) ', 'Prof. Edgardo G. Atanacio\nDean\nCollege of Engineering\nUniversity of the Philippines Diliman\n\nDear Dean Atanacio, \n\nI would like to request funding to undertake a teaching effectiveness course for new faculty of the College of Engineering. I have made arrangements with the Office of Director for Instruction to conduct the training course exclusively for engineering faculty. \n\nThe budget for this undertaking is estimated at one hundred twenty five thousand pesos (P125,000.00) to cover cost for honoraria of speakers, food and documentation. A total of 34 new faculty are expected to participate in this course which is planned for five consecutive Saturdays commencing October 28, 2000. \n\nYours sincerely, \n\nProf. Florencio C. Ballesteros, Jr. \nChairman\nCollege Committee on Instruction ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1466, 'E2-1466AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Proposal on Teaching Effectiveness Course for Engineering Faculty \nSeptember 29, 2000', 'Target Date : 5 Saturdays commencing October 28, 2000\nCourse Philosophy :\n\nThis course is based upon the philosophy that : good teaching practices can be taught and can be learned, i.e., a \"real\" academic scholar is both a good teacher and a good researcher; in a competitive marketplace, those who demonstrate the ability to cogently represent their research and the research in the field (the same skills of a good teacher), will be the favored candidate for the future professorate; teacher and student both, have a responsibility to provide an optimal learning environment; the current research on, and philosophies of, teaching and learning can be translated into sound practice; students and individuals, can profoundly influence the success of the classroom experience; and faculty from all disciplines have something of value with which to engage in dialogues for learning; and that close collaboration with the discipline is essential for effectively learning teaching skills that match the language and culture of the discipline. \n\nCourse Goals:\n\nCollege and university professors traditionally have been better prepared in their content area than the practice of teaching. With sound practice and the current, competitive marketplace in mind, this course is designed to assist future applicants to the professorate to : \n\n- Cogently represent their research, the research in the field, and their content (the same skills required of a good teacher), thus being the favored candidate for the professorate;\n- Combine their content knowledge with the theory and practice of sound teaching; \n- Acquire an advanced level of skill and understanding of the philosophy and practice of teaching and learning in the college and university setting; and \n- Carry this skill and understanding to every campus on which they have teaching appointments, becoming advocates for the advancement of good teaching. \n\nCourse Objective : \nThrough classroom discussions, assignments, and exercises, students will be able to demonstrate:\n\n- Familiarity with the diversity of the individuals, i.e., the faculty and student population, student development and student learning; \n- A skill level and knowledge of a number of instructional methods\n- A skill level and knowledge of organizational skills and classroom management\n- Familiarity with resources and technology available to enhance teaching and learning; \n- Personal philosophy of teaching and scholarship;\n- Familiarity with the role of the faculty member in the university and college setting\n\nTeaching and Learning Strategies :\nThe underlying philosophies for teaching and learning in this course include active learning, critical reflection and experiential learning. A variety of instructional methods including lecture, teamwork, class discussion and interaction, guest speakers, reflective writing and reading, video, technology and the internet will be used to model good teaching practice. The participants will have the opportunity to practice and reflect on the course material and class discussions in a real setting, that is, experiential learning. \n\nCourse Syllabus: \n1. Introduction to the Course\n- Individual introductions and expectations\n- The syllabus - course policy and practices\n- Assigning teams for facilitation of weekly discussions\n\n2. The College Student\n- Student Development\n- Learning styles and knowledge acquisition\n- Motivation\n\n3. What makes a good teacher?\n- What makes a good teacher?\n- The first day of class\n- Diversity in the classroom\n\n4. Instructional Methods\n- Active learning\n- Lecturing\n- Teams\n- Discussions\n- -Questioning\n- -Case study\n- -Laboratory games\n- -Role play\n- -Simulation\n- Writing and reading \n-- Experiential learning\n-- Individual instruction\n-- Field trips, study tours\n\n5. Organizational skills\n- Being prepared\n- The syllabus\n- Time management\n\n6. Ethics\n7. Classroom management\n--Academic integrity\n--Discipline and problem situation\n\n8. Evaluation of teaching\n-- Instructor and course evaluation\n-- Feedback\n-- Teaching Portfolio\n\n9. Testing and Grading\n-- Learning assessments formats\n-- Grading\n\n10. The faculty role\n-- Teaching, Tenure and Promotion\n-- Research and teaching connection\n-- Guest : Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs or the Chancellor herself\n-- Responsibilities outside the classroom\n-- Mentoring\n\n11. Teaching Resources\n-- Teaching tools, media and technology\n-- The internet\n-- Campus and community services\n\n12. Course wrap-up\n-- Feedback\n-- Dialogue about the course\n-- Course and instructor evaluation\n\nBudget : \nThe budget for this activity is estimated at one hundred twenty five thousand pesos (P115,000) broken down as follows : \nHonoraria for resources speakers \nP1000/hr X 8 hr/day x 5 days    P40,000\nLunch and Snacks\nP200/pax X 40 pax                      P80,000\nPhotocopying/Documentation       5,000\nTOTAL                                            P125,000', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1467, 'E2-1467AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Expected Participants', '1. Avestro, Joyce\n2. Bermejo, Ronald\n3. Blanco, Ariel\n4. Celzo, Ma. Penafrancia\n5. Dapit, Marcelo III\n6. De Guzman, Oliver\n7. Dela Fuente, Rogel\n8. Denoga, Gay Marie\n9. Denoga, Gerald\n10. Dimaculangan, Benjie\n11. Dizon, Michael Butch\n12. Figueroa, Emilio III\n13. Garcia, Romeo, Jr. \n14. Gotauco, Brian\n15. Gonzales, Christine\n16. Hizon, John Richard\n17. Ibabao, Jhoana\n18. Macatulad, Ma. Lourdes\n19. Malquisto, Bienvenido Jr. \n20. Manauis, Melissa\n21. Napolis, Michelle\n22. Padilla, Gilba Joy\n23. Ramos, Norman\n24. Rodriguez, Samuel\n25. Romanes, Maia\n26. Santos, Jose Carlos\n27. Sotto, Rommelyn\n28. Tabat, Franco\n29. Tan, Honee Lyn\n30. Tianco, Beatriz Estela\n31. Toledo, Nikholas\n32. Uy, Roberto\n33. Vasquez, Magdaleno\n34. Villacorta, Rachel ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1468, 'E2-1468AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, October 3) ', 'Dean EDGARDO G. ATANACIO\nCollege of Engineering\nU.P. Diliman, Quezon City\n\nDear Sir : \n\nI am making my request anew to report back to NEC where my original appointment belong. I believe that you agree with me Sir if I may trace it back to the days of Project Development Office wherein its composition includes Mr. Eugene Gonzales, Mr. Nestor Raneses, Miss Aura Castillo and our present dean of the college.\nI am making this request because of my present working condition is not ergonomically sound. At present I am using computer without mouse using only keyboards and what aggravated the condition is that my only means access to HP Laser Jet Printer through sharing with Mrs. Israel has just been terminated this morning by rearranging office desk. The present ratio of 1:1 has just been reduced to 5:1 where I have to compete with students using IEEE CD ROM. All these things despite having a position of Data Entry Machine Operator II where the bulk of my manhours is use for voucher preparation on SA payrolls and reimbursements. \nLastly, I will not be an intellectual handicap to NEC considering that I am a graduate of B.S. Education with professional teacher license no. 0595398. Pertinent to this may I also mention the fact that no less than Mrs. Aura Matias acceded to the fact of my return to NEC.\nSir, you being an Industrial Engineer you value the significance of psychological make-up as an essential factor in a productive output of personnel. But the present behavior of the students deter it so. The Theory of X and Y in management I believe should be apply to my particular case.\nSir, I shall thank you for your humane approach to my predicament. \n\nRespectfully yours, \n\nMr. Ronilo G. Salustiano', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1469, 'E2-1469AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, September 25) ', 'Dean Edgardo G. Atanacio\nCollege of Engineering\nU.P. Diliman\n\nThrough : Prof. Jonathan D. L. Salvacion\nProf. Florencio C. Ballesteros Jr. \n\nDear Dean Atanacio :\n\nThe Office of the Director of Instruction (ODI) under the Office of the Vice Chancellor for Academic Affairs (OVCAA), in consortium with your faculty members in a committee to review the SET for laboratory courses, is most pleased to finally submit to you a copy of the improved SET instrument for laboratory courses.\nIn this connection, may we request permission to field test the instrument anytime between today till the end of the semester. \nThank you for your cooperation.\n\nSincerely, \n\nCelia T. Adriano\nDirector ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1470, 'E2-1470AC', '  ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, September 22) ', 'Prof. Edgardo G. Atanacio\nDean\nU.P. College of Engineering\n\nSir : \n\nI would like to request for the release of FRIA funds for the allowances and honoraria of the project researchers and the acquisition of supplies, devices and equipment necessary for approved project entitled \"Two-Channel Multiplexed Signals Over a 2.375 GHz Wireless Link\" of Randy C. Barsatan, Rolando C. Guevarra and Dr. Delfin Jay Sabido IX.\nThe total fund costs P80,000.00. The breakdown is as follows : \n\nAllowances\nProject Leader (P5,000 x 5 months) : P25,000.00\n2 Student Assistants (P2,500 x 5 months x 2) : P25,000.00\nFabrication : P10,000.00\nSupplies and Materials : P20,000.00\n\nI hope to hear from you soon regarding this matter because we need these additional funding to proceed with the next phase of the aforementioned project. \n\nThank you very much for your time and attention. \n\nRespectfully yours,\n\nNikholas G. Toledo\nProject Adviser\nElectrical and Electronics Engineering Department\n\nNoted by : \n\nRowena Cristina L. Guevara, Ph.D.\nDepartment of Chairperson\nElectrical and Electronics Engineering Department', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1471, 'E2-1471AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, August 31) ', 'University of the Philippines\nQuezon City\n\nExcerpt from the Minutes of the 1144th Meeting of the Board of Regents held on 31 August 2000 \n\nIX. Matters for Confirmation of the Board\n\nThe Board DEFERRED action on the following, pending clarification of the provision in the Memorandum of Agreement as specifically stated in letter a below.\n\nThe Board would like to find out if this includes appointment of UP faculty/academic personnel to administrative positions at Mapua. \n\nA. Memorandum of Agreement entered into by and between U.P. Diliman and the Mapua Institute of Technology (MIT).\n\nProject : Faculty Exchange \n\nParticulars : \n\na. Upon request of Mapua Institute of Technology, U.P. Diliman shall permit its faculty from the College of Engineering, College of Education, and other colleges as may be needed, to serve at MIT on a part-time basis in such capacity as may be requested by them and subject to the rules and procedures agreed upon. (underscoring ours)\nb. Faculty members of U.P. Diliman serving at MIT shall be given reasonable compensation by the latter institution, in accordance with its salary administration plan, policies and rules; provided that faculty members and/or academic personnel given teaching assignments at MIT shall be appointed threat to a rank equivalent to that held by said faculty member and/or academic personnel in U.P. Diliman. \n\nDuration : From 15 June 2000 to 14 June 2003\n\nDate Signed : 10 June 2000\n\nCERTIFIED CORRECT : \n\nMARTIN V. GREGORIO\nSecretary of the University and of the Board of Regents ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1472, 'E2-1472AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'MEMORANDUM OF AGREEMENT\n\nKNOW ALL MEN BY THESE PRESENTS :\n\nThis Memorandum of Agreement, made and entered into this 10th day of June, 2000 at Diliman, Quezon City, Philippines, by and between :\n\nThe UNIVERSITY OF THE PHILIPPINES DILIMAN, a State Institution of higher learning, created and operating pursuant to Act. 1870, as amended, with principal office at Quezon Hall, U.P. Campus, Diliman, Quezon City, herein represented by its Chancellor, DR. EMERLINDA R. ROMAN, hereinafter referred to as \"U.P. DILIMAN\";\nand\nMAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY, a private non-sectarian institution, organized and operating in accordance with laws of the Republic of the Philippines, with principal office at Muralla St., Intramuros, Manila, herein represented by its President, DR. REYNALDO B. VEA., hereafter referred to as \"MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY\".\n\nWITNESSETH : that\n\nWHEREAS, one of the current thrusts of UP DILIMAN is to provide advanced instruction in engineering and to give professional and technical training to deserve students of the country;\n\nWHEREAS, MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY is a private non-sectarian educational institution founded more than 75 years ago by Don Tomas Mapua;\n\nWHEREAS, it is a policy of U.P. DILIMAN to extend assistance, consistent with its purpose and without prejudice to its needs and programs, to other institutions of learning in order to further the interests of higher education in the Philippines; \n\nWHEREAS, the current thrust of MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY is consistent with U.P. DILIMAN\'s mission of helping attain quality education; \n\nWHEREAS, MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY desires and seeks assistance from U.P. DILIMAN;\n\nWHEREAS, U.P. DILIMAN has faculty members and/or academic personnel who possess the necessary qualification and are willing to undertake services for the assistance sought; \n\nNOW, THEREFORE, for and in consideration of the foregoing premises, the parties hereto hereby agree as follows :\n\n1. On request by MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY, U.P. DILIMAN shall permit its faculty member and/or academic personnel from the College of Engineering, College of Education, and other colleges as may be needed, to serve in the former on a part-time basis in such capacity as may be requested by MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY, and subject to the rules and procedures stipulated in Annex \"A\" which is made an integral part hereof. \n\n2. Faculty members and/or academic personnel of U.P. DILIMAN serving in MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY shall be given reasonable compensation by the latter institution, in accordance with its salary administration plan, policies and rules; Provided that, the faculty membre and/or academic personnel given teaching assignments at MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY shall be appointed thereat to a rank equivalent to that held by said faculty member and/or academic personnel in U.P. DILIMAN.\n\n3. MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY shall furnish U.P. DILIMAN and the college where the faculty/staff belongs with a copy of the appointment issued, or contract of employment executed, as the case may be, for each faculty member and/or academic personnel.\n\n4. As needed by, and on request of, U.P. DILIMAN, MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY shall permit its faculty member and other academic personnel to serve in the former on a part-time basis with compensation as may be agreed upon by both parties, in such capacity as may be desired by U.P. DILIMAN.\n\n5. All Dean, Directors and Heads of other principal units of U.P. DILIMAN and MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY shall be informed of this Agreement in its entirety; Provided that, faculty members and/or academic personnel whose services are sought shall be apprised of this Agreement before their written consent is required. \n\n6. Only Graduate Students of MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY shall have access to U.P. DILIMAN library facilities, subject to U.P. DILIMAN\'s library rules and regulations. The library shall be open to the Graduate Students only on Wednesdays, for room use only, upon presentation of a referral letter from the MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY librarian, and a valid ID from said students. \n\n7. It is understood that the activities enumerated herein shall be decided through consultation with the concerned U.P. DILIMAN college/unit, and that the assistance extended to MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY by U.P. DILIMAN shall be subject to the availability of faculty members and/or academic personnel and other resources. \n\n8. This Agreement shall be deemed modified accordingly insofar as it may be affected by new policies, rules and procedures or amendments to existing ones that may be adopted by either institution, provided that the other institution shall be notified thereof within thirty (30) days from its issuance. \n\n9. This Agreement shall be effective upon completion of the signatures of both parties and shall remain in full force and effect for a period of three (3) years beginning 15 June 2000 to 14 June 2003, unless terminated by mutual consent or as the exigencies of the services in either institution may require; Provided that, in the latter instance, the party initiating termination hereof shall notify the other at least thirty (30) days in advance in order that pending programs are not prejudiced. \n\n10. This Agreement may be renewed or amended for such period and under such terms and conditions mutually agreed upon by the parties in writing. \n\nIN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have hereunto set their hands on the date and at the place first above written. \n\nUNIVERSITY OF THE PHILIPPINES DILIMAN\nby : DR. EMERLINDA R. ROMAN\nChancellor\n\nMAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY\nby : DR. REYNALDO B. VEA\nPresident\n\nSIGNED IN THE PRESENCE OF : \nDR. AMELIA P. GUEVARA\nVice-Chancellor for Academic Affairs\n\nDR. CONSUELO V. FLORA\nVice-President for Academic Affairs ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1473, 'E2-1473AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'ACKNOWLEDGMENT\n\nREPUBLIC OF THE PHILIPPINES\nQuezon City\n\nBEFORE ME, a Notary Public for and in Quezon City, this 21st day of June 2000, personally appeared :\n\nNAME \nEMERLINDA R. ROMAN\nDR. REYNALDO B. VEA\nknown to me and to me known to be the same persons who executed the foregoing instrument and acknowledged to me that the same is their free and voluntary act and deed and that of the institutions they respectively represent. \n\nThis instrument, consisting of six (6) pages, including this page whereon this Acknowledgment in written and Annex \"A\" hereof, refers to a Memorandum of Agreement signed by the parties together with their instrumental witnesses on each and every page thereof. \n\nWITNESS MY HAND AND SEAL on the date place above written.', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1474, 'E2-1474AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Rules and procedures to govern the involvement of members of the faculty of the U.P. Diliman in Mapu', 'A. RULES\nThe following Rules shall govern the involvement of members of the faculty of U.P. Diliman in MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY and the faculty of MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY in U.P. Diliman without prejudice to such other rules as may be promulgated as the need arises : \n1. Specific authorization in each case from the Office of the Chancellor of U.P. Diliman is required before a faculty member may teach in MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY. \n2. Each authorization shall be for a period not exceeding one (1) semester, exclusive of any renewal which shall in no case go beyond the term of the Memorandum of Agreement. \n3. The maximum permissible load of a faculty member who will teach in MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY shall not exceed six (6) units (i.e. course credits) per semester.\n4. Service in MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY shall be rendered outside the regular office hours of the faculty member in U.P. DILIMAN.\n5. It is to be understood that the involvement of a faculty member in MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY shall not interfere with or prejudice his or her regular and other responsibilities, ongoing projects or programs. Corollary to this, therefore, the permission granted may be withdrawn by the Office of the Chancellor of U.P. DILIMAN if the exigencies of the service so require. An advance notice of at least thirty (30) days shall be served to MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY before such a withdrawal shall take effect. \n6. No authorization shall be issued without the occurence of the dean and department chairperson concerned and the written consent of the faculty member whose services are being requested. \nB. PROCEDURES\nThe following procedures shall be followed in the processing of requests (initial or renewal) for services of faculty members of U.P. DILIMAN.\nStep 1 - MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY prepares the request for services addressed to the Chancellor of U.P. DILIMAN through channels, specifying, among other things, the following : \na. Name of faculty member whose services are sought;\nb. Nature of projected assignment or involvement, including course title and number of units;\nc. Projected service hours; and \nd. Approximate duration (i.e. , the inclusive dates) of projected assignment \nThe requests should be forwarded directly to the Chancellor of U.P. Diliman or the department where the faculty member belongs. The request should be submitted at least thirty (30) days in advance. \nStep 2 - Chairperson of Department - With the needs of the service in mind, the Chairman endorses the request, together with the written consent of the faculty member concerned, to the Dean. However, if the chairperson feels the services of the faculty member cannot be made available, he should communicate directly with MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY accordingly and need not forward the request to the Dean. \nStep 3 - Office of the Chancellor - Also with the needs of the service in mind, the Chancellor of U.P. Diliman approves or disapproves the request and subsequently informs MAPUA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY of the action taken. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1475, 'E2-1475AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, March 15) ', 'Office of Extension Coordination\n\nDr. Amelia P. Guevara\nVice-Chancellor for Academic Affairs\nU.P. Diliman\n\nDear Vice-Chancellor Guevara :\n\nAttached are comments/recommendations from the College of Engineering and the University Library regarding the proposed renewal of Memorandum of Agreement with Mapua Institute of Technology (MIT).\n\nThe College of Engineering endorses a renewal of the linkage. The University Library proposes to grant privileges only to graduate students of MIT on Wednesdays, subject to the same library rules/regulations and fees. \n\nFor your consideration. \n\nTruly yours,\n\nCorazon F. Gatchalian\nDirector ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1476, 'E2-1476AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, February 15) ', 'Dr. Emerlinda R. Roman\nChancellor, U.P. Diliman\nDiliman, Quezon City\n\nDear Chancellor Roman : \n\nThis is with reference to the Memorandum of Agreement between U.P. Diliman and the Mapua Institute of Technology (MIT) on faculty exchange and sharing of library facilities. This MOA has been in full force since 15 June 1999 and shall so remain until 14 June 2000.\n\nUnder this MOA, Dr. Jonathan Salvacion of UP has been able to teach at MIT while Prof. Gil Cardiel of MIT has been able to teach at U.P. Needless to say, this has been of mutual advantage to both institutions. \n\nWe believe then that a renewal of the MOA is well justified. To allow for better planning, we suggest that the duration of the MOA be three years instead of one year. \n\nWe hope for your favorable response. \n\nPlease accept my best regards.\n\nVery truly yours,\n\nREYNALDO B. VEA, Ph.D.\nPresident ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1477, 'E2-1477AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, March 8)', 'Dr. Corazon F. Gatchalian\nOffice of Extension Coordination\nUniversity of the Philippines Diliman\n\nDear Dr. Gatchalian, \n\nHerewith are our recommendations regarding the proposed library \"sharing\" arrangements in connection with the renewal of the UP Memorandum of Agreement with Mapua Institute of Technology.\n\nWe will extend Room Use library privilege only to graduate students of Mapua Institute of Technology, on Wednesdays, subject to library rules and regulations (research/equipment fees). We will require a referral letter from the MIT librarian and a valid ID from said students. \n\nVery truly yours, \n\nSALVACION M. ARLANTE\nUniversity Librarian ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1478, 'E2-1478AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, March 8) ', 'Corazon F. Gatchalian, Ph.D.\nDirector, Office of Extension Coordination\n\nSubject : Result of MOA with MIT\n\nDear Dr. Gatchalian;\n\nRespectfully submitting a summary report on what took place as a result of our Memorandum of Agreement with the Mapua Institute of Technology. \n\nVery truly yours, \n\nJonathan L. Salvacion, Dr. Eng.\n\nNoted by : \n\nProfessor Edgardo G. Atanacio\nDean', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1479, 'E2-1479AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, March 10) Summary Report on the Results of the Memorandum of Agreement with the Mapua Institu', 'The original and main intent behind the Memorandum of Agreement with the Mapua Institute of Technology (MIT) was to enable an exchange of faculty members between the U.P. College of Engineering and MIT. It took effect between June 15, 1999 and June 14, 2000. \nAs an immediate result of the MOA, the author was able to teach a graduate course (Advanced Mass Transfer) for one semester following the signing of the MOA. However, no other faculty member of the College is known to have taught in Mapua during that semester up to the present. \nAs a result also of the MOA, problems concerning faculty members of MIT which are enrolled in the Ph.D. program of the U.P. Department of Chemical Engineering were easily resolved. Advising was facilitated because of frequent contacts between faculty members of both sides. Two Ph.D. students whose research projects were discontinued because of the termination of the Engineering and Science Education Program (ESEP) and the second-ment of their U.P. adviser to the DOST were able to change their research direction and/or adviser. Although the direct benefits of this may be seen to accrue mainly on the side of MIT, the main benefits to the U.P. Department of Chemical Engineering is the continuation of research projects led by U.P. faculty members and a new linkage. Indeed, the MOA fostered a much better atmosphere for collaboration between the Departments of Chemical Engineering of both institutions. It is therefore hoped that in the future, a new MOA can be signed extending to joint research projects that can be undertaken between the faculties of U.P. and MIT. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1480, 'E2-1480AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, September 1) ', 'Dean Edgardo Atanacio\nCollege of Engineering\nMelchor Hall\n\nDean, \n\nMay I inquire on follow-up about the possible renewal of my Domingo Toledo Professorial Chair for this next school year? Hope for your consideration. \n\nThanks\n\nRichard \nDepartment of Chemical Engineering ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1481, 'E2-1481AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, August 17)', 'Human Resources Development Office\n\nDean Edgardo G. Atanacio\nCollege of Engineering\n\nDear Dean Atanacio : \n\nIn connection with your inquiry regarding the status of the contractual obligation of Prof. ELSIE M. DAVID, please find attached herewith a chronological summary of the action taken by the Scholarships Section, HRDO.\n\nWe have prepared an initial statement of her contractual obligation amounting to P59,460.75 (without 3M\'s expenses) and furnished the Office of Legal Services a copy from which Atty. Ma. Luisa Felizardo initiated preparation of the demand letter, but since Prof. David opted to execute a Promissory Note, the demand letter did not push through. \n\nHowever, Atty. Felizardo requested HRDO that 3M\'s expenses be included in Prof. David\'s contractual obligation. Mr. David helped us secure the statement of expenses from 3M and a revised contractual obligation statement was prepared amounting to P102,362.47 exclusive of interest. \n\nThe last time we had information about her was when her husband came over to our office and asked for the Promissory Note form for her accomplishment pertinent to her application for a leave of absence without pay from December 19, 1996 until October 31, 1997. Prof. David was furnished a copy of her contractual obligation statement from which she would base the amount for her Promissory Note. This form was supposed to have been returned to us after accomplishment as we gave Mr. David instructions to furnish as a copy after seeing the University Legal Counsel and after notarization of the Promissory Note. We likewise informed the College, through Ms. Remedios Santiago and Mr. Alfonso Julian about these developments since the college was in a better position to communicate with Prof. David. \n\nWe took it to mean therefore, that Prof. David had been making arrangements with the University Legal Counsel regarding the settlement of her contractual obligation. However, when Dr. Jonathan C. Salvacion came over to our Office to inquire about Prof. David\'s status, we learned from the Office of Legal Services, that there was no Promissory Note filed with their office. We have likewise attached a copy of the steps/procedures involved in the normal processing of reneging fellow\'s settlement of his contractual obligation.\n\nSince Prof. David has now been appointed Senior Lecturer in your college, we would appreciate your immediate action to clarify her contractual obligation status. \n\nVery truly yours, \n\nMA. BELINDA V. LOPEZ\nDirector\n\ncc : Dr. Jonathan Salvacion\nDr. Jose C. Muñoz', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1482, 'E2-1482AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Background information on the Resignation case of Prof. Elsie M. David, College of Engineering \n1.) August 28, 1996 - Copy of contractual obligation (w/o sponsor\'s expenses) furnished Office of Legal Services (Attachment A)\n2.) July 31, 1997 - Follow-up copy of contractual obligation (w/o sponsor\'s expenses) furnished Office of Legal Services (Attachment B) \n3.) Oct. 20, 1997 - HRDO received Prof. Munoz\'s resignation letter and accomplishment of University Clearance was required (Attachment C)\n3.) Nov. 11, 1997 - Letter to Prof. David (received by Mr. A Julian, College of Engineering) informing her of the status of her resignation. (Attachment D)\n4) Jan. 27, 1998 - Statement of expenses from University of Minnesota received (Attachment E)\n5) Jan. 28, 1998 - Revised computation of contractual obligation (with donor\'s expenses) furnished OLS and College of Engineering (Attachment F)\nPer information of Ms. Lucy Capones of the Office of Legal Services, they have no record of a Promissory Note filed by Mr. Muñoz, which explains why HRDO does not have a copy on file. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1483, 'E2-1483AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1996, September 9) ', 'MS. LILIA DIMACULANGAN\nHuman Resource Management Officer III\nChief Scholarship Section\nHuman Resource Development Office\n\nDear Ms. Dimaculangan,\n\nIn connection with the demand letters we will be sending to : \n1) Prof. ELSIE M. DAVID \n2) Mr. EDWIN C. ADVERSARIO \nand their respective sureties, may we request for their folders?\n\nThank you for your continued assistance. \n\nMA. LUISA DEL ROSARIO - FELIZARDO\nOfficer-in-charge', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1484, 'E2-1484AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1997, October 20) ', '#5 Adams Street\nFilinvest Homes II\nQuezon City 1126\nOctober 17, 1997\n\nDr. Claro Llaguno \nChancellor\nU.P. Diliman\nDiliman, Quezon City\n\n       Thru Channels\n\nDear Dr. Llaguno : \n\nThis is to tender my resignation from the University of the Philippines effective October 31, 1997.\n\nServing the University for 17 years has been a rare privilege and honor. The U.P. College of Engineering, with its rich intellectual and moral culture, will be a cherished memory.\n\nThis year I begin anew and move on to J.G. Summit Petrochemical Corporation, a Philippine pioneer in Polyethylene polymerization. I join J.G. Summit in proving to the rest of the world that Filipinos can succeed in the high-technology, capital-intensive petrochemical industry. As understudy to the expatriate Technical Manager I am initially responsible for the Technical Services and Quality Assurance Laboratories. Start-up is scheduled for the First Quarter of 1998. \n\nWith regards to the cash equivalent of the unserved part of the teaching contract due to my studies at the University of Minnesota, I would like to request that I be allowed to settle it within two years. This will allow me sufficient time to raise the amount needed. \n\nI thank the University for the generosity and support it extended to me during my years of service. I assure the University that its ideals will always be alive and well in me. \n\nVery truly yours, \n\nELSIE DAVID\n\ncc : Mr. James Go, J.G. Summit\nMr. Wilfredo A. Paras, J.G. Summit', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1485, 'E2-1485AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1997, November 12) ', 'Prof. ELSIE M. DAVID\nCollege of Engineering\nThru the Acting Dean\n\nDear Prof. David : \n\nThis is in connection with your outstanding contractual obligation with the University in the amount of P59,470.75 excluding Interest at the prevailing rate. This amount, however, reflects the total U.P. expenses only and does not include 3M\'s expenses which funded your fellowship. The Promissory Note which you executed will, therefore, have to be changed to reflect the total amount expended by U.P. and your sponsor. This is particularly specified in Item No. 7 of the fellowship contract which you executed with the University, to wit : \n\"7. THE GRANTEE shall reimburse the UNIVERSITY in full such amounts as may have been defrayed for his/her salary, allowances, transportation, and all other expenses incurred by the UNIVERSITY for the Philippine Government) as well as such financial grants as may have been given him/her through of upon endorsement of the UNIVERSITY in connection with his/her scholarship/fellowship/study leave/special detail...\" (underscoring ours). \nThe initial computation of your contractual obligation was made only to facilitate the processing of your leave without pay which is required for you to accomplish the University clearance. But since you have now affirmed your resignation, we are, therefore, including your donor\'s expenses. We have personally communicated with your husband about securing a statement of expenses you incurred from 3M to facilitate immediate processing of your resignation when he came over to submit your Promissory Note. We hope that this information has been relayed to you. We are in fact, up to this moment, waiting for that statement to be able to recompute your total contractual obligation.\nThis letter, therefore, seeks to inform you of the developments re the status of the acceptance of your resignation from the University. Pending receipt of your donor\'s statement of expenses, we cannot act upon your clearance and subsequently, your resignation.\nWe earnestly hope that you will help us secure the necessary document we need to complete the processing of your separation papers. Please find attached a photocopy of Prof. Jose Munoz\'s letter requesting us to communicate with you on the matter. \nWith all good wishes.\n\nVery truly yours, \n\nMA. BELINDA V. LOPEZ\nDirector ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1486, 'E2-1486AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1998, January 14) ', 'The Legal Department\nUniversity of the Philippines\nDiliman, Quezon City\n\nTo Whom It May Concern :\n\nAttached is a memorandum from Ms. Beverly Harren, who is the principal accountant in the Department of Chemical Engineering and Materials Science at the University of Minnesota. It gives the final accounting of the 3M Foreign Fellowship funds paid on behalf of Elsie David. The total of the disbursements if $12, 237.10.\n\nSincerely,\n\nRobert Carr\nProfessor ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1487, 'E2-1487AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Standard Operating Procedures on the Processing of Resignations/Dropping From the Rolls of Fellows with Contractual Obligations \nHRDO :\n1. HRDO (EBRS) receives resignation letter of fellow (with endorsements of the Dean and Department of Chairman), or recommendation from dropping from the rolls. \n2. EBRS checks with the Scholarships Section if the fellow has a contractual obligation. If the resignation letter is unaccompanied by a duty accomplished University clearance, the fellow is requested to submit this requirement before acceptance of the resignation and clearance is granted. \n3. HRDO requests for a statement of actual fellowship expenses incurred from the Accounting Office. \n4. HRDO computes total contractual obligation upon receipt of certified statement of expenses from the Accounting Office. \n5. If there is a donor/sponsoring agency (i.e., Fulbright-PAEF, Colombo Plan, Bilateral Programme, etc.) a statement of expenses is likewise requested from the agency and added to the computation of the contractual obligation statement. \n6. The fellow\'s contractual obligation is indicated on the University clearance form. If there is a contractual obligation, the University Legal Officer will not sign the clearance. \n7. HRDO informs and furnishes the fellow/unit or his appointed representative a copy of the contractual obligation statement and gives instructions to communicate with the Legal Office to facilitate the processing of the fellow\'s clearance papers. \n8. The Legal Office secures the fellow\'s files/records from the HRDO for study and evaluation and preparation of demand letter. \n9. Upon grant of clearance by the University Legal Officer when the fellow has made arrangements to settle his contractual obligation, the resignation paper will be processed by the HRDO and the corresponding notification of acceptance of the resignation will be issued addressed to the fellow, copy furnished the unit through the Dean or Head of Unit. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1488, 'E2-1488AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Office of Legal Services :\n1. The Legal Office secures the fellow\'s fellowship folder from the HRDO for study/evaluation of the case. \n2. Informs the fellow or his representative of the options/mode of payment of the contractual obligation based on 980th BOR ruling, dated August 29, 1985.\n3. Prepares the necessary contract on the manner of payment as indicated in a Memorandum of Undertaking/Promissory Note the fellow is required to execute with the University Legal Office, before the Legal Officer signs the clearance. \n7. The fellow is given instructions to remit payment to the Accounting Office for which he will be given an official receipt acknowledging the payment which is deposited to the Reneging Fellows fund. \n8. OLS furnishes HRDO a copy of the Promissory Note or certification on the necessary arrangements made by the fellow regarding the settlement of his/her contractual obligation.\n9. If neither the fellow nor his sureties could be contacted, the Legal Office will request the Department of Foreign Affairs to put the fellow\'s name on watch for cancellation of his passport if ever he/she is abroad. \n\nHead Unit/College : \n1. The dean/unit head endorses resignation letter or recommendation for dropping from the rolls of the reneging fellow.\n2. Upon receipt of statement of contractual obligation, unit informs the fellow to make arrangements for the settlement of his contractual obligation to facilitate processing of his clearance papers. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1489, 'E2-1489AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2000, March 17)', 'PROF. EDGARDO G. ATANACIO\nExecutive Director\nNational Engineering Center\nU.P. Diliman, Quezon City\n\nDear Sir : \nWe are pleased to submit herewith financial report of the three major accounts of the National Engineering Center with the U.P. Enginerering Research & Development Foundation, Inc. for your review and endorsement to the Foundation. We hope that you find the report in order. \n\nVery truly yours,\n\nAURA C. MATIAS, Ph.D.\nDeputy Executive Director', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1490, 'E2-1490AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(2002, March 15)', 'President\nDr. Francisco Nemenzo\nUniversity of the Philippines\nLos Banos\nCollege 4031 - Engineering\nLaguna\nPhilippinen\n\nFAG Innovation Award 2002 - Announcement\n\nDear Mr. Dr. Nemenzo,\n\nThe FAG Kugelfischer Foundation promotes science, research and teaching in the field of scientific engineering related to bearing technology.\nThe foundation breaches the gap between industry and science by awarding the ideas, visions and goals of those working at the universities, in research and business.\nIn order to achieve this target, the FAG Innovation Award includes prize money at a total of 25,000 euro for the disciplines of Product Innovation, Market Strategy and Enhanced Manufacturing.\nWe kindly ask you to support the FAG Innovation Award through publicity and putting up the enclosed poster.\nYou will find further information about the award and the foundation at the founder\'s homepage under www.fag.com heading Career, Innovation Award. \nThank you very much in advance for your efforts.\n\nYours sincerely,\n\nFAG KUGELFISCHER-STIFTUNG\nThe Management', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1491, 'E2-1491AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FAG INNOVATION AWARD 2002', 'FAG Innovation Award 2002\nFAG KUGELFICHER FOUNDATION\n\nFAG Kugelfischer Georg Schafer AG, one of the world\'s leading rolling bearing manufacturers, established the FAG KUGELFISCHER FOUNDATION on the occasion of its 100th anniversary in 1983.\nIts object is the promotion of science, research and teaching in the field of scientific engineering related to bearing technology.\nWith its foundation, FAG Kugelfisher Georg Schafer AG breaches the gap between industry and science by awarding the ideas, visions and goals of those working at the universities, in research and business.\nIt is the goal of the foundation to promote the innovative potential and support competitive performance.\n\nIn serving its aims, the FAG KUGELFISHER FOUNDATION offers the FAG INNOVATION AWARD for outstanding treatises in the fields of Product Innovation/Enhanced Manufacturing/Market Strategy', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1492, 'E2-1492AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'FAG INNOVATION AWARD 2002', 'FAG INNOVATION AWARD 2002\nFAG KUGELFISCHER FOUNDATION\n\nConditions...Conditions of entry\nTreatises from the fields of Product Innovation, Market Strategy and Enhanced Manufacturing that are related to bearing technology can be submitted. We refer to the enclosed examples of topics. \nThe treatises may have been drawn up by individual natural persons or by teams. In the case of teams consisting of natural persons, the team has to nominate an authorized person to represent the team against FAG KUGELFISCHER FOUNDATION in all actions. \nIf the treatise has been drawn up in the context of a scientific institute, a company or a similar institution, the corresponding consent with the participation in this competition is required. \nThe treatises may be submitted in German or English and should not have been completed more than three years before the application deadine. \nApplications are to be directed to the FAG KUGELFISCHER FOUNDATION by the announced application deadline.\nDocuments...The following documents must be submitted along with an application :\n- Fully completed application form\n- Curriculum vitae\n- Scientific-engineering treatise (in copy)\n- Short description of the treatise contents\n- Expert assessment on the treatise\n- Teams : Authorization\nAddress...The documents should be sent to : \nFAG KUGELFISHER FOUNDATION\nGeorg-Schafer-Strasse 30\nD-97421 Schweinfurt\nThe contents of the submitted treatises will be treated confidentially. The applicant agrees that the submitted treatise be passed on to the founder for inspection and for utilization, should the occasion arise. \nThe foundation and the founder will handle the submitted treatise with care. However no liability will be accepted for its loss, damage or unauthorized usage by third parties.\nThe awarding of prizes will be decided by the foundation committee of the FAG KUGELFISCHER FOUNDATION. The judges\' decision is final.\nWe reserve the right to renounce on the awarding of prizes if no prize-worthy treatise has been handed in. In the case of several equally good treatises, a division of prizes is possible. \nThe conditions of entry are accepted as binding on submitting the application. ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49');
