(1583, 'E2-1583AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1986, December 8) 254th ENGINEERING FACULTY MEETING', '8 December 1986\n\nMEMORANDUM\n\nFor : ALL FACULTY MEMBERS\nCollege of Engineering\n\nSubject : 254th ENGINEERING FACULTY MEETING\n\nFrom : The College Secretary \n\nPlease be informed that the 254th Engineering Faculty Meeting will be held on WEDNESDAY, 10 December 1986, 2:00 p.m. at MH 410 (GE Conference Room). The agenda will be : \n\n(1) Approval of the minutes of the 253th meeting held on October 15, 1986;\n(2) Business arising from the minutes;\n(3) Approval of candidates for graduation as of first semester 1986-87;\n(4) Action on Requests for Change of Grades;\n(5) Other matters.\n\nADOLFO JESUS R. GOPEZ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1584, 'E2-1584AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'MINUTES OF THE 253RD ENGINEERING FACULTY MEETING HELD ON OCTOBER 15, 1986, ROOM 410, MELCHOR HALL ', '(1) The meeting was called to order at 9:25 a.m. with Dean Garcia presiding. \n(2) The minutes of the 252nd Faculty Meeting were approved with the following correction : \nIn Item 7(a) the name \"Leonardo Yabes\" should be corrected to \"Leopoldo Yabes\".\n(3) Business arising from the minutes\na) Mr. J. Ofreneo has no grade yet in EE 81 under Prof. J.A. Azarcon, Jr. Considering the time elapsed since this course finished, Mr. Ofreneo should already have a grade, even an \"INC\". Dr. Pacheco inquired as to what steps should be taken to make sure that the faculty member involved will give Mr. Ofreneo a grade. Dean Garcia replied that he would send a letter to Dr. Azarcon. \nb) The Secretary informed the body that Ms. R.A. Nisperos opted to take Speech I in the summer of 1987. Her request for extension of residence up to the end of summer 1987 has already been approved by the Chancellor, U.P. Diliman. \nc) The Secretary also informed the body that Mr. V. L. Romero, whose request for extension of residence was endorsed by the faculty during the 252nd meeting, is enrolled in Chem 28 in the first semester 1986-87.\nd) The revised graduate courses in Metallurgical Engineering were approved in the last meeting of the University Council. They are now ready for implementation.  \n(4) Abolition and Institution of Some EE Courses\nThe Secretary announced that EE 28 and 29 as presented have been endorsed for approval by the Executive Committee. The action of the Committee was carried out by means of a referendum. These courses will be offered by the EE Department for BCS students and interested EE students. \nProf. R.G. Solis presented the proposal to institute EE 6 and 7 to replace the EE 3, 4, 5 series. He said however that EE 3 will be retained because it best meets the needs of the CE students particularly in wiring requirements. Prof. Solis also presented the proposed EE 28 and 29 courses on computer hardware for BCS students. Prof. Francisco stated that the prerequisite for EE 28 is CS 21, not CS 20 as listed in the proposal. \nThe abolition of EE 4 and 5 and the institution of EE 6 and 7 were approved by the body.\nThe institution of EE 28 and 29 was also approved. Upon suggestion of Dr. J. Bala, these courses will be numbered as EE 8 and 9 respectively. \n(5) Biotechnology and Biochemical Engineering\nDr. Jose presented the proposal to institute three courses : ChE 174, 202 and 294. He informed the body that an ad hoc committee composed of professors from the Colleges of Home Economics, Science, and Engineering, and the Natural Science Research Institute have already discussed these courses. \nWith respect to the two graduate courses being instituted they will form part of the Biochemical Engineering option in the MSChE program. The other option in MSChE is the general Chemical Engineering option which is currently being offered. \nDr. Jose added a footnote to the Biochemical Engineering option which reads : \"Students with insufficient background in biochemistry and microbiology will be required to take Chem 40 and 40.1 and Biology 120 or their equivalents.\" he also stated that since the graduate courses are also intended as elective courses for interested students from the other departments, the footnote applies only to students in the Biochemical Engineering option. \nWhen questioned about possible funding, Dr. Jose replied that this field will be considered as a priority by the PCIERD. \nThe courses were approved for institution. \n(6) Revision of the BS and MS Mechanical Engineering Programs\nDr. Hernandez gave the salient features of the proposed revisions. Dr. Pacheco pointed out that the footnote of the course checklist of the revised program should read : \"May be taken in English or Filipino\".\nThe revisions were approved. \n(7) Revision of the Geodetic Engineering Program \nDr. Marzan discussed the significant features of the proposed revision of the BSGE program. Total number of units will be 181 units, up from 177 units.\nThe section on institution of courses should read \"Institution of Undergraduate Course\" since only one course is being instituted. \nIn response to Dr. Abis\' inquiry regarding Remote Sensing, Dr. Marzan stated that it is being taught as part of Photo-Interpretation. In fact, the title of GE 159, which is the revised GE 59, is now \"Photo-Interpretation and Remote Sensing\".\nThe revision was approved. \n(8) Revision of the BS (Metallurgical Engineering) Program\nDr. Ordillas presented the proposal to revise the BSMetE program. Due to the increase in the number of units of the General Education Program (GEP) the total number of units in the BSMetE program was increased to 186. The revised program brings the total number of units down to 180. Dr. Ordillas also told the body that the section on institution of courses should be entitled : \"Institution of a Course\" since only one new course is being proposed. \nDue to similar corrections in the course lists of all the proposed revisions, the body agreed that the listing of courses (particularly those in the GEP) should be standardized. The College Secretary was requested to carry out the standardization. \nIn response to a question by Dr. J. Bala, the Secretary informed the body that the following notations have been the official U.P. designations of the engineering programs for at least two years now: \nPresent notation\nBachelor of Science (Chemical Engineering)\nBachelor of Science (Civil Engineering)\nBachelor of Science (Metallurgical Engineering)\nFormer notation\nBachelor of Science in Chemical Engineering\nBachelor of Science in Civil Engineering\nBachelor of Science in Metallurgical Engineering\nThe proposed revised BSMetE program was approved by the faculty. \n(9) Revision of the BS and MS Civil Engineering Programs\nProf. de Castro, Officer-in-Charge of the CE Department presented the significant features of the proposed revisions. He cited the increase in the units of the new GEP as one of the reasons which led to the revision of the BSCE program. \nDr. Pacheco cited some corrections in the notations of courses in the GEP and requested the inclusion of the current course checklist in the proposal. \nThe body approved the revised BSCE curriculum as corrected and the renumbering of the EnE courses as presented. With the exception of CE 245 all the graduate course revisions were approved. For CE 245 the CE Department was authorized to effect such changes as may be needed (even withdraw the course) after consultation with the staff of the School of Urban and Regional Planning. \n(10) Revision of the Bachelor of Computer Science (BCS) Program\nProf. Francisco presented the signficant features of the BCS program revision. He also cited the following corrections :\na) EE 38 and 29 should be replaced with EE 8 and 9, pursuant to the decisions of the body (see Item 3 of these minutes);\nb) Page 11 of the proposal should be deleted,\nc) IE 3 (instead of IE 31) should be placed in the list of electives;\nd) The footnote of the course checklist should be \"may be taken in Filipino or English\".\nDr. Pacheco made the comment that 20 units in the first year, second semester might be too heavy for freshman. Prof. Francisco replied that the three units cannot be absorbed in other semesters but may be taken in the summer session. The adviser should help the student decide whether the student\'s load will be 20 units or just 17 units with the other three to be taken in summer. Ms. Vencio supported the latter view and stated that the adviser and the student should decide on a case-to-case basis. \nDr. Pacheco suggested that the program be modified such that the first year second semester load would be 17 units with the three units being taken in the summer after the first year. This would allow the students to justify the summer session for scholarship purposes or to their parents, while act preventing the capable students from taking all of the 20 units during the semester. \nAfter some discussion the ES Department agreed to Dr. Pacheco\'s suggestion. Social Science II will be taken in the summer after the first year of the BCS program. \nThe faculty approved the revised BCS program as modified. \nIn response to Dr. Abis\' inquiry, Dean Garcia stated that the institution of an MSCS program is being considered. \n(11) Action on a Request for Extension of Resilience beyond 8-1/2 years \nThe request of Mr. Gerardo A. Remulla 76-01260 to take Shop 4 in the second semester 1986-87 and CMT in the summer of 1987 to allow him to obtain his BSME degree was approved by the faculty. \nThe Secretary will prepare the indorsement to the Chancellor, U.P. Diliman. \n(12) Other matters\na) The Secretary read a position paper made by the personnel of National Water Resources Council (NWRC) on the request of the faculty to retain the Water Resources library and databank at the National Hydraulic Research Council (NHRC). \nb) The Secretary reminded the faculty that the deadline for the submission of grades was last Monday, 13 October 1986. \n(13) The meeting was adjourned at 11:30 a.m. \n\nADOLFO JESUS R. GOPEZ\n\nCOLLEGE OF ENGINEERING \nUniversity of the Philippines\nDiliman, Quezon City\n\nCANDIDATES FOR GRADUATION\nFirst Semester, 1986-87\nWITHOUT DEFICIENCY\nGRADUATE\n\nI. For the degree of Master of Science :\nElectrical Engineering : (1) \n1. Esmail Ghelich Afshari\n2260-B Crisolita St., San Andres Bukid, M.M.\nB.S.E.E., Adamson University, 1981\nThesis Title : Design and Development of a Single Phase Power System Simulator\n\nEnergy Engineering : (1)\n1. Ruth Concepcion M. Dellota\n1114 Constancia, Sampaloc, M.M.\nB.S.Ch. E., University of the Philippines, 1982\nNon-Thesis Option\n\nII. For the degree of Master of Engineering :\nElectrical Engineering : (1)\n1. Loreto A. Marcelino\n472 Mabolo, Malolos, Bulacan\nB.S.E.E., University of the East, 1979\n\nIndustrial Engineering : (1)\n1. Ma. Theresa O. Lustre\n836 Moret St., Sampaloc, M.M.\nB.S.Ch.E., University of Santo Tomas, 1978\n\nIII. For the Diploma in Water Resources (1)\n1. Ambrocio R. Castaneda\nVillegas Subd., Los Banos, Laguna\nB.S. Agricultural Eng\'g., Central Luzon State University, Munoz, Nueva Ecija, 1974\n\nUNDERGRADUATE\nI. For the degree of Bachelor of Computer Science : \n1. Arthur P. Kho\nII. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Chemical Engineering) (2)\n1. Dulce L. Bernardo\n2. Higino P. Porte, Jr. \n\nIII. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Civil Engineering) : (10)\n1. Emmanuel R. Apilado\n2. Ricardo S. Consunji III\n3. Erwin L. Gomez\n4. Peter Noel P. Herrera\n5. Dantes S. Manuel, Jr.\n6. Joselito L. Matanguihan\n7. Jaime I. Nerona\n8. Darius Gregorio S. Parala\n9. Ronald Dominic C. Salazar\n10. Renato E. Teves\n\nIV. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Electrical Engineering) : (11)\n1. Genaro B. Catalan, Jr.\n2. Joseph C. Chavez\n3. Theodore C. de Veyra\n4. Ma. Socorro L. Feliciano\n5. Ray E. Gonzales\n6. Manuel J. Henares, Jr. \n7. Ramon E. Loria\n8. Domingo James M. Ramos\n9. Ramon P. Resma\n10. Arnel Q. Viduya\n11. Noel L. Viduya\n\nV. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Geodetic Engineering) : (2)\n1. Gemma A. Mercado\n2. Marvin C. Austria \n\nVI. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Industrial Engineering) : (7) \n1. Evelyn B. Alban\n2. Lynne Cleotilde S. Alzona\n3. Gregorio R. Ditching\n4. Berandette B. Mutuc\n5. Noel Lyndon A. Onggue\n6. Lawrence T. Raya\n7. James April G. Yap\n\nVII. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Mechanical Engineering) : (13)\n1. Rafael R. Aguila\n2. Jose Rene D. Benedicto\n3. Eugenio Roy A. Cordero\n4. Gerardo C. Dineros\n5. Carmelo Angelo H. Guerrero\n6. Cesar A. Laxamana\n7. Maria Lucia C. Limson\n8. Anthony Y. Mancao\n9. Angel P. Mejia, Jr. \n10. Victor Conrado C. Perez\n11. J. Milon L. Villa\n12. Cesar G. Romero cum laude, gen ave. - 1.736\n13. Ferdinand M. dela Cruz cum laude, gen ave. - 1.714\n\nVIII. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Metallurgical Eng\'g) : (1)\n1. Jose Leonard B. Adante, Jr. \n\nIX. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Mining Engineering) : (1)\n1. Virgilio L. Romero ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1585, 'E2-1585AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1986, June 2) ', 'COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING\nUniversity of the Philippines\nDiliman, Quezon City\n\nMEMORANDUM\n\nFor : ALL FACULTY MEMBERS\nCollege of Engineering\n\nFrom : The College Secretary\n\nThe 252nd faculty meeting of the College of Engineering will be held on WEDNESDAY 11 JUNE 1986, 1:30 p.m. at MH 410 (GE Conference Room) to enable the faculty to act on requests of undergraduate students for readmission and/or extension of residence more than eight and one-half years after the student\'s initial admission into the University (Faculty decision during the 251st meeting). The agenda is as follows : \n(1) Approval of minutes of the 251st meeting held on 24 March 1986;\n(2) Business arising from the minutes;\n(3) Approval of the candidates for graduation as of the end of Summer 1986.\n(4) Action on requests of undergraduate students for readmission and/or extension of residence;\n(5) Action on requests for change of grades;\n(6) Other matters. \n\nADOLFO JESUS R. GOPEZ ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1586, 'E2-1586AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'MINUTES OF THE 251ST ENGINEERING FACULTY MEETING HELD ON MARCH 24, 1986, ROOM 410, MELCHOR HALL ', '(1) The meeting was called to order at 2:20 p.m. with Dean Garcia presiding. \n(2) The minutes of the 250th was approved with the following correction : \nItem 5. Insert the word \"class\" before the word \"record\" in the last sentence of the last paragraph. \n(3) Business arising from the minutes : \n(a) General Education Program. Diliman approved 45 units while the system approved 42 (same as DIliman except for Spec. Thought).\n(b) ES 1 grade of Albert Mirani. The Registrar has verified that he has indeed passed ES I. Mr. Mirani\'s name was not included in Mr. Phil Torio\'s records because he had transferred sections. Relating to this matter, Dr. Pacheco suggested that a student not be issued a classcard unless he is enrolled in that class. \n(4) Approval of Candidates for Graduation. \nThe candidates for graduation as of the end of the second semester 1985-1986 as presented in the submitted list were approved by the faculty after endorsements by the Department Chairmen and the Director, Graduation Division. \nApproval of the graduation of the following three students involved in SDT CASE #85-007 was given on the condition that the case against them is decided in their favor : \nMANAHAN, Ronaldo R. \nLAO, Rufino S. \nJaranilla, Adrian P.S. \nThe following students names were withdrawn from the list of candidates with deficiencies : \nMANZANO, Enrique M. - No records with Registrar : Speech I and Span. II\nDELGADO, Florein S. - \"5\" in EE 3. \nThe following correction was also noted : \nThe name of Ms. Ma. Celeste L. Magsino (IE; no. 29 in the list of candidates with deficiencies) is not spelled correctly. \n(5) Other matters. \n(a) After some lengthy discussions of the case, Mr. Carmelo T. Casibang was granted one more semester of extension of his studies up to the end of the second semester 1985-1986. \n(b) Prof. A.P. Paran suggested that justifications for cross-enrolling in other units be documented. \n(c) Prof. E.S. Pacheco suggested that any extension beyond 8-1/2 years be brought to the faculty body. \n(6) The meeting was adjourned at 4:15 p.m.\n\nALEXANDER P. PARAN\nOfficer-in-Charge\n\nLIST OF CANDIDATES FOR GRADUATION AT THE END OF THE SECOND SEMESTER, 1985-1986 WHO WERE CLEARED FOR GRADUATION (TAKEN FROM THE LIST OF \"CONDITIONALLY\" APPROVED NAMES\nI. For the degree of Bachelor of Computer Science : \n1. Mary Anne L. Alde \n2. Diana Min Tung C. Ang\n3. John R. Apacible \n4. Joselito M. Baetiong\n5. Monica Isabel R. Carale\nmagna cum laude \n6. Anna Katharyna Ascencion C. Chan\n7. Darryl T. Co, cum laude\n8. Ronora A. Covar, cum laude\n9. Lenore Emily T. Cruz\n10. Efraim P. David\n11. Ma. Paz Trinidad de Castro, cum laude\n12. Juliana M. de Guia\n13. Alfred John A. de Veyra\n14. Melinda T. Gervasio, magna cum laude\n15. Roterna M. Gustillo \n16. Anna J. Hernandez\nmagna cum laude\n17. Manolo C. Jorge\n18. Juven Yan J. Joson\n19. Noeme Gertrude Asteria F. Madamba\nmagna cum laude\n20. Chak Ho T. Ng\n21. Aurora Socorro D. Ocampo\n22. Maria Riza B. Padolina\n23. Ma. Elorita T. Pasco\n24. Arnold C. Roxas\n25. Celeste G. Santos\n26. Maria Theresa U. Santos\n27. Celine G. See, cum laude\n28. Ma. Estrella Bernardita P. Sinense, cum laude\n29. Jude Thadeus U. Socrates, magna cum laude\nII. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Chemical Engineering) : \n1. Edgardo N. Agbigay\n2. Roy R. Alminanza, cum laude\n3. Emmanuel D. Bautista, magna cum laude\n4. Cecilia Ursula R. Briones\n5. Reuben Reuel T. Comagon\n6. Cesar S. dela Cruz\n7. Remigio A. de Ungria, Jr.\n8. Alexander F. Diaz, magna cum laude\n9. Lourdes C. Dy Quiangco\n10. Aida D. Fernandez\n11. Anna Marie S. Fernando\n12. Natalie S. Go\n13. Pancho E. Josafat\n14. Anthony S. Mariano\n15. Marcelito Y. Narcida\n16. Jose Maria A. Ochave \n17. Ethel Teresita H. Olaer\n18. Annabella M. Pangan\n19. Myrna E. Punzalan\n20. Hector V. Rivera III\n21. Jonathan Winston L. Salvacion, cum laude\n22. Eugen T. Tan\n23. Maria Angela A. Virata\n24. Ma. Ruth R. Martirez, cum laude \n*Probable with honors \nIII. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Civil Engineering) : \n1. Dante M. Abando \n2. Jose Rojo G. Alisla\n3. Patrocenio F. Arcenal, Jr. \n4. Ernesto F. Botin, Jr. \n5. Venn Ronald P. Cabalu\n6. Jose Wielelmino G. Carlos, magna cum laude\n7. Delfino R. Consunji\n8. Ariel C. Corpuz \n9. Armand P. Cruel\n10. Martin Ericson S. Cruel \n18. Michael B. Kabiling\n19. Adonis M. Langcauon\n20. Anson G. Lee\n21. Ronaldo Jose R. Manahan\n22. Jason B. Mendoza\n23. Felix C. Narito, Jr. \n24. Gatmahal Johann R. Ochoco, magna cum laude\n25. Gerardo S. Pangan\n26. Gaudencio C. Pascual, Jr. \n27. Rolando S. Punla \nVII. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Mechanical Eng\'g.) :\n1. Armando N. Arciaga, Jr. \n2. Francisco B. Baytan\n3. Roman R. Buenafe\n4. Conrado U. Bulanhagui\n5. Jorge L. Bustamante\n6. Alfredo Michael T. Camacho\n7. Leomyr L. de Jesus\n8. Gerardo R. Ditching\n9. C.C. Rajan R. Francisco\n10. Edwin S. Guiang\n11. Adrain Philip S. Jaranilla\n12. Romeo F. Jimenez\n13. Angelito L. Joson\n14. Jonathan R. Joson\n15. Roquito P. Mallorca\n16. Pio Diomedes B. Manalo\n17. Augusto P. Mathay\n18. Gerafil J. Placido\n19. Ramon Jose A. Ramos\n20. Andrew Dominic J. Santos\n21. Hugh Arnold L. Soriano\n22. Reinato Fidel A. Velasco \nVIII. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Metallurgical Eng\'g) :\n1. Jesus M. Alonsagay, Jr. \n2. Gerardo C. Angeles cum laude\n3. Reu Fred M. Dellota cum laude\n4. Agustin M. Fudolig\nIX. For the degree of Bachelor of Science (Mining Engineering) : \n1. Felipe Edsel P. Carandang\nX. For the degree of MASTER OF SCIENCE (Civil Engineering) :\n1. LEONCIO Q. BAUTISTA\n9 Marathon St. Q.C.\nB.S. (Civil Engineering)\nUniversity of the Philippines', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49'),
(1587, 'E2-1587AC', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '(1986, March 20) 251st Engineering Faculty Meeting  ', 'Memorandum \nFor : ALL FACULTY MEMBERS\nCollege of Engineering\nFrom : The Officer-In-Charge \nOffice of the College Secretary \nThe 251st Engineering Faculty Meeting will be held on MONDAY, 24 March 1986 at 2:00 PM in Room 410.\n\nAGENDA : \n1. Approval of the minutes of the 250th meeting. \n2. Business arising from the minutes.\n3. Approval of course revisions. \n4. Approval of the candidates for graduation as of the end of the second semester, 1985-86. \n5. Other matters. \n\nALEXANDER P. PARAN\nOfficer-In-Charge\n\n(1) The meeting was called to order at 1:25 p.m., Dean R.A. Garcia presiding. \n(2) The minutes of the 247th, 248th and 249th faculty meeting were approved with the following corrections : \na) 247th meeting\ni) to be added to the list of members present : Mr. Conrado Rotor, Mr. Arturo Santos\nii) to be added to the list of members on leave : Mr. Gino T. Bautista \niii) to be moved from the list of members absent to the list of members on special detail : Dr. Francisco L. Viray\niv) corrections in the names of new faculty members : Geraldo Quelapio instead of Gerard Ragnar Ledesma instead of Ramer\nb) 248th meeting\ni) to be added to the list of members present : Mr. Conrado Rotor and Mr. Arturo Santos\nii) to be added to the list of members on leave : Mr. Gino T. Bautista\niii) page 4, Item 4h-c : \n... \"to prevent any confusion\"... instead of\n... \" to prevent ant\"\n... \"CS 70...\" instead of ...\"CE 70...\"\niv) page 4, Item 4i\n\"To consolidate these recommendations and to present the Engineering...\"instead of\"... and to prevent the Engineering...\"\nc) 249th meeting\ni) correction in list of members present : \nMr. J. Reyes instead of Jr. J. Reyes\nMr. F. L. Serrano instead of Mr. F.L. Forado\nii) to be added to the list of members present : \nDr. M.V. Hernandez, Jr. \n(3) The following new members of the faculty were introduced by their chairmen : \nMetE Dept. : Jesus Noel A. Calata, Jr. \nCE Dept. : Michael V. Gonzales\nRolando Orense\nAndre S. Publico\nEE Dept. : Aurelio Pimentel\n(4) Business arising from the minutes : \na) General Education (G.E.) Program\nA system-wide G.E. Conference (248th meeting) will be held on 15 to 17 December 1985. Dr. Gopez will be attending at the request of Dean Garcia.\nb) National Telecommunications Institute (NTI)\nThe Dean informed the Body that there is no longer a need for a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) between the U.P. and the MOTC. \nPres. Angara and Minister Dans have already drafted a letter to the President of the Philippines to be submitted with a draft of an Executive Order empowering the U.P. Board of Regents to create the NTI and to determine the working relationship between the U.P. and MOTC. According to one of the memoranda issued by the Office of the U.P. President, the NTI will be attached to the U.P. College of Engineering. \nThe papers have already been endorsed by the Prime Minister and are already at Malacañang.\nDr. G.T. Marzan pointed out that Item 5d-i (pages 6) of the minutes of the 248th has now been answered. \nMr. E. Gonzales asked about the role of the College faculty in the creation of the NTI. Dean Garcia replied that the unit will be attached to the College but no structure nor procedure presently exist for its establishment. No details are as yet available. Establishment of the NTI will be a first experience. \n(5) Approval of Candidates for Graduation\nThe candidates for graduation as of the end of the first semester, 1985-86 as presented in the submitted list were approved by the faculty after endorsements by the Department Chairmen and the Director, Graduate Division. The following correction was noted for Master of Science, Civil Engineering : \nPeter S. Lim obtained his B.S.C.E. from University of Santo Tomas\nThe case of Albert Mirani, candidate for the degree of B.S.Ch.E. with deficiency was discussed. Mr. Mirani gave a classcard stub in ES I signed by the instructor, Mr. Phil Torio as proof that he has finished and passed the said subject. However, Mr. Mirani\'s name is not on the grade sheet submitted by Mr. Torio. The E.S. Department will ask Mr. Torio to verify his signature and if needed, submit a report of grade. In this connection, it was suggested that departing faculty members be required to leave with the Department their record books or \"hard copies\" of their records. \n(6) Change of Grade/Status\nThe following requests for change of grade/status were approved by the faculty : \nName of Student \n1) OFRENEO, Jehmel C. - EE 197 - 2.5 - 2.0 - 1/85-86  J.A. Kirsch\n2) SIRILAN, Melchor P. - ES 15  - 4.0 - 2.75 - 1/85/86  L.Q. Liongson\n3) COCHINGYAN, Eric U. - CE 80 - INC - DRP - 1/85/86  S.E. Reyes \n4) DIAZ, Abelardo - CS 12 - 4.0 - 3.0 - 1/85/86  M.L.S. Vencio\n5) DIAZ, Alexander F.  ChE 55 - 2.0 - 1.5 - 1/85-86 - J.C. Muñoz\n6) DUCLAYAN, Aileen - CE 71 - 5.0 - 3.0 - 1/85-86  - G.V. Aristoreans\n7) DE GUZMAN, Joel - IE 53 - 1.25 - 1.0 - 1/85-86 - E.M. Gonzales\n(7) Other matters\na) The faculty approved the change in the prerequisite of MetE 12 as endorsed by the College Executive Committee, from prerequisite : Physics 72 to co-requisite : Physics 72.\nb) The Secretary announced a change in the contributions for the Christmas party. \nc) The Dean reminded the faculty members of the Engineering Conference on Friday, 13 December 1985.\nd) In preparation for the visit of the UGC (India) Delegation, the Dean asked the Chairmen, Dean Mena and Dr. L.Q. Liongson to stay behind. \n(8) The meeting was adjourned at 2:30 p.m. \n\nADOLFO JESUS R. GOPEZ, Dr. -Ing. \nSecretary ', '', NULL, NULL, 'Public (Metadata Only)', 'active', '2026-03-18 08:36:49', '2026-03-18 08:36:49');
